147 GCGLint clamp(GCGLint value, GCGLint min, GCGLint max)
148 {
149 if (value < min)
150 value = min;
151 if (value > max)
152 value = max;
153 return value;
154 }
155
156 // Return true if a character belongs to the ASCII subset as defined in
157 // GLSL ES 1.0 spec section 3.1.
158 bool validateCharacter(unsigned char c)
159 {
160 // Printing characters are valid except " $ ` @ \ ' DEL.
161 if (c >= 32 && c <= 126
162 && c != '"' && c != '$' && c != '`' && c != '@' && c != '\\' && c != '\'')
163 return true;
164 // Horizontal tab, line feed, vertical tab, form feed, carriage return
165 // are also valid.
166 if (c >= 9 && c <= 13)
167 return true;
168 return false;
169 }
170
171 bool isPrefixReserved(const String& name)
172 {
173 if (name.startsWith("gl_") || name.startsWith("webgl_") || name.startsWith("_webgl_"))
174 return true;
175 return false;
176 }
177
178 // Strips comments from shader text. This allows non-ASCII characters
179 // to be used in comments without potentially breaking OpenGL
180 // implementations not expecting characters outside the GLSL ES set.
181 class StripComments {
182 public:
183 StripComments(const String& str)
184 : m_parseState(BeginningOfLine)
185 , m_sourceString(str)
186 , m_length(str.length())
187 , m_position(0)
188 {
189 parse();
190 }
191
192 String result()
193 {
194 return m_builder.toString();
195 }
196
197 private:
198 bool hasMoreCharacters() const
199 {
200 return (m_position < m_length);
201 }
202
203 void parse()
204 {
205 while (hasMoreCharacters()) {
206 process(current());
207 // process() might advance the position.
208 if (hasMoreCharacters())
209 advance();
210 }
211 }
212
213 void process(UChar);
214
215 bool peek(UChar& character) const
216 {
217 if (m_position + 1 >= m_length)
218 return false;
219 character = m_sourceString[m_position + 1];
220 return true;
221 }
222
223 UChar current() const
224 {
225 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(m_position < m_length);
226 return m_sourceString[m_position];
227 }
228
229 void advance()
230 {
231 ++m_position;
232 }
233
234 bool isNewline(UChar character) const
235 {
236 // Don't attempt to canonicalize newline related characters.
237 return (character == '\n' || character == '\r');
238 }
239
240 void emit(UChar character)
241 {
242 m_builder.append(character);
243 }
244
245 enum ParseState {
246 // Have not seen an ASCII non-whitespace character yet on
247 // this line. Possible that we might see a preprocessor
248 // directive.
249 BeginningOfLine,
250
251 // Have seen at least one ASCII non-whitespace character
252 // on this line.
253 MiddleOfLine,
254
255 // Handling a preprocessor directive. Passes through all
256 // characters up to the end of the line. Disables comment
257 // processing.
258 InPreprocessorDirective,
259
260 // Handling a single-line comment. The comment text is
261 // replaced with a single space.
262 InSingleLineComment,
263
264 // Handling a multi-line comment. Newlines are passed
265 // through to preserve line numbers.
266 InMultiLineComment
267 };
268
269 ParseState m_parseState;
270 String m_sourceString;
271 unsigned m_length;
272 unsigned m_position;
273 StringBuilder m_builder;
274 };
275
276 void StripComments::process(UChar c)
277 {
278 if (isNewline(c)) {
279 // No matter what state we are in, pass through newlines
280 // so we preserve line numbers.
281 emit(c);
282
283 if (m_parseState != InMultiLineComment)
284 m_parseState = BeginningOfLine;
285
286 return;
287 }
288
289 UChar temp = 0;
290 switch (m_parseState) {
291 case BeginningOfLine:
292 if (WTF::isASCIISpace(c)) {
293 emit(c);
294 break;
295 }
296
297 if (c == '#') {
298 m_parseState = InPreprocessorDirective;
299 emit(c);
300 break;
301 }
302
303 // Transition to normal state and re-handle character.
304 m_parseState = MiddleOfLine;
305 process(c);
306 break;
307
308 case MiddleOfLine:
309 if (c == '/' && peek(temp)) {
310 if (temp == '/') {
311 m_parseState = InSingleLineComment;
312 emit(' ');
313 advance();
314 break;
315 }
316
317 if (temp == '*') {
318 m_parseState = InMultiLineComment;
319 // Emit the comment start in case the user has
320 // an unclosed comment and we want to later
321 // signal an error.
322 emit('/');
323 emit('*');
324 advance();
325 break;
326 }
327 }
328
329 emit(c);
330 break;
331
332 case InPreprocessorDirective:
333 // No matter what the character is, just pass it
334 // through. Do not parse comments in this state. This
335 // might not be the right thing to do long term, but it
336 // should handle the #error preprocessor directive.
337 emit(c);
338 break;
339
340 case InSingleLineComment:
341 // The newline code at the top of this function takes care
342 // of resetting our state when we get out of the
343 // single-line comment. Swallow all other characters.
344 break;
345
346 case InMultiLineComment:
347 if (c == '*' && peek(temp) && temp == '/') {
348 emit('*');
349 emit('/');
350 m_parseState = MiddleOfLine;
351 advance();
352 break;
353 }
354
355 // Swallow all other characters. Unclear whether we may
356 // want or need to just emit a space per character to try
357 // to preserve column numbers for debugging purposes.
358 break;
359 }
360 }

450class ScopedUnpackParametersResetRestore {
451public:
452 explicit ScopedUnpackParametersResetRestore(WebGLRenderingContextBase* context, bool enabled = true)
453 : m_context(context), m_enabled(enabled)
454 {
455 if (m_enabled)
456 m_context->resetUnpackParameters();
457 }
458
459 ~ScopedUnpackParametersResetRestore()
460 {
461 if (m_enabled)
462 m_context->restoreUnpackParameters();
463 }
464
465private:
466 WebGLRenderingContextBase* m_context;
467 bool m_enabled;
468};

470class ScopedDisableRasterizerDiscard {
471public:
472 explicit ScopedDisableRasterizerDiscard(WebGLRenderingContextBase* context, bool wasEnabled)
473 : m_context(context)
474 , m_wasEnabled(wasEnabled)
475 {
476 if (m_wasEnabled)
477 m_context->disable(GraphicsContextGL::RASTERIZER_DISCARD);
478 }
479
480 ~ScopedDisableRasterizerDiscard()
481 {
482 if (m_wasEnabled)
483 m_context->enable(GraphicsContextGL::RASTERIZER_DISCARD);
484 }
485
486private:
487 WebGLRenderingContextBase* m_context;
488 bool m_wasEnabled;
489};

491#define ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(set, arr) \
492 set.add(arr, arr + WTF_ARRAY_LENGTH(arr))

494#if !USE(ANGLE)
495// Returns false if no clipping is necessary, i.e., x, y, width, height stay the same.
496static bool clip2D(GCGLint x, GCGLint y, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height,
497 GCGLsizei sourceWidth, GCGLsizei sourceHeight,
498 GCGLint* clippedX, GCGLint* clippedY, GCGLsizei* clippedWidth, GCGLsizei*clippedHeight)
499{
500 ASSERT(clippedX && clippedY && clippedWidth && clippedHeight);
501
502 GCGLint left = std::max(x, 0);
503 GCGLint top = std::max(y, 0);
504 GCGLint right = 0;
505 GCGLint bottom = 0;
506
507 Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow> checkedInputRight = Checked<GCGLint>(x) + Checked<GCGLsizei>(width);
508 Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow> checkedInputBottom = Checked<GCGLint>(y) + Checked<GCGLsizei>(height);
509 if (!checkedInputRight.hasOverflowed() && !checkedInputBottom.hasOverflowed()) {
510 right = std::min(checkedInputRight.value(), sourceWidth);
511 bottom = std::min(checkedInputBottom.value(), sourceHeight);
512 }
513
514 if (left >= right || top >= bottom) {
515 *clippedX = 0;
516 *clippedY = 0;
517 *clippedWidth = 0;
518 *clippedHeight = 0;
519 return true;
520 }
521
522 *clippedX = left;
523 *clippedY = top;
524 *clippedWidth = right - left;
525 *clippedHeight = bottom - top;
526
527 return (*clippedX != x || *clippedY != y || *clippedWidth != width || *clippedHeight != height);
528}
529#endif

531class InspectorScopedShaderProgramHighlight {
532public:
533 InspectorScopedShaderProgramHighlight(WebGLRenderingContextBase& context, WebGLProgram* program)
534 : m_context(context)
535 , m_program(program)
536 {
537 showHightlight();
538 }
539
540 ~InspectorScopedShaderProgramHighlight()
541 {
542 hideHighlight();
543 }
544
545private:
546 void showHightlight()
547 {
548 if (!m_program || LIKELY(!InspectorInstrumentation::isWebGLProgramHighlighted(m_context, *m_program)))
549 return;
550
551 if (hasBufferBinding(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING)) {
552 if (!hasBufferBinding(GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_BINDING))
553 return;
554 if (hasFramebufferParameterAttachment(GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_ATTACHMENT))
555 return;
556 if (hasFramebufferParameterAttachment(GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_ATTACHMENT))
557 return;
558#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
559 if (hasFramebufferParameterAttachment(GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT))
560 return;
561#endif
562 }
563
564 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_COLOR, m_savedBlend.color);
565 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_EQUATION_RGB, m_savedBlend.equationRGB);
566 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_EQUATION_ALPHA, m_savedBlend.equationAlpha);
567 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_SRC_RGB, m_savedBlend.srcRGB);
568 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_SRC_ALPHA, m_savedBlend.srcAlpha);
569 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_DST_RGB, m_savedBlend.dstRGB);
570 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_DST_ALPHA, m_savedBlend.dstAlpha);
571 saveBlendValue(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND, m_savedBlend.enabled);
572
573 static const GCGLfloat red = 111.0 / 255.0;
574 static const GCGLfloat green = 168.0 / 255.0;
575 static const GCGLfloat blue = 220.0 / 255.0;
576 static const GCGLfloat alpha = 2.0 / 3.0;
577
578 m_context.enable(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND);
579 m_context.blendColor(red, green, blue, alpha);
580 m_context.blendEquation(GraphicsContextGL::FUNC_ADD);
581 m_context.blendFunc(GraphicsContextGL::CONSTANT_COLOR, GraphicsContextGL::ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA);
582
583 m_didApply = true;
584 }
585
586 void hideHighlight()
587 {
588 if (!m_didApply)
589 return;
590
591 if (!m_savedBlend.enabled)
592 m_context.disable(GraphicsContextGL::BLEND);
593
594 const RefPtr<Float32Array>& color = m_savedBlend.color;
595 m_context.blendColor(color->item(0), color->item(1), color->item(2), color->item(3));
596 m_context.blendEquationSeparate(m_savedBlend.equationRGB, m_savedBlend.equationAlpha);
597 m_context.blendFuncSeparate(m_savedBlend.srcRGB, m_savedBlend.dstRGB, m_savedBlend.srcAlpha, m_savedBlend.dstAlpha);
598
599 m_savedBlend.color = nullptr;
600
601 m_didApply = false;
602 }
603
604 template <typename T>
605 void saveBlendValue(GCGLenum attachment, T& destination)
606 {
607 WebGLAny param = m_context.getParameter(attachment);
608 if (WTF::holds_alternative<T>(param))
609 destination = WTF::get<T>(param);
610 }
611
612 bool hasBufferBinding(GCGLenum pname)
613 {
614 WebGLAny binding = m_context.getParameter(pname);
615 if (pname == GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING)
616 return WTF::holds_alternative<RefPtr<WebGLFramebuffer>>(binding) && WTF::get<RefPtr<WebGLFramebuffer>>(binding);
617 if (pname == GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_BINDING)
618 return WTF::holds_alternative<RefPtr<WebGLRenderbuffer>>(binding) && WTF::get<RefPtr<WebGLRenderbuffer>>(binding);
619 return false;
620 }
621
622 bool hasFramebufferParameterAttachment(GCGLenum attachment)
623 {
624 WebGLAny attachmentParameter = m_context.getFramebufferAttachmentParameter(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, attachment, GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE);
625 if (!WTF::holds_alternative<unsigned>(attachmentParameter))
626 return false;
627 if (WTF::get<unsigned>(attachmentParameter) != static_cast<unsigned>(GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER))
628 return false;
629 return true;
630 }
631
632 struct {
633 RefPtr<Float32Array> color;
634 unsigned equationRGB { 0 };
635 unsigned equationAlpha { 0 };
636 unsigned srcRGB { 0 };
637 unsigned srcAlpha { 0 };
638 unsigned dstRGB { 0 };
639 unsigned dstAlpha { 0 };
640 bool enabled { false };
641 } m_savedBlend;
642
643 WebGLRenderingContextBase& m_context;
644 WebGLProgram* m_program { nullptr };
645 bool m_didApply { false };
646};
647
648static bool isHighPerformanceContext(const RefPtr<GraphicsContextGL>& context)
649{
650 return context->contextAttributes().powerPreference == WebGLPowerPreference::HighPerformance;
651}
652
653std::unique_ptr<WebGLRenderingContextBase> WebGLRenderingContextBase::create(CanvasBase& canvas, WebGLContextAttributes& attributes, WebGLVersion type)
654{
655 auto scriptExecutionContext = canvas.scriptExecutionContext();
656 if (!scriptExecutionContext)
657 return nullptr;
658
659#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
660 // Note: WebGL 2.0 is only supported with the ANGLE backend.
661 if (type == GraphicsContextGLWebGLVersion::WebGL2 && !scriptExecutionContext->settingsValues().webGL2Enabled)
662 return nullptr;
663#else
664 UNUSED_PARAM(type);
665#endif
666
667 bool isPendingPolicyResolution = false;
668 HostWindow* hostWindow = nullptr;
669
670 auto* canvasElement = is<HTMLCanvasElement>(canvas) ? &downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(canvas) : nullptr;
671
672 if (canvasElement) {
673 Document& document = canvasElement->document();
674 RefPtr<Frame> frame = document.frame();
675 if (!frame)
676 return nullptr;
677
678 // The FrameLoaderClient might block creation of a new WebGL context despite the page settings; in
679 // particular, if WebGL contexts were lost one or more times via the GL_ARB_robustness extension.
680 if (!frame->loader().client().allowWebGL(frame->settings().webGLEnabled())) {
681 canvasElement->dispatchEvent(WebGLContextEvent::create(eventNames().webglcontextcreationerrorEvent,
682 Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes, "Web page was not allowed to create a WebGL context."));
683 return nullptr;
684 }
685
686 Document& topDocument = document.topDocument();
687 Page* page = topDocument.page();
688 bool forcingPendingPolicy = frame->settings().isForcePendingWebGLPolicy();
689
690 if (forcingPendingPolicy || (page && !topDocument.url().isLocalFile())) {
691 WebGLLoadPolicy policy = forcingPendingPolicy ? WebGLLoadPolicy::WebGLPendingCreation : page->mainFrame().loader().client().webGLPolicyForURL(topDocument.url());
692
693 if (policy == WebGLLoadPolicy::WebGLBlockCreation) {
694 LOG(WebGL, "The policy for this URL (%s) is to block WebGL.", topDocument.url().host().utf8().data());
695 return nullptr;
696 }
697
698 if (policy == WebGLLoadPolicy::WebGLPendingCreation) {
699 LOG(WebGL, "WebGL policy is pending. May need to be resolved later.");
700 isPendingPolicyResolution = true;
701 }
702 }
703
704 if (frame->settings().forceWebGLUsesLowPower()) {
705 if (attributes.powerPreference == GraphicsContextGLPowerPreference::HighPerformance)
706 LOG(WebGL, "Overriding powerPreference from high-performance to low-power.");
707 attributes.powerPreference = GraphicsContextGLPowerPreference::LowPower;
708 }
709
710 if (page)
711 attributes.devicePixelRatio = page->deviceScaleFactor();
712
713 hostWindow = document.view()->root()->hostWindow();
714 }
715
716 attributes.noExtensions = true;
717 attributes.shareResources = false;
718 attributes.initialPowerPreference = attributes.powerPreference;
719 attributes.webGLVersion = type;
720
721#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
722 if (scriptExecutionContext->settingsValues().webGLUsingMetal)
723 attributes.useMetal = true;
724#endif
725
726 if (isPendingPolicyResolution) {
727 LOG(WebGL, "Create a WebGL context that looks real, but will require a policy resolution if used.");
728 std::unique_ptr<WebGLRenderingContextBase> renderingContext = nullptr;
729#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
730 if (type == WebGLVersion::WebGL2)
731 renderingContext = WebGL2RenderingContext::create(canvas, attributes);
732 else
733#endif
734 renderingContext = WebGLRenderingContext::create(canvas, attributes);
735 renderingContext->suspendIfNeeded();
736 return renderingContext;
737 }
738 auto context = GraphicsContextGL::create(attributes, hostWindow);
739 if (!context) {
740 if (canvasElement) {
741 canvasElement->dispatchEvent(WebGLContextEvent::create(eventNames().webglcontextcreationerrorEvent,
742 Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes, "Could not create a WebGL context."));
743 }
744 return nullptr;
745 }
746
747 std::unique_ptr<WebGLRenderingContextBase> renderingContext;
748#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
749 if (type == WebGLVersion::WebGL2)
750 renderingContext = WebGL2RenderingContext::create(canvas, context.releaseNonNull(), attributes);
751 else
752#endif
753 renderingContext = WebGLRenderingContext::create(canvas, context.releaseNonNull(), attributes);
754 renderingContext->suspendIfNeeded();
755
756 return renderingContext;
757}
758
759WebGLRenderingContextBase::WebGLRenderingContextBase(CanvasBase& canvas, WebGLContextAttributes attributes)
760 : GPUBasedCanvasRenderingContext(canvas)
761 , m_restoreTimer(canvas.scriptExecutionContext(), *this, &WebGLRenderingContextBase::maybeRestoreContext)
762 , m_attributes(attributes)
763 , m_numGLErrorsToConsoleAllowed(maxGLErrorsAllowedToConsole)
764 , m_isPendingPolicyResolution(true)
765 , m_checkForContextLossHandlingTimer(*this, &WebGLRenderingContextBase::checkForContextLossHandling)
766#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
767 , m_isXRCompatible(attributes.xrCompatible)
768#endif
769{
770 m_restoreTimer.suspendIfNeeded();
771
772 registerWithWebGLStateTracker();
773 if (canvas.isHTMLCanvasElement())
774 m_checkForContextLossHandlingTimer.startOneShot(checkContextLossHandlingDelay);
775}
776
777WebGLRenderingContextBase::WebGLRenderingContextBase(CanvasBase& canvas, Ref<GraphicsContextGL>&& context, WebGLContextAttributes attributes)
778 : GPUBasedCanvasRenderingContext(canvas)
779 , m_context(WTFMove(context))
780 , m_restoreTimer(canvas.scriptExecutionContext(), *this, &WebGLRenderingContextBase::maybeRestoreContext)
781 , m_generatedImageCache(4)
782 , m_attributes(attributes)
783 , m_numGLErrorsToConsoleAllowed(maxGLErrorsAllowedToConsole)
784 , m_checkForContextLossHandlingTimer(*this, &WebGLRenderingContextBase::checkForContextLossHandling)
785#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
786 , m_isXRCompatible(attributes.xrCompatible)
787#endif
788{
789 m_restoreTimer.suspendIfNeeded();
790
791 m_contextGroup = WebGLContextGroup::create();
792 m_contextGroup->addContext(*this);
793
794 m_context->addClient(*this);
795
796 m_context->getIntegerv(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_VIEWPORT_DIMS, m_maxViewportDims);
797
798 setupFlags();
799
800 registerWithWebGLStateTracker();
801 if (canvas.isHTMLCanvasElement())
802 m_checkForContextLossHandlingTimer.startOneShot(checkContextLossHandlingDelay);
803
804 addActivityStateChangeObserverIfNecessary();
805}
806
807WebGLCanvas WebGLRenderingContextBase::canvas()
808{
809 auto& base = canvasBase();
810#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS)
811 if (is<OffscreenCanvas>(base))
812 return &downcast<OffscreenCanvas>(base);
813#endif
814 return &downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(base);
815}
816
817#if ENABLE(OFFSCREEN_CANVAS)
818OffscreenCanvas* WebGLRenderingContextBase::offscreenCanvas()
819{
820 auto& base = canvasBase();
821 if (!is<OffscreenCanvas>(base))
822 return nullptr;
823 return &downcast<OffscreenCanvas>(base);
824}
825#endif
826
827// We check for context loss handling after a few seconds to give the JS a chance to register the event listeners
828// and to discard temporary GL contexts (e.g. feature detection).
829void WebGLRenderingContextBase::checkForContextLossHandling()
830{
831 auto canvas = htmlCanvas();
832 if (!canvas)
833 return;
834
835 if (!canvas->renderer())
836 return;
837
838 auto* page = canvas->document().page();
839 if (!page)
840 return;
841
842 bool handlesContextLoss = canvas->hasEventListeners(eventNames().webglcontextlostEvent) && canvas->hasEventListeners(eventNames().webglcontextrestoredEvent);
843 page->diagnosticLoggingClient().logDiagnosticMessage(DiagnosticLoggingKeys::pageHandlesWebGLContextLossKey(), handlesContextLoss ? DiagnosticLoggingKeys::yesKey() : DiagnosticLoggingKeys::noKey(), ShouldSample::No);
844}
845
846void WebGLRenderingContextBase::registerWithWebGLStateTracker()
847{
848 auto canvas = htmlCanvas();
849 if (!canvas)
850 return;
851
852 auto* page = canvas->document().page();
853 if (!page)
854 return;
855
856 auto* tracker = page->webGLStateTracker();
857 if (!tracker)
858 return;
859
860 m_trackerToken = tracker->token(m_attributes.initialPowerPreference);
861}
862
863void WebGLRenderingContextBase::initializeNewContext()
864{
865 ASSERT(!m_contextLost);
866 m_needsUpdate = true;
867 m_markedCanvasDirty = false;
868 m_activeTextureUnit = 0;
869 m_packAlignment = 4;
870 m_unpackAlignment = 4;
871 m_unpackFlipY = false;
872 m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha = false;
873 m_unpackColorspaceConversion = GraphicsContextGL::BROWSER_DEFAULT_WEBGL;
874 m_boundArrayBuffer = nullptr;
875 m_currentProgram = nullptr;
876 m_framebufferBinding = nullptr;
877 m_renderbufferBinding = nullptr;
878 m_depthMask = true;
879 m_stencilEnabled = false;
880 m_stencilMask = 0xFFFFFFFF;
881 m_stencilMaskBack = 0xFFFFFFFF;
882 m_stencilFuncRef = 0;
883 m_stencilFuncRefBack = 0;
884 m_stencilFuncMask = 0xFFFFFFFF;
885 m_stencilFuncMaskBack = 0xFFFFFFFF;
886 m_layerCleared = false;
887 m_numGLErrorsToConsoleAllowed = maxGLErrorsAllowedToConsole;
888
889 m_rasterizerDiscardEnabled = false;
890
891 m_clearColor[0] = m_clearColor[1] = m_clearColor[2] = m_clearColor[3] = 0;
892 m_scissorEnabled = false;
893 m_clearDepth = 1;
894 m_clearStencil = 0;
895 m_colorMask[0] = m_colorMask[1] = m_colorMask[2] = m_colorMask[3] = true;
896
897 GCGLint numCombinedTextureImageUnits = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_COMBINED_TEXTURE_IMAGE_UNITS);
898 m_textureUnits.clear();
899 m_textureUnits.resize(numCombinedTextureImageUnits);
900#if !USE(ANGLE)
901 for (GCGLint i = 0; i < numCombinedTextureImageUnits; ++i)
902 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(i);
903#endif
904
905 GCGLint numVertexAttribs = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_VERTEX_ATTRIBS);
906 m_maxVertexAttribs = numVertexAttribs;
907
908 m_maxTextureSize = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE);
909 m_maxTextureLevel = WebGLTexture::computeLevelCount(m_maxTextureSize, m_maxTextureSize);
910 m_maxCubeMapTextureSize = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_CUBE_MAP_TEXTURE_SIZE);
911 m_maxCubeMapTextureLevel = WebGLTexture::computeLevelCount(m_maxCubeMapTextureSize, m_maxCubeMapTextureSize);
912 m_maxRenderbufferSize = m_context->getInteger(GraphicsContextGL::MAX_RENDERBUFFER_SIZE);
913
914 // These two values from EXT_draw_buffers are lazily queried.
915 m_maxDrawBuffers = 0;
916 m_maxColorAttachments = 0;
917
918 m_backDrawBuffer = GraphicsContextGL::BACK;
919 m_drawBuffersWebGLRequirementsChecked = false;
920 m_drawBuffersSupported = false;
921
922 m_vertexAttribValue.resize(m_maxVertexAttribs);
923
924#if !USE(ANGLE)
925 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
926 createFallbackBlackTextures1x1();
927#endif
928
929 IntSize canvasSize = clampedCanvasSize();
930 m_context->reshape(canvasSize.width(), canvasSize.height());
931 m_context->viewport(0, 0, canvasSize.width(), canvasSize.height());
932 m_context->scissor(0, 0, canvasSize.width(), canvasSize.height());
933
934 m_supportedTexImageSourceInternalFormats.clear();
935 m_supportedTexImageSourceFormats.clear();
936 m_supportedTexImageSourceTypes.clear();
937 m_areWebGL2TexImageSourceFormatsAndTypesAdded = false;
938 m_areOESTextureFloatFormatsAndTypesAdded = false;
939 m_areOESTextureHalfFloatFormatsAndTypesAdded = false;
940 m_areEXTsRGBFormatsAndTypesAdded = false;
941 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceInternalFormats, SupportedFormatsES2);
942 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceFormats, SupportedFormatsES2);
943 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceTypes, SupportedTypesES2);
944
945 initializeVertexArrayObjects();
946}
947
948void WebGLRenderingContextBase::setupFlags()
949{
950 ASSERT(m_context);
951
952 auto canvas = htmlCanvas();
953 if (canvas) {
954 if (Page* page = canvas->document().page())
955 m_synthesizedErrorsToConsole = page->settings().webGLErrorsToConsoleEnabled();
956 }
957
958 // FIXME: With ANGLE as a backend this probably isn't needed any more. Unfortunately
959 // turning it off causes problems.
960 m_isGLES2Compliant = m_context->isGLES2Compliant();
961 if (m_isGLES2Compliant) {
962 m_isGLES2NPOTStrict = !m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_OES_texture_npot");
963 m_isDepthStencilSupported = m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_OES_packed_depth_stencil") || m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_ANGLE_depth_texture");
964 } else {
965#if USE(ANGLE)
966 m_isGLES2NPOTStrict = true;
967#else
968 m_isGLES2NPOTStrict = !m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_ARB_texture_non_power_of_two");
969#endif
970 m_isDepthStencilSupported = m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_EXT_packed_depth_stencil") || m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_ANGLE_depth_texture");
971 }
972 m_isRobustnessEXTSupported = m_context->getExtensions().isEnabled("GL_EXT_robustness");
973}
974
975void WebGLRenderingContextBase::addCompressedTextureFormat(GCGLenum format)
976{
977 if (!m_compressedTextureFormats.contains(format))
978 m_compressedTextureFormats.append(format);
979}
980
981void WebGLRenderingContextBase::resetUnpackParameters()
982{
983 if (m_unpackAlignment != 1)
984 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ALIGNMENT, 1);
985}
986
987void WebGLRenderingContextBase::restoreUnpackParameters()
988{
989 if (m_unpackAlignment != 1)
990 m_context->pixelStorei(GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ALIGNMENT, m_unpackAlignment);
991}
992
993void WebGLRenderingContextBase::addActivityStateChangeObserverIfNecessary()
994{
995 // We are only interested in visibility changes for contexts
996 // that are using the high-performance GPU.
997 if (!isHighPerformanceContext(m_context))
998 return;
999
1000 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
1001 if (!canvas)
1002 return;
1003
1004 auto* page = canvas->document().page();
1005 if (!page)
1006 return;
1007
1008 page->addActivityStateChangeObserver(*this);
1009
1010 // We won't get a state change right away, so
1011 // make sure the context knows if it visible or not.
1012 if (m_context)
1013 m_context->setContextVisibility(page->isVisible());
1014}
1015
1016void WebGLRenderingContextBase::removeActivityStateChangeObserver()
1017{
1018 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
1019 if (canvas) {
1020 if (auto* page = canvas->document().page())
1021 page->removeActivityStateChangeObserver(*this);
1022 }
1023}
1024
1025WebGLRenderingContextBase::~WebGLRenderingContextBase()
1026{
1027 // Remove all references to WebGLObjects so if they are the last reference
1028 // they will be freed before the last context is removed from the context group.
1029 m_boundArrayBuffer = nullptr;
1030 m_defaultVertexArrayObject = nullptr;
1031 m_boundVertexArrayObject = nullptr;
1032#if !USE(ANGLE)
1033 m_vertexAttrib0Buffer = nullptr;
1034#endif
1035 m_currentProgram = nullptr;
1036 m_framebufferBinding = nullptr;
1037 m_renderbufferBinding = nullptr;
1038
1039 for (auto& textureUnit : m_textureUnits) {
1040 textureUnit.texture2DBinding = nullptr;
1041 textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding = nullptr;
1042 }
1043
1044 m_blackTexture2D = nullptr;
1045 m_blackTextureCubeMap = nullptr;
1046
1047 if (!m_isPendingPolicyResolution) {
1048 detachAndRemoveAllObjects();
1049 loseExtensions(LostContextMode::RealLostContext);
1050 destroyGraphicsContextGL();
1051 m_contextGroup->removeContext(*this);
1052 }
1053
1054 {
1055 Locker locker { WebGLProgram::instancesLock() };
1056 for (auto& entry : WebGLProgram::instances()) {
1057 if (entry.value == this) {
1058 // Don't remove any WebGLProgram from the instances list, as they may still exist.
1059 // Only remove the association with a WebGL context.
1060 entry.value = nullptr;
1061 }
1062 }
1063 }
1064}
1065
1066void WebGLRenderingContextBase::destroyGraphicsContextGL()
1067{
1068 if (m_isPendingPolicyResolution)
1069 return;
1070
1071 removeActivityStateChangeObserver();
1072
1073 if (m_context) {
1074 m_context->removeClient(*this);
1075 m_context = nullptr;
1076 }
1077}
1078
1079void WebGLRenderingContextBase::markContextChanged()
1080{
1081 if (m_framebufferBinding)
1082 return;
1083
1084 m_context->markContextChanged();
1085
1086 m_layerCleared = false;
1087 m_compositingResultsNeedUpdating = true;
1088
1089 if (auto* canvas = htmlCanvas()) {
1090 RenderBox* renderBox = canvas->renderBox();
1091 if (isAccelerated() && renderBox && renderBox->hasAcceleratedCompositing()) {
1092 m_markedCanvasDirty = true;
1093 canvas->clearCopiedImage();
1094 renderBox->contentChanged(CanvasPixelsChanged);
1095 return;
1096 }
1097 }
1098
1099 if (!m_markedCanvasDirty) {
1100 m_markedCanvasDirty = true;
1101 canvasBase().didDraw(FloatRect(FloatPoint(0, 0), clampedCanvasSize()));
1102 }
1103}
1104
1105void WebGLRenderingContextBase::markContextChangedAndNotifyCanvasObserver()
1106{
1107 // If we're not touching the default framebuffer, nothing visible has changed.
1108 if (m_framebufferBinding)
1109 return;
1110
1111 markContextChanged();
1112 if (!isAccelerated())
1113 return;
1114
1115 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
1116 if (!canvas)
1117 return;
1118
1119 canvas->notifyObserversCanvasChanged(FloatRect(FloatPoint(0, 0), clampedCanvasSize()));
1120}
1121
1122bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::clearIfComposited(WebGLRenderingContextBase::ClearCaller caller, GCGLbitfield mask)
1123{
1124 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1125 return false;
1126
1127 if (!m_context->layerComposited() || m_layerCleared || m_preventBufferClearForInspector)
1128 return false;
1129
1130 GCGLbitfield buffersNeedingClearing = m_context->getBuffersToAutoClear();
1131
1132 if (!buffersNeedingClearing || (mask && m_framebufferBinding) || (m_rasterizerDiscardEnabled && caller == ClearCallerDrawOrClear))
1133 return false;
1134
1135 // Use the underlying GraphicsContext3D's attributes to take into
1136 // account (for example) packed depth/stencil buffers.
1137 auto contextAttributes = m_context->contextAttributes();
1138
1139 // Determine if it's possible to combine the clear the user asked for and this clear.
1140 bool combinedClear = mask && !m_scissorEnabled;
1141
1142 m_context->disable(GraphicsContextGL::SCISSOR_TEST);
1143 if (combinedClear && (mask & GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_BUFFER_BIT)) {
1144 m_context->clearColor(m_colorMask[0] ? m_clearColor[0] : 0,
1145 m_colorMask[1] ? m_clearColor[1] : 0,
1146 m_colorMask[2] ? m_clearColor[2] : 0,
1147 m_colorMask[3] ? m_clearColor[3] : 0);
1148 } else
1149 m_context->clearColor(0, 0, 0, 0);
1150 m_context->colorMask(true, true, true, true);
1151 GCGLbitfield clearMask = GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_BUFFER_BIT;
1152 if (contextAttributes.depth) {
1153 if (!combinedClear || !m_depthMask || !(mask & GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT))
1154 m_context->clearDepth(1.0f);
1155 clearMask |= GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT;
1156 m_context->depthMask(true);
1157 }
1158 if (contextAttributes.stencil) {
1159 if (combinedClear && (mask & GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT))
1160 m_context->clearStencil(m_clearStencil & m_stencilMask);
1161 else
1162 m_context->clearStencil(0);
1163 clearMask |= GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT;
1164 m_context->stencilMaskSeparate(GraphicsContextGL::FRONT, 0xFFFFFFFF);
1165 }
1166
1167 GCGLenum bindingPoint = isWebGL2() ? GraphicsContextGL::DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER : GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER;
1168 if (m_framebufferBinding)
1169 m_context->bindFramebuffer(bindingPoint, 0);
1170 {
1171 ScopedDisableRasterizerDiscard disable(this, m_rasterizerDiscardEnabled);
1172 // If the WebGL 2.0 clearBuffer APIs already have been used to
1173 // selectively clear some of the buffers, don't destroy those
1174 // results.
1175 m_context->clear(clearMask & buffersNeedingClearing);
1176 }
1177 m_context->setBuffersToAutoClear(0);
1178
1179 restoreStateAfterClear();
1180 if (m_framebufferBinding)
1181 m_context->bindFramebuffer(bindingPoint, objectOrZero(m_framebufferBinding.get()));
1182 m_layerCleared = true;
1183
1184 return combinedClear;
1185}
1186
1187void WebGLRenderingContextBase::restoreStateAfterClear()
1188{
1189 // Restore the state that the context set.
1190 if (m_scissorEnabled)
1191 m_context->enable(GraphicsContextGL::SCISSOR_TEST);
1192 m_context->clearColor(m_clearColor[0], m_clearColor[1],
1193 m_clearColor[2], m_clearColor[3]);
1194 m_context->colorMask(m_colorMask[0], m_colorMask[1],
1195 m_colorMask[2], m_colorMask[3]);
1196 m_context->clearDepth(m_clearDepth);
1197 m_context->clearStencil(m_clearStencil);
1198 m_context->stencilMaskSeparate(GraphicsContextGL::FRONT, m_stencilMask);
1199 m_context->depthMask(m_depthMask);
1200}
1201
1202
1203void WebGLRenderingContextBase::prepareForDisplayWithPaint()
1204{
1205 m_isDisplayingWithPaint = true;
1206}
1207
1208void WebGLRenderingContextBase::paintRenderingResultsToCanvas()
1209{
1210 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1211 return;
1212
1213 if (m_isDisplayingWithPaint) {
1214 bool canvasContainsDisplayBuffer = !m_markedCanvasDirty;
1215 prepareForDisplay();
1216 m_isDisplayingWithPaint = false;
1217 if (!canvasContainsDisplayBuffer) {
1218 auto& base = canvasBase();
1219 base.clearCopiedImage();
1220 m_markedCanvasDirty = false;
1221 // FIXME: Remote ImageBuffers do not flush the buffers that are drawn to a buffer.
1222 // Avoid leaking the WebGL content in the cases where a WebGL canvas element is drawn to a Context2D
1223 // canvas element repeatedly.
1224 base.buffer()->flushDrawingContext();
1225 m_context->paintCompositedResultsToCanvas(*base.buffer());
1226 }
1227 return;
1228 }
1229
1230 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
1231
1232 if (!m_markedCanvasDirty && !m_layerCleared)
1233 return;
1234
1235 auto& base = canvasBase();
1236 base.clearCopiedImage();
1237
1238 m_markedCanvasDirty = false;
1239 // FIXME: Remote ImageBuffers do not flush the buffers that are drawn to a buffer.
1240 // Avoid leaking the WebGL content in the cases where a WebGL canvas element is drawn to a Context2D
1241 // canvas element repeatedly.
1242 base.buffer()->flushDrawingContext();
1243 m_context->paintRenderingResultsToCanvas(*base.buffer());
1244}
1245
1246std::optional<PixelBuffer> WebGLRenderingContextBase::paintRenderingResultsToPixelBuffer()
1247{
1248 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1249 return std::nullopt;
1250 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
1251 return m_context->paintRenderingResultsToPixelBuffer();
1252}
1253
1254WebGLTexture::TextureExtensionFlag WebGLRenderingContextBase::textureExtensionFlags() const
1255{
1256 return static_cast<WebGLTexture::TextureExtensionFlag>((m_oesTextureFloatLinear ? WebGLTexture::TextureExtensionFloatLinearEnabled : 0) | (m_oesTextureHalfFloatLinear ? WebGLTexture::TextureExtensionHalfFloatLinearEnabled : 0));
1257}
1258
1259void WebGLRenderingContextBase::reshape(int width, int height)
1260{
1261 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1262 return;
1263
1264 // This is an approximation because at WebGLRenderingContext level we don't
1265 // know if the underlying FBO uses textures or renderbuffers.
1266 GCGLint maxSize = std::min(m_maxTextureSize, m_maxRenderbufferSize);
1267 GCGLint maxWidth = std::min(maxSize, m_maxViewportDims[0]);
1268 GCGLint maxHeight = std::min(maxSize, m_maxViewportDims[1]);
1269 width = clamp(width, 1, maxWidth);
1270 height = clamp(height, 1, maxHeight);
1271
1272 if (m_needsUpdate) {
1273 notifyCanvasContentChanged();
1274 m_needsUpdate = false;
1275 }
1276
1277 // We don't have to mark the canvas as dirty, since the newly created image buffer will also start off
1278 // clear (and this matches what reshape will do).
1279 m_context->reshape(width, height);
1280
1281 auto& textureUnit = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit];
1282 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D, objectOrZero(textureUnit.texture2DBinding.get()));
1283#if !USE(ANGLE)
1284 if (textureUnit.texture2DBinding && textureUnit.texture2DBinding->needToUseBlackTexture(textureExtensionFlags()))
1285 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(m_activeTextureUnit);
1286#endif
1287 m_context->bindRenderbuffer(GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER, objectOrZero(m_renderbufferBinding.get()));
1288 if (m_framebufferBinding)
1289 m_context->bindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, objectOrZero(m_framebufferBinding.get()));
1290}
1291
1292int WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawingBufferWidth() const
1293{
1294 if (isContextLost())
1295 return 0;
1296
1297 if (m_isPendingPolicyResolution && !m_hasRequestedPolicyResolution)
1298 return 0;
1299
1300 return m_context->getInternalFramebufferSize().width();
1301}
1302
1303int WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawingBufferHeight() const
1304{
1305 if (isContextLost())
1306 return 0;
1307
1308 if (m_isPendingPolicyResolution && !m_hasRequestedPolicyResolution)
1309 return 0;
1310
1311 return m_context->getInternalFramebufferSize().height();
1312}
1313
1314unsigned WebGLRenderingContextBase::sizeInBytes(GCGLenum type)
1315{
1316 switch (type) {
1317 case GraphicsContextGL::BYTE:
1318 return sizeof(GCGLbyte);
1319 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
1320 return sizeof(GCGLubyte);
1321 case GraphicsContextGL::SHORT:
1322 return sizeof(GCGLshort);
1323 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
1324 return sizeof(GCGLushort);
1325 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
1326 return sizeof(GCGLint);
1327 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
1328 return sizeof(GCGLuint);
1329 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
1330 return sizeof(GCGLfloat);
1331 case GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT:
1332 return 2;
1333 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
1334 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
1335 return 4;
1336 }
1337 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1338 return 0;
1339}
1340
1341void WebGLRenderingContextBase::activeTexture(GCGLenum texture)
1342{
1343 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1344 return;
1345 if (texture - GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE0 >= m_textureUnits.size()) {
1346 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "activeTexture", "texture unit out of range");
1347 return;
1348 }
1349 m_activeTextureUnit = texture - GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE0;
1350 m_context->activeTexture(texture);
1351}
1352
1353void WebGLRenderingContextBase::attachShader(WebGLProgram& program, WebGLShader& shader)
1354{
1355 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1356
1357 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("attachShader", &program) || !validateWebGLProgramOrShader("attachShader", &shader))
1358 return;
1359 if (!program.attachShader(locker, &shader)) {
1360 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "attachShader", "shader attachment already has shader");
1361 return;
1362 }
1363 m_context->attachShader(program.object(), shader.object());
1364 shader.onAttached();
1365}
1366
1367void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bindAttribLocation(WebGLProgram& program, GCGLuint index, const String& name)
1368{
1369 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("bindAttribLocation", &program))
1370 return;
1371 if (!validateLocationLength("bindAttribLocation", name))
1372 return;
1373 if (!validateString("bindAttribLocation", name))
1374 return;
1375 if (isPrefixReserved(name)) {
1376 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "bindAttribLocation", "reserved prefix");
1377 return;
1378 }
1379 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
1380 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bindAttribLocation", "index out of range");
1381 return;
1382 }
1383 m_context->bindAttribLocation(program.object(), index, name);
1384}
1385
1386bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateNullableWebGLObject(const char* functionName, WebGLObject* object)
1387{
1388 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1389 return false;
1390 if (!object) {
1391 // This differs in behavior to ValidateWebGLObject; null objects are allowed
1392 // in these entry points.
1393 return true;
1394 }
1395 return validateWebGLObject(functionName, object);
1396}
1397
1398bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateBufferTarget(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
1399{
1400 switch (target) {
1401 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
1402 case GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER:
1403 return true;
1404 default:
1405 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
1406 return false;
1407 }
1408}
1409
1410WebGLBuffer* WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateBufferDataTarget(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
1411{
1412 WebGLBuffer* buffer = nullptr;
1413 switch (target) {
1414 case GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER:
1415 buffer = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer();
1416 break;
1417 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER:
1418 buffer = m_boundArrayBuffer.get();
1419 break;
1420 default:
1421 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
1422 return nullptr;
1423 }
1424 if (!buffer) {
1425 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no buffer");
1426 return nullptr;
1427 }
1428 return buffer;
1429}
1430
1431bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateAndCacheBufferBinding(const AbstractLocker& locker, const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
1432{
1433 if (!validateBufferTarget(functionName, target))
1434 return false;
1435
1436 if (buffer && buffer->getTarget() && buffer->getTarget() != target) {
1437 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "buffers can not be used with multiple targets");
1438 return false;
1439 }
1440
1441 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER)
1442 m_boundArrayBuffer = buffer;
1443 else {
1444 ASSERT(target == GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER);
1445 m_boundVertexArrayObject->setElementArrayBuffer(locker, buffer);
1446 }
1447
1448 if (buffer && !buffer->getTarget())
1449 buffer->setTarget(target);
1450 return true;
1451}
1452
1453void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bindBuffer(GCGLenum target, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
1454{
1455 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1456
1457 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("bindBuffer", buffer))
1458 return;
1459
1460 if (!validateAndCacheBufferBinding(locker, "bindBuffer", target, buffer))
1461 return;
1462
1463 m_context->bindBuffer(target, objectOrZero(buffer));
1464}
1465
1466void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bindFramebuffer(GCGLenum target, WebGLFramebuffer* buffer)
1467{
1468 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1469
1470 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("bindFramebuffer", buffer))
1471 return;
1472
1473 if (target != GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER) {
1474 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "bindFramebuffer", "invalid target");
1475 return;
1476 }
1477
1478 setFramebuffer(locker, target, buffer);
1479}
1480
1481void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bindRenderbuffer(GCGLenum target, WebGLRenderbuffer* renderBuffer)
1482{
1483 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1484
1485 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("bindRenderbuffer", renderBuffer))
1486 return;
1487 if (target != GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER) {
1488 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "bindRenderbuffer", "invalid target");
1489 return;
1490 }
1491 m_renderbufferBinding = renderBuffer;
1492 m_context->bindRenderbuffer(target, objectOrZero(renderBuffer));
1493 if (renderBuffer)
1494 renderBuffer->setHasEverBeenBound();
1495}
1496
1497void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bindTexture(GCGLenum target, WebGLTexture* texture)
1498{
1499 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
1500
1501 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("bindTexture", texture))
1502 return;
1503 if (texture && texture->getTarget() && texture->getTarget() != target) {
1504 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "bindTexture", "textures can not be used with multiple targets");
1505 return;
1506 }
1507 GCGLint maxLevel = 0;
1508 auto& textureUnit = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit];
1509 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D) {
1510 textureUnit.texture2DBinding = texture;
1511 maxLevel = m_maxTextureLevel;
1512#if !USE(ANGLE)
1513 if (texture && texture->needToUseBlackTexture(textureExtensionFlags()))
1514 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(m_activeTextureUnit);
1515 else
1516 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.remove(m_activeTextureUnit);
1517#endif
1518 } else if (target == GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP) {
1519 textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding = texture;
1520 maxLevel = m_maxCubeMapTextureLevel;
1521#if !USE(ANGLE)
1522 if (texture && texture->needToUseBlackTexture(textureExtensionFlags()))
1523 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(m_activeTextureUnit);
1524 else
1525 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.remove(m_activeTextureUnit);
1526#endif
1527 } else if (isWebGL2() && target == GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY) {
1528 textureUnit.texture2DArrayBinding = texture;
1529 // maxLevel is unused in the ANGLE backend.
1530 } else if (isWebGL2() && target == GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_3D) {
1531 textureUnit.texture3DBinding = texture;
1532 // maxLevel is unused in the ANGLE backend.
1533 } else {
1534 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "bindTexture", "invalid target");
1535 return;
1536 }
1537 m_context->bindTexture(target, objectOrZero(texture));
1538 if (texture)
1539 texture->setTarget(target, maxLevel);
1540
1541 // Note: previously we used to automatically set the TEXTURE_WRAP_R
1542 // repeat mode to CLAMP_TO_EDGE for cube map textures, because OpenGL
1543 // ES 2.0 doesn't expose this flag (a bug in the specification) and
1544 // otherwise the application has no control over the seams in this
1545 // dimension. However, it appears that supporting this properly on all
1546 // platforms is fairly involved (will require a HashMap from texture ID
1547 // in all ports), and we have not had any complaints, so the logic has
1548 // been removed.
1549}

1553 if (isContextLostOrPending())

1587
1588void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bufferData(GCGLenum target, long long size, GCGLenum usage)
1589{
1590 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1591 return;
1592 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> buffer = validateBufferDataParameters("bufferData", target, usage);
1593 if (!buffer)
1594 return;
1595 if (size < 0) {
1596 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bufferData", "size < 0");
1597 return;
1598 }
1599 if (!buffer->associateBufferData(static_cast<GCGLsizeiptr>(size))) {
1600 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bufferData", "invalid buffer");
1601 return;
1602 }
1603
1604 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
1605 m_context->bufferData(target, static_cast<GCGLsizeiptr>(size), usage);
1606 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()) {
1607 // The bufferData function failed. Tell the buffer it doesn't have the data it thinks it does.
1608 buffer->disassociateBufferData();
1609 }
1610}
1611
1612void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bufferData(GCGLenum target, std::optional<BufferDataSource>&& data, GCGLenum usage)
1613{
1614 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1615 return;
1616 if (!data) {
1617 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bufferData", "null data");
1618 return;
1619 }
1620 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> buffer = validateBufferDataParameters("bufferData", target, usage);
1621 if (!buffer)
1622 return;
1623
1624 WTF::visit([&](auto& data) {
1625 if (!buffer->associateBufferData(data.get())) {
1626 this->synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bufferData", "invalid buffer");
1627 return;
1628 }
1629
1630 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
1631 m_context->bufferData(target, GCGLSpan<const GCGLvoid>(data->data(), data->byteLength()), usage);
1632 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()) {
1633 // The bufferData function failed. Tell the buffer it doesn't have the data it thinks it does.
1634 buffer->disassociateBufferData();
1635 }
1636 }, data.value());
1637}
1638
1639void WebGLRenderingContextBase::bufferSubData(GCGLenum target, long long offset, BufferDataSource&& data)
1640{
1641 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1642 return;
1643 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> buffer = validateBufferDataParameters("bufferSubData", target, GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_DRAW);
1644 if (!buffer)
1645 return;
1646 if (offset < 0) {
1647 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bufferSubData", "offset < 0");
1648 return;
1649 }
1650
1651 WTF::visit([&](auto& data) {
1652 if (!buffer->associateBufferSubData(static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), data.get())) {
1653 this->synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "bufferSubData", "offset out of range");
1654 return;
1655 }
1656
1657 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
1658 m_context->bufferSubData(target, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), GCGLSpan<const GCGLvoid>(data->data(), data->byteLength()));
1659 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()) {
1660 // The bufferSubData function failed. Tell the buffer it doesn't have the data it thinks it does.
1661 buffer->disassociateBufferData();
1662 }
1663 }, data);
1664}
1665
1666GCGLenum WebGLRenderingContextBase::checkFramebufferStatus(GCGLenum target)
1667{
1668 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1669 return GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_UNSUPPORTED;
1670 if (!validateFramebufferTarget(target)) {
1671 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "checkFramebufferStatus", "invalid target");
1672 return 0;
1673 }
1674#if USE(ANGLE)
1675 return m_context->checkFramebufferStatus(target);
1676#else
1677 auto targetFramebuffer = getFramebufferBinding(target);
1678
1679 if (!targetFramebuffer || !targetFramebuffer->object())
1680 return GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE;
1681 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
1682 GCGLenum result = targetFramebuffer->checkStatus(&reason);
1683 if (result != GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER_COMPLETE) {
1684 String str = "WebGL: checkFramebufferStatus:" + String(reason);
1685 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Warning, str);
1686 return result;
1687 }
1688 result = m_context->checkFramebufferStatus(target);
1689 return result;
1690#endif
1691}
1692
1693void WebGLRenderingContextBase::clear(GCGLbitfield mask)
1694{
1695 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1696 return;
1697#if !USE(ANGLE)
1698 if (mask & ~(GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_BUFFER_BIT | GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_BUFFER_BIT | GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BUFFER_BIT)) {
1699 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "clear", "invalid mask");
1700 return;
1701 }
1702 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
1703 if (m_framebufferBinding && !m_framebufferBinding->onAccess(m_context.get(), &reason)) {
1704 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, "clear", reason);
1705 return;
1706 }
1707#endif
1708 if (!clearIfComposited(ClearCallerDrawOrClear, mask))
1709 m_context->clear(mask);
1710 markContextChangedAndNotifyCanvasObserver();
1711}
1712
1713void WebGLRenderingContextBase::clearColor(GCGLfloat r, GCGLfloat g, GCGLfloat b, GCGLfloat a)
1714{
1715 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1716 return;
1717 if (std::isnan(r))
1718 r = 0;
1719 if (std::isnan(g))
1720 g = 0;
1721 if (std::isnan(b))
1722 b = 0;
1723 if (std::isnan(a))
1724 a = 1;
1725 m_clearColor[0] = r;
1726 m_clearColor[1] = g;
1727 m_clearColor[2] = b;
1728 m_clearColor[3] = a;
1729 m_context->clearColor(r, g, b, a);
1730}

1758
1759void WebGLRenderingContextBase::compileShader(WebGLShader& shader)
1760{
1761 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("compileShader", &shader))
1762 return;
1763 m_context->compileShader(shader.object());
1764 GCGLint value = m_context->getShaderi(shader.object(), GraphicsContextGL::COMPILE_STATUS);
1765 shader.setValid(value);
1766
1767 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
1768
1769 if (canvas && m_synthesizedErrorsToConsole && !value) {
1770 Ref<Inspector::ScriptCallStack> stackTrace = Inspector::createScriptCallStack(JSExecState::currentState());
1771
1772 for (auto& error : getShaderInfoLog(shader).split('\n'))
1773 canvas->document().addConsoleMessage(makeUnique<Inspector::ConsoleMessage>(MessageSource::Rendering, MessageType::Log, MessageLevel::Error, "WebGL: " + error, stackTrace.copyRef()));
1774 }
1775}
1776
1777void WebGLRenderingContextBase::compressedTexImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLint border, ArrayBufferView& data)
1778{
1779 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1780 return;
1781#if USE(ANGLE)
1782 if (!validateTexture2DBinding("compressedTexImage2D", target))
1783 return;
1784 m_context->compressedTexImage2D(target, level, internalformat, width, height,
1785 border, data.byteLength(), makeGCGLSpan(data.baseAddress(), data.byteLength()));
1786#else
1787 if (!validateTexFuncLevel("compressedTexImage2D", target, level))
1788 return;
1789
1790 if (!validateCompressedTexFormat(internalformat)) {
1791 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "compressedTexImage2D", "invalid internalformat");
1792 return;
1793 }
1794 if (border) {
1795 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "compressedTexImage2D", "border not 0");
1796 return;
1797 }
1798 if (!validateCompressedTexDimensions("compressedTexImage2D", target, level, width, height, internalformat))
1799 return;
1800 if (!validateCompressedTexFuncData("compressedTexImage2D", width, height, internalformat, data))
1801 return;
1802
1803 auto tex = validateTexture2DBinding("compressedTexImage2D", target);
1804 if (!tex)
1805 return;
1806 if (!validateNPOTTextureLevel(width, height, level, "compressedTexImage2D"))
1807 return;
1808 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
1809 static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->compressedTexImage2D(target, level, internalformat, width, height,
1810 border, data.byteLength(), makeGCGLSpan(data.baseAddress(), data.byteLength()));
1811 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()) {
1812 // The compressedTexImage2D function failed. Tell the WebGLTexture it doesn't have the data for this level.
1813 tex->markInvalid(target, level);
1814 return;
1815 }
1816
1817 tex->setLevelInfo(target, level, internalformat, width, height, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE);
1818 tex->setCompressed();
1819#endif
1820}
1821
1822void WebGLRenderingContextBase::compressedTexSubImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format, ArrayBufferView& data)
1823{
1824 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1825 return;
1826#if USE(ANGLE)
1827 if (!validateTexture2DBinding("compressedTexSubImage2D", target))
1828 return;
1829 m_context->compressedTexSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, data.byteLength(), GCGLSpan<const GCGLvoid>(data.baseAddress(), data.byteLength()));
1830#else
1831 if (!validateTexFuncLevel("compressedTexSubImage2D", target, level))
1832 return;
1833 if (!validateCompressedTexFormat(format)) {
1834 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "compressedTexSubImage2D", "invalid format");
1835 return;
1836 }
1837 if (!validateCompressedTexFuncData("compressedTexSubImage2D", width, height, format, data))
1838 return;
1839
1840 auto tex = validateTexture2DBinding("compressedTexSubImage2D", target);
1841 if (!tex)
1842 return;
1843
1844 if (format != tex->getInternalFormat(target, level)) {
1845 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "compressedTexSubImage2D", "format does not match texture format");
1846 return;
1847 }
1848
1849 if (!validateCompressedTexSubDimensions("compressedTexSubImage2D", target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, tex.get()))
1850 return;
1851
1852 static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(graphicsContextGL())->compressedTexSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, data.byteLength(), makeGCGLSpan(data.baseAddress(), data.byteLength()));
1853 tex->setCompressed();
1854#endif
1855}
1856
1857bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateSettableTexInternalFormat(const char* functionName, GCGLenum internalFormat)
1858{
1859 if (isWebGL2())
1860 return true;
1861
1862 switch (internalFormat) {
1863 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT:
1864 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL:
1865 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT16:
1866 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT24:
1867 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT32F:
1868 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH24_STENCIL8:
1869 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH32F_STENCIL8:
1870 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_INDEX8:
1871 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "format can not be set, only rendered to");
1872 return false;
1873 default:
1874 return true;
1875 }
1876}
1877
1878void WebGLRenderingContextBase::copyTexSubImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLint x, GCGLint y, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height)
1879{
1880 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1881 return;
1882#if USE(ANGLE)
1883 if (!validateTexture2DBinding("copyTexSubImage2D", target))
1884 return;
1885 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
1886 m_context->copyTexSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, x, y, width, height);
1887#else
1888 if (!validateTexFuncLevel("copyTexSubImage2D", target, level))
1889 return;
1890 auto tex = validateTexture2DBinding("copyTexSubImage2D", target);
1891 if (!tex)
1892 return;
1893 if (!validateSize("copyTexSubImage2D", xoffset, yoffset) || !validateSize("copyTexSubImage2D", width, height))
1894 return;
1895 // Before checking if it is in the range, check if overflow happens first.
1896 if (xoffset + width < 0 || yoffset + height < 0) {
1897 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyTexSubImage2D", "bad dimensions");
1898 return;
1899 }
1900 if (xoffset + width > tex->getWidth(target, level) || yoffset + height > tex->getHeight(target, level)) {
1901 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyTexSubImage2D", "rectangle out of range");
1902 return;
1903 }
1904 GCGLenum internalFormat = tex->getInternalFormat(target, level);
1905 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat("copyTexSubImage2D", internalFormat))
1906 return;
1907 if (!isTexInternalFormatColorBufferCombinationValid(internalFormat, getBoundReadFramebufferColorFormat())) {
1908 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "copyTexSubImage2D", "framebuffer is incompatible format");
1909 return;
1910 }
1911 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
1912 if (m_framebufferBinding && !m_framebufferBinding->onAccess(graphicsContextGL(), &reason)) {
1913 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, "copyTexSubImage2D", reason);
1914 return;
1915 }
1916 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
1917
1918 GCGLint clippedX, clippedY;
1919 GCGLsizei clippedWidth, clippedHeight;
1920 if (clip2D(x, y, width, height, getBoundReadFramebufferWidth(), getBoundReadFramebufferHeight(), &clippedX, &clippedY, &clippedWidth, &clippedHeight)) {
1921 GCGLenum format;
1922 GCGLenum type;
1923 if (!GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::possibleFormatAndTypeForInternalFormat(tex->getInternalFormat(target, level), format, type)) {
1924 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "copyTexSubImage2D", "Texture has unknown internal format");
1925 return;
1926 }
1927 UniqueArray<unsigned char> zero;
1928 unsigned size = 0;
1929 if (width && height) {
1930 GCGLenum error = m_context->computeImageSizeInBytes(format, type, width, height, 1, getUnpackPixelStoreParams(TexImageDimension::Tex2D), &size, nullptr, nullptr);
1931 if (error != GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR) {
1932 synthesizeGLError(error, "copyTexSubImage2D", "bad dimensions");
1933 return;
1934 }
1935 zero = makeUniqueArray<unsigned char>(size);
1936 if (!zero) {
1937 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyTexSubImage2D", "out of memory");
1938 return;
1939 }
1940 memset(zero.get(), 0, size);
1941 }
1942 m_context->texSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(zero.get(), size));
1943 if (clippedWidth > 0 && clippedHeight > 0)
1944 m_context->copyTexSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset + clippedX - x, yoffset + clippedY - y, clippedX, clippedY, clippedWidth, clippedHeight);
1945 } else
1946 m_context->copyTexSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, x, y, width, height);
1947#endif
1948}
1949
1950RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> WebGLRenderingContextBase::createBuffer()
1951{
1952 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1953 return nullptr;
1954 auto buffer = WebGLBuffer::create(*this);
1955 addSharedObject(buffer.get());
1956 return buffer;
1957}
1958
1959RefPtr<WebGLFramebuffer> WebGLRenderingContextBase::createFramebuffer()
1960{
1961 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1962 return nullptr;
1963 auto buffer = WebGLFramebuffer::create(*this);
1964 addContextObject(buffer.get());
1965 return buffer;
1966}
1967
1968RefPtr<WebGLTexture> WebGLRenderingContextBase::createTexture()
1969{
1970 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1971 return nullptr;
1972 auto texture = WebGLTexture::create(*this);
1973 addSharedObject(texture.get());
1974 return texture;
1975}

1977RefPtr<WebGLProgram> WebGLRenderingContextBase::createProgram()
1978{
1979 if (isContextLostOrPending())
1980 return nullptr;
1981 auto program = WebGLProgram::create(*this);
1982 addSharedObject(program.get());
1983
1984 InspectorInstrumentation::didCreateWebGLProgram(*this, program.get());
1985
1986 return program;
1987}

1992 return nullptr;

1998RefPtr<WebGLShader> WebGLRenderingContextBase::createShader(GCGLenum type)
1999{
2000 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2001 return nullptr;
2002 if (type != GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_SHADER && type != GraphicsContextGL::FRAGMENT_SHADER) {
2003 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "createShader", "invalid shader type");
2004 return nullptr;
2005 }
2006

2008 addSharedObject(shader.get());

2010}

2016 m_context->cullFace(mode);
2017}
2018
2019bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteObject(const AbstractLocker& locker, WebGLObject* object)
2020{
2021 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !object)
2022 return false;
2023 if (!object->validate(contextGroup(), *this)) {
2024 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "delete", "object does not belong to this context");
2025 return false;
2026 }
2027 if (object->isDeleted())
2028 return false;
2029 if (object->object())
2030 // We need to pass in context here because we want
2031 // things in this context unbound.
2032 object->deleteObject(locker, graphicsContextGL());
2033 return true;
2034}
2035
2036#define REMOVE_BUFFER_FROM_BINDING(binding) \
2037 if (binding == buffer) \
2038 binding = nullptr;
2039
2040void WebGLRenderingContextBase::uncacheDeletedBuffer(const AbstractLocker& locker, WebGLBuffer* buffer)
2041{
2042 REMOVE_BUFFER_FROM_BINDING(m_boundArrayBuffer);
2043
2044 m_boundVertexArrayObject->unbindBuffer(locker, *buffer);
2045}
2046
2047void WebGLRenderingContextBase::setBoundVertexArrayObject(const AbstractLocker&, WebGLVertexArrayObjectBase* arrayObject)
2048{
2049 m_boundVertexArrayObject = arrayObject ? arrayObject : m_defaultVertexArrayObject;
2050}
2051
2052#undef REMOVE_BUFFER_FROM_BINDING
2053
2054void WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteBuffer(WebGLBuffer* buffer)
2055{
2056 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2057
2058 if (!deleteObject(locker, buffer))
2059 return;
2060
2061 uncacheDeletedBuffer(locker, buffer);
2062}
2063
2064void WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteFramebuffer(WebGLFramebuffer* framebuffer)
2065{
2066 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2067
2068#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
2069 if (framebuffer && framebuffer->isOpaque()) {
2070 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "deleteFramebuffer", "An opaque framebuffer's attachments cannot be inspected or changed");
2071 return;
2072 }
2073#endif
2074
2075 if (!deleteObject(locker, framebuffer))
2076 return;
2077
2078 if (framebuffer == m_framebufferBinding) {
2079 m_framebufferBinding = nullptr;
2080 m_context->bindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, 0);
2081 }
2082}
2083
2084void WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteProgram(WebGLProgram* program)
2085{
2086 if (program)
2087 InspectorInstrumentation::willDestroyWebGLProgram(*program);
2088
2089 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2090
2091 deleteObject(locker, program);
2092 // We don't reset m_currentProgram to 0 here because the deletion of the
2093 // current program is delayed.
2094}
2095
2096void WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteRenderbuffer(WebGLRenderbuffer* renderbuffer)
2097{
2098 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2099
2100 if (!deleteObject(locker, renderbuffer))
2101 return;
2102 if (renderbuffer == m_renderbufferBinding)
2103 m_renderbufferBinding = nullptr;
2104 if (m_framebufferBinding)
2105 m_framebufferBinding->removeAttachmentFromBoundFramebuffer(locker, GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, renderbuffer);
2106 auto readFramebufferBinding = getFramebufferBinding(GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER);
2107 if (readFramebufferBinding)
2108 readFramebufferBinding->removeAttachmentFromBoundFramebuffer(locker, GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER, renderbuffer);
2109}
2110
2111void WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteShader(WebGLShader* shader)
2112{
2113 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2114 deleteObject(locker, shader);
2115}
2116
2117void WebGLRenderingContextBase::deleteTexture(WebGLTexture* texture)
2118{
2119 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
2120
2121 if (!deleteObject(locker, texture))
2122 return;
2123
2124 unsigned current = 0;
2125 for (auto& textureUnit : m_textureUnits) {
2126 if (texture == textureUnit.texture2DBinding) {
2127 textureUnit.texture2DBinding = nullptr;
2128#if !USE(ANGLE)
2129 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.remove(current);
2130#endif
2131 }
2132 if (texture == textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding) {
2133 textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding = nullptr;
2134#if !USE(ANGLE)
2135 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.remove(current);
2136#endif
2137 }
2138 if (isWebGL2()) {
2139 if (texture == textureUnit.texture3DBinding)
2140 textureUnit.texture3DBinding = nullptr;
2141 if (texture == textureUnit.texture2DArrayBinding)
2142 textureUnit.texture2DArrayBinding = nullptr;
2143 }
2144 ++current;
2145 }
2146 if (m_framebufferBinding)
2147 m_framebufferBinding->removeAttachmentFromBoundFramebuffer(locker, GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, texture);
2148 auto readFramebufferBinding = getFramebufferBinding(GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER);
2149 if (readFramebufferBinding)
2150 readFramebufferBinding->removeAttachmentFromBoundFramebuffer(locker, GraphicsContextGL::READ_FRAMEBUFFER, texture);
2151}

2179void WebGLRenderingContextBase::detachShader(WebGLProgram& program, WebGLShader& shader)
2180{

2182
2183 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("detachShader", &program) || !validateWebGLProgramOrShader("detachShader", &shader))
2184 return;

2186 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "detachShader", "shader not attached");
2187 return;

2189 m_context->detachShader(program.object(), shader.object());
2190 shader.onDetached(locker, graphicsContextGL());
2191}
