2238
2239bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateElementArraySize(GCGLsizei count, GCGLenum type, GCGLintptr offset)
2240{
2241 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> elementArrayBuffer = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer();
2242
2243 if (!elementArrayBuffer)
2244 return false;
2245
2246 if (offset < 0)
2247 return false;
2248
2249 if (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT) {
2250 // For an unsigned int array, offset must be divisible by 4 for alignment reasons.
2251 if (offset % 4)
2252 return false;
2253
2254 // Make uoffset an element offset.
2255 offset /= 4;
2256
2257 GCGLsizeiptr n = elementArrayBuffer->byteLength() / 4;
2258 if (offset > n || count > n - offset)
2259 return false;
2260 } else if (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT) {
2261 // For an unsigned short array, offset must be divisible by 2 for alignment reasons.
2262 if (offset % 2)
2263 return false;
2264
2265 // Make uoffset an element offset.
2266 offset /= 2;
2267
2268 GCGLsizeiptr n = elementArrayBuffer->byteLength() / 2;
2269 if (offset > n || count > n - offset)
2270 return false;
2271 } else if (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE) {
2272 GCGLsizeiptr n = elementArrayBuffer->byteLength();
2273 if (offset > n || count > n - offset)
2274 return false;
2275 }
2276 return true;
2277}
2278
2279bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateIndexArrayPrecise(GCGLsizei count, GCGLenum type, GCGLintptr offset, unsigned& numElementsRequired)
2280{
2281 ASSERT(count >= 0 && offset >= 0);
2282 unsigned maxIndex = 0;
2283
2284 RefPtr<WebGLBuffer> elementArrayBuffer = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer();
2285
2286 if (!elementArrayBuffer)
2287 return false;
2288
2289 if (!count) {
2290 numElementsRequired = 0;
2291 return true;
2292 }
2293
2294 auto buffer = elementArrayBuffer->elementArrayBuffer();
2295 if (!buffer)
2296 return false;
2297
2298 switch (type) {
2299 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
2300 maxIndex = getMaxIndex<GCGLuint>(buffer, offset, count);
2301 break;
2302 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
2303 maxIndex = getMaxIndex<GCGLushort>(buffer, offset, count);
2304 break;
2305 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
2306 maxIndex = getMaxIndex<GCGLubyte>(buffer, offset, count);
2307 break;
2308 }
2309
2310 // Then set the maxiumum index in the index array and make sure it is valid.
2311 auto checkedNumElementsRequired = checkedAddAndMultiply<unsigned>(maxIndex, 1, 1);
2312 if (!checkedNumElementsRequired)
2313 return false;
2314 numElementsRequired = checkedNumElementsRequired.value();
2315 return true;
2316}
2317
2318bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateVertexAttributes(unsigned elementCount, unsigned primitiveCount)
2319{
2320#if USE(ANGLE)
2321 UNUSED_PARAM(elementCount);
2322 UNUSED_PARAM(primitiveCount);
2323#else
2324 if (!m_currentProgram)
2325 return false;
2326
2327 // Look in each enabled vertex attrib and check if they've been bound to a buffer.
2328 for (unsigned i = 0; i < m_maxVertexAttribs; ++i) {
2329 if (!m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(i).validateBinding())
2330 return false;
2331 }
2332
2333 if (!elementCount)
2334 return true;
2335
2336 // Look in each consumed vertex attrib (by the current program).
2337 bool sawNonInstancedAttrib = false;
2338 bool sawEnabledAttrib = false;
2339 int numActiveAttribLocations = m_currentProgram->numActiveAttribLocations();
2340 for (int i = 0; i < numActiveAttribLocations; ++i) {
2341 int loc = m_currentProgram->getActiveAttribLocation(i);
2342 if (loc >= 0 && loc < static_cast<int>(m_maxVertexAttribs)) {
2343 const WebGLVertexArrayObjectBase::VertexAttribState& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(loc);
2344 if (state.enabled) {
2345 sawEnabledAttrib = true;
2346 // Avoid off-by-one errors in numElements computation.
2347 // For the last element, we will only touch the data for the
2348 // element and nothing beyond it.
2349 int bytesRemaining = static_cast<int>(state.bufferBinding->byteLength() - state.offset);
2350 if (bytesRemaining <= 0)
2351 return false;
2352 unsigned numElements = 0;
2353 ASSERT(state.stride > 0);
2354 if (bytesRemaining >= state.bytesPerElement)
2355 numElements = 1 + (bytesRemaining - state.bytesPerElement) / state.stride;
2356 unsigned instancesRequired = 0;
2357 if (state.divisor) {
2358 instancesRequired = ceil(static_cast<float>(primitiveCount) / state.divisor);
2359 if (instancesRequired > numElements)
2360 return false;
2361 } else {
2362 sawNonInstancedAttrib = true;
2363 if (elementCount > numElements)
2364 return false;
2365 }
2366 }
2367 }
2368 }
2369
2370 if (!sawNonInstancedAttrib && sawEnabledAttrib)
2371 return false;
2372
2373 bool usingSimulatedArrayBuffer = m_currentProgram->isUsingVertexAttrib0();
2374
2375 // Guard against access into non-existent buffers.
2376 if (elementCount && !sawEnabledAttrib && !usingSimulatedArrayBuffer)
2377 return false;
2378
2379 if (elementCount && sawEnabledAttrib) {
2380 if (!m_boundArrayBuffer && !m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer()) {
2381 if (usingSimulatedArrayBuffer) {
2382 auto& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(0);
2383 if (state.enabled && state.isBound()) {
2384 if (state.bufferBinding->getTarget() == GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER || state.bufferBinding->getTarget() == GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER)
2385 return !!state.bufferBinding->byteLength();
2386 }
2387 }
2388 return false;
2389 }
2390 }
2391#endif
2392
2393 return true;
2394}
2395
2396bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateWebGLObject(const char* functionName, WebGLObject* object)
2397{
2398 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2399 return false;
2400 if (!object) {
2401 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "object is null");
2402 return false;
2403 }
2404 if (object->isDeleted()) {
2405 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "attempt to use a deleted object");
2406 return false;
2407 }
2408 if (!object->validate(contextGroup(), *this)) {
2409 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "object does not belong to this context");
2410 return false;
2411 }
2412 return true;
2413}
2414
2415bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateWebGLProgramOrShader(const char* functionName, WebGLObject* object)
2416{
2417 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2418 return false;
2419 if (!object) {
2420 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "program or shader is null");
2421 return false;
2422 }
2423 // OpenGL ES 3.0.5 p. 45:
2424 // "Commands that accept shader or program object names will generate the
2425 // error INVALID_VALUE if the provided name is not the name of either a shader
2426 // or program object and INVALID_OPERATION if the provided name identifies an
2427 // object that is not the expected type."
2428 //
2429 // Programs and shaders also have slightly different lifetime rules than other
2430 // objects in the API; they continue to be usable after being marked for
2431 // deletion.
2432 if (!object->object()) {
2433 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "attempt to use a deleted program or shader");
2434 return false;
2435 }
2436 if (!object->validate(contextGroup(), *this)) {
2437 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "object does not belong to this context");
2438 return false;
2439 }
2440 return true;
2441}
2442
2443#if !USE(ANGLE)
2444bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateDrawArrays(const char* functionName, GCGLenum mode, GCGLint first, GCGLsizei count, GCGLsizei primitiveCount)
2445{
2446 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateDrawMode(functionName, mode))
2447 return false;
2448
2449 if (!validateStencilSettings(functionName))
2450 return false;
2451
2452 if (first < 0 || count < 0) {
2453 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "first or count < 0");
2454 return false;
2455 }
2456
2457 if (!count) {
2458 markContextChanged();
2459 return false;
2460 }
2461
2462 if (primitiveCount < 0) {
2463 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "primcount < 0");
2464 return false;
2465 }
2466
2467 // Ensure we have a valid rendering state.
2468 Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow> checkedSum = Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow>(first) + Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow>(count);
2469 Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow> checkedPrimitiveCount(primitiveCount);
2470 if (checkedSum.hasOverflowed() || checkedPrimitiveCount.hasOverflowed() || !validateVertexAttributes(checkedSum, checkedPrimitiveCount)) {
2471 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "attempt to access out of bounds arrays");
2472 return false;
2473 }
2474#if !USE(ANGLE)
2475 if (!validateSimulatedVertexAttrib0(checkedSum.value() - 1)) {
2476 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "attempt to access outside the bounds of the simulated vertexAttrib0 array");
2477 return false;
2478 }
2479#endif
2480
2481 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
2482 if (m_framebufferBinding && !m_framebufferBinding->onAccess(graphicsContextGL(), &reason)) {
2483 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, functionName, reason);
2484 return false;
2485 }
2486
2487 return true;
2488}
2489
2490bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateDrawElements(const char* functionName, GCGLenum mode, GCGLsizei count, GCGLenum type, long long offset, unsigned& numElements, GCGLsizei primitiveCount)
2491{
2492 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateDrawMode(functionName, mode))
2493 return false;
2494
2495 if (!validateStencilSettings(functionName))
2496 return false;
2497
2498 switch (type) {
2499 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
2500 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
2501 break;
2502 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
2503 if (m_oesElementIndexUint || isWebGL2())
2504 break;
2505 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid type");
2506 return false;
2507 default:
2508 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid type");
2509 return false;
2510 }
2511
2512 if (count < 0 || offset < 0) {
2513 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "count or offset < 0");
2514 return false;
2515 }
2516
2517 if (!count) {
2518 markContextChanged();
2519 return false;
2520 }
2521
2522 if (primitiveCount < 0) {
2523 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "primcount < 0");
2524 return false;
2525 }
2526
2527 if (!m_boundVertexArrayObject->getElementArrayBuffer()) {
2528 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER bound");
2529 return false;
2530 }
2531
2532 // Ensure we have a valid rendering state.
2533 if (!validateElementArraySize(count, type, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset))) {
2534 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "request out of bounds for current ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER");
2535 return false;
2536 }
2537 if (!count)
2538 return false;
2539
2540 Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow> checkedCount(count);
2541 Checked<GCGLint, RecordOverflow> checkedPrimitiveCount(primitiveCount);
2542 if (checkedCount.hasOverflowed() || checkedPrimitiveCount.hasOverflowed()) {
2543 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "attempt to access out of bounds arrays");
2544 return false;
2545 }
2546
2547 if (!validateIndexArrayConservative(type, numElements) || !validateVertexAttributes(numElements, checkedPrimitiveCount)) {
2548 if (!validateIndexArrayPrecise(checkedCount, type, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), numElements) || !validateVertexAttributes(numElements, checkedPrimitiveCount)) {
2549 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "attempt to access out of bounds arrays");
2550 return false;
2551 }
2552 }
2553
2554#if !USE(ANGLE)
2555 if (!validateSimulatedVertexAttrib0(numElements)) {
2556 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "attempt to access outside the bounds of the simulated vertexAttrib0 array");
2557 return false;
2558 }
2559#endif
2560
2561 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
2562 if (m_framebufferBinding && !m_framebufferBinding->onAccess(graphicsContextGL(), &reason)) {
2563 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, functionName, reason);
2564 return false;
2565 }
2566
2567 return true;
2568}
2569#endif
2570
2571void WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawArrays(GCGLenum mode, GCGLint first, GCGLsizei count)
2572{
2573#if USE(ANGLE)
2574 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2575 return;
2576#else
2577 if (!validateDrawArrays("drawArrays", mode, first, count, 0))
2578 return;
2579#endif
2580
2581 if (m_currentProgram && InspectorInstrumentation::isWebGLProgramDisabled(*this, *m_currentProgram))
2582 return;
2583
2584 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerDrawOrClear);
2585
2586#if !USE(ANGLE)
2587 bool vertexAttrib0Simulated = false;
2588 if (!isGLES2Compliant()) {
2589 auto simulateVertexAttrib0Status = simulateVertexAttrib0(first + count - 1);
2590 if (!simulateVertexAttrib0Status) {
2591 // We were unable to simulate the attribute buffer.
2592 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawArrays", "unable to simulate vertexAttrib0 array");
2593 return;
2594 }
2595 vertexAttrib0Simulated = simulateVertexAttrib0Status.value();
2596 }
2597 bool usesFallbackTexture = false;
2598 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
2599 usesFallbackTexture = checkTextureCompleteness("drawArrays", true);
2600#endif
2601
2602 {
2603 InspectorScopedShaderProgramHighlight scopedHighlight(*this, m_currentProgram.get());
2604
2605 m_context->drawArrays(mode, first, count);
2606 }
2607
2608#if !USE(ANGLE)
2609 if (!isGLES2Compliant() && vertexAttrib0Simulated)
2610 restoreStatesAfterVertexAttrib0Simulation();
2611 if (usesFallbackTexture)
2612 checkTextureCompleteness("drawArrays", false);
2613#endif
2614 markContextChangedAndNotifyCanvasObserver();
2615}
2616
2617#if USE(OPENGL) && ENABLE(WEBGL2)
2618static GCGLuint getRestartIndex(GCGLenum type)
2619{
2620 switch (type) {
2621 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
2622 return std::numeric_limits<GCGLubyte>::max();
2623 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
2624 return std::numeric_limits<GCGLushort>::max();
2625 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
2626 return std::numeric_limits<GCGLuint>::max();
2627 }
2628
2629 return 0;
2630}
2631#endif
2632
2633void WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawElements(GCGLenum mode, GCGLsizei count, GCGLenum type, long long offset)
2634{
2635#if USE(ANGLE)
2636 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2637 return;
2638#else
2639 unsigned numElements = 0;
2640 if (!validateDrawElements("drawElements", mode, count, type, offset, numElements, 0))
2641 return;
2642#endif
2643
2644 if (m_currentProgram && InspectorInstrumentation::isWebGLProgramDisabled(*this, *m_currentProgram))
2645 return;
2646
2647 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerDrawOrClear);
2648
2649#if !USE(ANGLE)
2650 bool vertexAttrib0Simulated = false;
2651 if (!isGLES2Compliant()) {
2652 if (!numElements)
2653 validateIndexArrayPrecise(count, type, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), numElements);
2654 auto simulateVertexAttrib0Status = simulateVertexAttrib0(numElements);
2655 if (!simulateVertexAttrib0Status) {
2656 // We were unable to simulate the attribute buffer.
2657 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawElements", "unable to simulate vertexAttrib0 array");
2658 return;
2659 }
2660 vertexAttrib0Simulated = simulateVertexAttrib0Status.value();
2661 }
2662 bool usesFallbackTexture = false;
2663 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
2664 usesFallbackTexture = checkTextureCompleteness("drawElements", true);
2665#endif
2666
2667#if USE(OPENGL) && ENABLE(WEBGL2)
2668 if (isWebGL2())
2669 m_context->primitiveRestartIndex(getRestartIndex(type));
2670#endif
2671
2672 {
2673 InspectorScopedShaderProgramHighlight scopedHighlight(*this, m_currentProgram.get());
2674
2675 m_context->drawElements(mode, count, type, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset));
2676 }
2677
2678#if !USE(ANGLE)
2679 if (!isGLES2Compliant() && vertexAttrib0Simulated)
2680 restoreStatesAfterVertexAttrib0Simulation();
2681 if (usesFallbackTexture)
2682 checkTextureCompleteness("drawElements", false);
2683#endif
2684 markContextChangedAndNotifyCanvasObserver();
2685}
2686
2687void WebGLRenderingContextBase::enable(GCGLenum cap)
2688{
2689 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateCapability("enable", cap))
2690 return;
2691 if (cap == GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_TEST) {
2692 m_stencilEnabled = true;
2693 applyStencilTest();
2694 return;
2695 }
2696 if (cap == GraphicsContextGL::SCISSOR_TEST)
2697 m_scissorEnabled = true;
2698 if (cap == GraphicsContextGL::RASTERIZER_DISCARD)
2699 m_rasterizerDiscardEnabled = true;
2700 m_context->enable(cap);
2701}
2702
2703void WebGLRenderingContextBase::enableVertexAttribArray(GCGLuint index)
2704{
2705 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2706 return;
2707 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
2708 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "enableVertexAttribArray", "index out of range");
2709 return;
2710 }
2711
2712 WebGLVertexArrayObjectBase::VertexAttribState& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(index);
2713 state.enabled = true;
2714
2715 m_context->enableVertexAttribArray(index);
2716}

2719{
2720 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2721 return;
2722 m_context->finish();
2723}

2726{
2727 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2728 return;
2729 m_context->flush();
2730}
2731
2732void WebGLRenderingContextBase::framebufferRenderbuffer(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum attachment, GCGLenum renderbuffertarget, WebGLRenderbuffer* buffer)
2733{
2734 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateFramebufferFuncParameters("framebufferRenderbuffer", target, attachment))
2735 return;
2736 if (renderbuffertarget != GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER) {
2737 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "framebufferRenderbuffer", "invalid target");
2738 return;
2739 }
2740 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("framebufferRenderbuffer", buffer))
2741 return;
2742 if (buffer && !buffer->hasEverBeenBound()) {
2743 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferRenderbuffer", "buffer has never been bound");
2744 return;
2745 }
2746
2747 // Don't allow the default framebuffer to be mutated; all current
2748 // implementations use an FBO internally in place of the default
2749 // FBO.
2750 WebGLFramebuffer* framebufferBinding = getFramebufferBinding(target);
2751 if (!framebufferBinding || !framebufferBinding->object()) {
2752 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferRenderbuffer", "no framebuffer bound");
2753 return;
2754 }
2755
2756#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
2757 if (framebufferBinding->isOpaque()) {
2758 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferRenderbuffer", "An opaque framebuffer's attachments cannot be inspected or changed");
2759 return;
2760 }
2761#endif
2762
2763 framebufferBinding->setAttachmentForBoundFramebuffer(target, attachment, buffer);
2764 applyStencilTest();
2765}
2766
2767void WebGLRenderingContextBase::framebufferTexture2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum attachment, GCGLenum textarget, WebGLTexture* texture, GCGLint level)
2768{
2769 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateFramebufferFuncParameters("framebufferTexture2D", target, attachment))
2770 return;
2771 if (level && isWebGL1() && !m_oesFBORenderMipmap) {
2772 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "framebufferTexture2D", "level not 0 and OES_fbo_render_mipmap not enabled");
2773 return;
2774 }
2775 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("framebufferTexture2D", texture))
2776 return;
2777
2778 // Don't allow the default framebuffer to be mutated; all current
2779 // implementations use an FBO internally in place of the default
2780 // FBO.
2781 WebGLFramebuffer* framebufferBinding = getFramebufferBinding(target);
2782 if (!framebufferBinding || !framebufferBinding->object()) {
2783 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferTexture2D", "no framebuffer bound");
2784 return;
2785 }
2786#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
2787 if (framebufferBinding->isOpaque()) {
2788 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "framebufferTexture2D", "An opaque framebuffer's attachments cannot be inspected or changed");
2789 return;
2790 }
2791#endif
2792
2793 framebufferBinding->setAttachmentForBoundFramebuffer(target, attachment, textarget, texture, level, 0);
2794 applyStencilTest();
2795}
2796
2797void WebGLRenderingContextBase::frontFace(GCGLenum mode)
2798{
2799 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2800 return;
2801 m_context->frontFace(mode);
2802}
2803
2804void WebGLRenderingContextBase::generateMipmap(GCGLenum target)
2805{
2806 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2807 return;
2808#if USE(ANGLE)
2809 if (!validateTextureBinding("generateMipmap", target))
2810 return;
2811 m_context->generateMipmap(target);
2812#else
2813 auto tex = validateTextureBinding("generateMipmap", target);
2814 if (!tex)
2815 return;
2816 if (!tex->canGenerateMipmaps()) {
2817 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "generateMipmap", "level 0 not power of 2 or not all the same size");
2818 return;
2819 }
2820 // FIXME: https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=123916. Compressed textures should be allowed in WebGL 2:
2821 if (tex->isCompressed()) {
2822 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "generateMipmap", "trying to generate mipmaps from compressed texture");
2823 return;
2824 }
2825 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat("generateMipmap", tex->getInternalFormat(target, 0)))
2826 return;
2827
2828 // generateMipmap won't work properly if minFilter is not NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR
2829 // on Mac. Remove the hack once this driver bug is fixed.
2830#if OS(DARWIN)
2831 bool needToResetMinFilter = false;
2832 if (tex->getMinFilter() != GraphicsContextGL::NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR) {
2833 m_context->texParameteri(target, GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, GraphicsContextGL::NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR);
2834 needToResetMinFilter = true;
2835 }
2836#endif
2837 m_context->generateMipmap(target);
2838#if OS(DARWIN)
2839 if (needToResetMinFilter)
2840 m_context->texParameteri(target, GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, tex->getMinFilter());
2841#endif
2842 tex->generateMipmapLevelInfo();
2843#endif
2844}
2845
2846RefPtr<WebGLActiveInfo> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getActiveAttrib(WebGLProgram& program, GCGLuint index)
2847{
2848 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getActiveAttrib", &program))
2849 return nullptr;
2850 GraphicsContextGL::ActiveInfo info;
2851 if (!m_context->getActiveAttrib(program.object(), index, info))
2852 return nullptr;
2853
2854 LOG(WebGL, "Returning active attribute %d: %s", index, info.name.utf8().data());
2855
2856 return WebGLActiveInfo::create(info.name, info.type, info.size);
2857}
2858
2859RefPtr<WebGLActiveInfo> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getActiveUniform(WebGLProgram& program, GCGLuint index)
2860{
2861 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getActiveUniform", &program))
2862 return nullptr;
2863 GraphicsContextGL::ActiveInfo info;
2864 if (!m_context->getActiveUniform(program.object(), index, info))
2865 return nullptr;
2866 // FIXME: Do we still need this for the ANGLE backend?
2867 if (!isGLES2Compliant())
2868 if (info.size > 1 && !info.name.endsWith("[0]"))
2869 info.name.append("[0]");
2870
2871 LOG(WebGL, "Returning active uniform %d: %s", index, info.name.utf8().data());
2872
2873 return WebGLActiveInfo::create(info.name, info.type, info.size);
2874}
2875
2876std::optional<Vector<RefPtr<WebGLShader>>> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getAttachedShaders(WebGLProgram& program)
2877{
2878 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getAttachedShaders", &program))
2879 return std::nullopt;
2880
2881 const GCGLenum shaderTypes[] = {
2882 GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_SHADER,
2883 GraphicsContextGL::FRAGMENT_SHADER
2884 };
2885 Vector<RefPtr<WebGLShader>> shaderObjects;
2886 for (auto shaderType : shaderTypes) {
2887 RefPtr<WebGLShader> shader = program.getAttachedShader(shaderType);
2888 if (shader)
2889 shaderObjects.append(shader);
2890 }
2891 return shaderObjects;
2892}
2893
2894GCGLint WebGLRenderingContextBase::getAttribLocation(WebGLProgram& program, const String& name)
2895{
2896 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getAttribLocation", &program))
2897 return -1;
2898 if (!validateLocationLength("getAttribLocation", name))
2899 return -1;
2900 if (!validateString("getAttribLocation", name))
2901 return -1;
2902 if (isPrefixReserved(name))
2903 return -1;
2904 if (!program.getLinkStatus()) {
2905 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getAttribLocation", "program not linked");
2906 return -1;
2907 }
2908 return m_context->getAttribLocation(program.object(), name);
2909}
2910
2911WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getBufferParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname)
2912{
2913 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2914 return nullptr;
2915
2916 bool valid = false;
2917 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER || target == GraphicsContextGL::ELEMENT_ARRAY_BUFFER)
2918 valid = true;
2919#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
2920 if (isWebGL2()) {
2921 switch (target) {
2922 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_READ_BUFFER:
2923 case GraphicsContextGL::COPY_WRITE_BUFFER:
2924 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_PACK_BUFFER:
2925 case GraphicsContextGL::PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER:
2926 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER:
2927 case GraphicsContextGL::UNIFORM_BUFFER:
2928 valid = true;
2929 }
2930 }
2931#endif
2932 if (!valid) {
2933 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getBufferParameter", "invalid target");
2934 return nullptr;
2935 }
2936
2937 if (pname != GraphicsContextGL::BUFFER_SIZE && pname != GraphicsContextGL::BUFFER_USAGE) {
2938 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getBufferParameter", "invalid parameter name");
2939 return nullptr;
2940 }
2941
2942 GCGLint value = m_context->getBufferParameteri(target, pname);
2943 if (pname == GraphicsContextGL::BUFFER_SIZE)
2944 return value;
2945 return static_cast<unsigned>(value);
2946}
2947
2948std::optional<WebGLContextAttributes> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getContextAttributes()
2949{
2950 if (isContextLostOrPending())
2951 return std::nullopt;
2952
2953 // Also, we need to enforce requested values of "false" for depth
2954 // and stencil, regardless of the properties of the underlying
2955 // GraphicsContextGLOpenGL.
2956
2957 auto attributes = m_context->contextAttributes();
2958 if (!m_attributes.depth)
2959 attributes.depth = false;
2960 if (!m_attributes.stencil)
2961 attributes.stencil = false;
2962#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
2963 attributes.xrCompatible = m_isXRCompatible;
2964#endif
2965 return attributes;
2966}
2967
2968GCGLenum WebGLRenderingContextBase::getError()
2969{
2970 if (!m_context || m_isPendingPolicyResolution)
2971 return GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR;
2972 return m_context->getError();
2973}

2975WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getParameter(GCGLenum pname)

2990 return getIntParameter(pname);
2991 case GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:

2999 case GraphicsContextGL::BLEND_DST_RGB:
3000 return getUnsignedIntParameter(pname);

3050 FALLTHROUGH;

3053 if (!value) {

3055 // INVALID_OPERATION has been generated.

3119 return "WebGL GLSL ES 1.0 (1.0)"_str;
3120 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BACK_FAIL:

3124 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_BACK_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL:

3136 return 0;

3140 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_FAIL:
3141 return getUnsignedIntParameter(pname);

3143 return getUnsignedIntParameter(pname);
3144 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_PASS_DEPTH_FAIL:

3158 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_BINDING_2D:
3159 return m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture2DBinding;

3161 return m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].textureCubeMapBinding;

3172 case GraphicsContextGL::VERSION:
3173 return "WebGL 1.0"_str;
3174 case GraphicsContextGL::VIEWPORT:
3175 return getWebGLIntArrayParameter(pname);

3177 if (m_oesStandardDerivatives)
3178 return getUnsignedIntParameter(ExtensionsGL::FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES);
3179 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name, OES_standard_derivatives not enabled");

3186#endif

3188 }

3190 return nullptr;
3191 case WebGLDebugRendererInfo::UNMASKED_VENDOR_WEBGL:
3192 if (m_webglDebugRendererInfo) {
3193#if !PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
3194 if (!scriptExecutionContext()->settingsValues().maskWebGLStringsEnabled)
3195 return m_context->getString(GraphicsContextGL::VENDOR);
3196#endif

3199 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name, WEBGL_debug_renderer_info not enabled");
3200 return nullptr;
3201 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ARRAY_BINDING_OES: // OES_vertex_array_object
3202 if (m_oesVertexArrayObject) {
3203 if (m_boundVertexArrayObject->isDefaultObject())
3204 return nullptr;
3205 return makeRefPtr(static_cast<WebGLVertexArrayObjectOES&>(*m_boundVertexArrayObject));
3206 }
3207 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name, OES_vertex_array_object not enabled");
3208 return nullptr;
3209 case ExtensionsGL::MAX_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT: // EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic
3210 if (m_extTextureFilterAnisotropic)
3211 return getUnsignedIntParameter(ExtensionsGL::MAX_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT);
3212 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name, EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic not enabled");
3213 return nullptr;
3214 case ExtensionsGL::MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS_EXT: // EXT_draw_buffers BEGIN
3215 if (m_webglDrawBuffers || isWebGL2())
3216 return getMaxColorAttachments();
3217 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name, WEBGL_draw_buffers not enabled");
3218 return nullptr;
3219 case ExtensionsGL::MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS_EXT:
3220 if (m_webglDrawBuffers || isWebGL2())
3221 return getMaxDrawBuffers();
3222 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name, WEBGL_draw_buffers not enabled");
3223 return nullptr;
3224 default:
3225 if ((m_webglDrawBuffers || isWebGL2())
3226 && pname >= ExtensionsGL::DRAW_BUFFER0_EXT
3227 && pname < static_cast<GCGLenum>(ExtensionsGL::DRAW_BUFFER0_EXT + getMaxDrawBuffers())) {
3228 GCGLint value = GraphicsContextGL::NONE;
3229 if (m_framebufferBinding)
3230 value = m_framebufferBinding->getDrawBuffer(pname);
3231 else // emulated backbuffer
3232 value = m_backDrawBuffer;
3233 return value;
3234 }
3235 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3236 return nullptr;
3237 }
3238}
3239
3240WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getProgramParameter(WebGLProgram& program, GCGLenum pname)
3241{
3242 // COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR should always return true if the context is lost, so applications
3243 // don't get stuck in an infinite polling loop.
3244 if (isContextLostOrPending()) {
3245 if (pname == ExtensionsGL::COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR)
3246 return true;
3247 return nullptr;
3248 }
3249 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getProgramParameter", &program))
3250 return nullptr;
3251
3252 switch (pname) {
3253 case GraphicsContextGL::DELETE_STATUS:
3254 return program.isDeleted();
3255 case GraphicsContextGL::VALIDATE_STATUS:
3256 return static_cast<bool>(m_context->getProgrami(program.object(), pname));
3257 case GraphicsContextGL::LINK_STATUS:
3258 return program.getLinkStatus();
3259 case GraphicsContextGL::ATTACHED_SHADERS:
3260 return m_context->getProgrami(program.object(), pname);
3261 case GraphicsContextGL::ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTES:
3262 case GraphicsContextGL::ACTIVE_UNIFORMS:
3263#if USE(ANGLE)
3264 return m_context->getProgrami(program.object(), pname);
3265#else
3266 {
3267 GCGLint value = 0;
3268 static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->getNonBuiltInActiveSymbolCount(program.object(), pname, &value);
3269 return value;
3270 }
3271#endif // USE(ANGLE)
3272 case ExtensionsGL::COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR:
3273 if (m_khrParallelShaderCompile)
3274 return static_cast<bool>(m_context->getProgrami(program.object(), pname));
3275 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getProgramParameter", "KHR_parallel_shader_compile not enabled");
3276 return nullptr;
3277 default:
3278#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
3279 if (isWebGL2()) {
3280 switch (pname) {
3281 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_MODE:
3282 case GraphicsContextGL::TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYINGS:
3283 case GraphicsContextGL::ACTIVE_UNIFORM_BLOCKS:
3284 return m_context->getProgrami(program.object(), pname);
3285 default:
3286 break;
3287 }
3288 }
3289#endif // ENABLE(WEBGL2)
3290 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getProgramParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3291 return nullptr;
3292 }
3293}
3294
3295String WebGLRenderingContextBase::getProgramInfoLog(WebGLProgram& program)
3296{
3297 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getProgramInfoLog", &program))
3298 return String();
3299 return ensureNotNull(m_context->getProgramInfoLog(program.object()));
3300}
3301
3302WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getRenderbufferParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname)
3303{
3304 if (isContextLostOrPending())
3305 return nullptr;
3306 if (target != GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER) {
3307 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getRenderbufferParameter", "invalid target");
3308 return nullptr;
3309 }
3310 if (!m_renderbufferBinding || !m_renderbufferBinding->object()) {
3311 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getRenderbufferParameter", "no renderbuffer bound");
3312 return nullptr;
3313 }
3314
3315 if (m_renderbufferBinding->getInternalFormat() == GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL
3316 && !m_renderbufferBinding->isValid()) {
3317 ASSERT(!isDepthStencilSupported());
3318 int value = 0;
3319 switch (pname) {
3320 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_WIDTH:
3321 value = m_renderbufferBinding->getWidth();
3322 break;
3323 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_HEIGHT:
3324 value = m_renderbufferBinding->getHeight();
3325 break;
3326 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_RED_SIZE:
3327 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_GREEN_SIZE:
3328 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_BLUE_SIZE:
3329 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_ALPHA_SIZE:
3330 value = 0;
3331 break;
3332 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_DEPTH_SIZE:
3333 value = 24;
3334 break;
3335 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_STENCIL_SIZE:
3336 value = 8;
3337 break;
3338 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_INTERNAL_FORMAT:
3339 return m_renderbufferBinding->getInternalFormat();
3340 default:
3341 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getRenderbufferParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3342 return nullptr;
3343 }
3344 return value;
3345 }
3346
3347 switch (pname) {
3348 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_SAMPLES:
3349 if (!isWebGL2()) {
3350 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getRenderbufferParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3351 return nullptr;
3352 }
3353 FALLTHROUGH;
3354 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_WIDTH:
3355 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_HEIGHT:
3356 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_RED_SIZE:
3357 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_GREEN_SIZE:
3358 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_BLUE_SIZE:
3359 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_ALPHA_SIZE:
3360 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_DEPTH_SIZE:
3361 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_STENCIL_SIZE:
3362 return m_context->getRenderbufferParameteri(target, pname);
3363 case GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER_INTERNAL_FORMAT:
3364 return m_renderbufferBinding->getInternalFormat();
3365 default:
3366 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getRenderbufferParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3367 return nullptr;
3368 }
3369}
3370
3371WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getShaderParameter(WebGLShader& shader, GCGLenum pname)
3372{
3373 // COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR should always return true if the context is lost, so applications
3374 // don't get stuck in an infinite polling loop.
3375 if (isContextLostOrPending()) {
3376 if (pname == ExtensionsGL::COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR)
3377 return true;
3378 return nullptr;
3379 }
3380 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getShaderParameter", &shader))
3381 return nullptr;
3382
3383 switch (pname) {
3384 case GraphicsContextGL::DELETE_STATUS:
3385 return shader.isDeleted();
3386 case GraphicsContextGL::COMPILE_STATUS:
3387 return static_cast<bool>(m_context->getShaderi(shader.object(), pname));
3388 case GraphicsContextGL::SHADER_TYPE:
3389 return static_cast<unsigned>(m_context->getShaderi(shader.object(), pname));
3390 case ExtensionsGL::COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR:
3391 if (m_khrParallelShaderCompile)
3392 return static_cast<bool>(m_context->getShaderi(shader.object(), pname));
3393 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getShaderParameter", "KHR_parallel_shader_compile not enabled");
3394 return nullptr;
3395 default:
3396 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getShaderParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3397 return nullptr;
3398 }
3399}

3402{
3403 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getShaderInfoLog", &shader))
3404 return String();
3405 return ensureNotNull(m_context->getShaderInfoLog(shader.object()));
3406}
3407
3408RefPtr<WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getShaderPrecisionFormat(GCGLenum shaderType, GCGLenum precisionType)
3409{
3410 if (isContextLostOrPending())
3411 return nullptr;
3412 switch (shaderType) {
3413 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_SHADER:
3414 case GraphicsContextGL::FRAGMENT_SHADER:
3415 break;
3416 default:
3417 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getShaderPrecisionFormat", "invalid shader type");
3418 return nullptr;
3419 }
3420 switch (precisionType) {
3421 case GraphicsContextGL::LOW_FLOAT:
3422 case GraphicsContextGL::MEDIUM_FLOAT:
3423 case GraphicsContextGL::HIGH_FLOAT:
3424 case GraphicsContextGL::LOW_INT:
3425 case GraphicsContextGL::MEDIUM_INT:
3426 case GraphicsContextGL::HIGH_INT:
3427 break;
3428 default:
3429 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getShaderPrecisionFormat", "invalid precision type");
3430 return nullptr;
3431 }
3432
3433 GCGLint range[2] { };
3434 GCGLint precision = 0;
3435 m_context->getShaderPrecisionFormat(shaderType, precisionType, range, &precision);
3436 return WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat::create(range[0], range[1], precision);
3437}

3442 return String();
3443 return ensureNotNull(shader.getSource());
3444}

3446WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getTexParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname)
3447{
3448 if (isContextLostOrPending())
3449 return nullptr;
3450 auto tex = validateTextureBinding("getTexParameter", target);
3451 if (!tex)
3452 return nullptr;
3453 switch (pname) {
3454 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
3455 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
3456 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
3457 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
3458 return static_cast<unsigned>(m_context->getTexParameteri(target, pname));
3459 case ExtensionsGL::TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT: // EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic
3460 if (m_extTextureFilterAnisotropic)
3461 return m_context->getTexParameterf(target, pname);
3462 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getTexParameter", "invalid parameter name, EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic not enabled");
3463 return nullptr;
3464 default:
3465 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getTexParameter", "invalid parameter name");
3466 return nullptr;
3467 }
3468}
3469
3470WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getUniform(WebGLProgram& program, const WebGLUniformLocation& uniformLocation)
3471{
3472 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getUniform", &program))
3473 return nullptr;
3474 if (uniformLocation.program() != &program) {
3475 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getUniform", "no uniformlocation or not valid for this program");
3476 return nullptr;
3477 }
3478 GCGLint location = uniformLocation.location();
3479
3480 GCGLenum baseType;
3481 unsigned length;
3482 switch (uniformLocation.type()) {
3483 case GraphicsContextGL::BOOL:
3484 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::BOOL;
3485 length = 1;
3486 break;
3487 case GraphicsContextGL::BOOL_VEC2:
3488 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::BOOL;
3489 length = 2;
3490 break;
3491 case GraphicsContextGL::BOOL_VEC3:
3492 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::BOOL;
3493 length = 3;
3494 break;
3495 case GraphicsContextGL::BOOL_VEC4:
3496 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::BOOL;
3497 length = 4;
3498 break;
3499 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
3500 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
3501 length = 1;
3502 break;
3503 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_VEC2:
3504 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
3505 length = 2;
3506 break;
3507 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_VEC3:
3508 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
3509 length = 3;
3510 break;
3511 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_VEC4:
3512 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
3513 length = 4;
3514 break;
3515 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
3516 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3517 length = 1;
3518 break;
3519 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_VEC2:
3520 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3521 length = 2;
3522 break;
3523 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_VEC3:
3524 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3525 length = 3;
3526 break;
3527 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_VEC4:
3528 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3529 length = 4;
3530 break;
3531 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT2:
3532 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3533 length = 4;
3534 break;
3535 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT3:
3536 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3537 length = 9;
3538 break;
3539 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT4:
3540 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3541 length = 16;
3542 break;
3543 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_2D:
3544 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_CUBE:
3545 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
3546 length = 1;
3547 break;
3548 default:
3549 if (!isWebGL2()) {
3550 // Can't handle this type.
3551 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getUniform", "unhandled type");
3552 return nullptr;
3553 }
3554 switch (uniformLocation.type()) {
3555 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
3556 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT;
3557 length = 1;
3558 break;
3559 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_VEC2:
3560 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT;
3561 length = 2;
3562 break;
3563 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_VEC3:
3564 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT;
3565 length = 3;
3566 break;
3567 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_VEC4:
3568 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT;
3569 length = 4;
3570 break;
3571 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT2x3:
3572 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3573 length = 6;
3574 break;
3575 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT2x4:
3576 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3577 length = 8;
3578 break;
3579 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT3x2:
3580 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3581 length = 6;
3582 break;
3583 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT3x4:
3584 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3585 length = 12;
3586 break;
3587 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT4x2:
3588 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3589 length = 8;
3590 break;
3591 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_MAT4x3:
3592 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
3593 length = 12;
3594 break;
3595 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_3D:
3596 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
3597 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_2D_SHADOW:
3598 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_CUBE_SHADOW:
3599 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY_SHADOW:
3600 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_SAMPLER_2D:
3601 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_SAMPLER_CUBE:
3602 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_SAMPLER_3D:
3603 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
3604 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D:
3605 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_CUBE:
3606 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_3D:
3607 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
3608 baseType = GraphicsContextGL::INT;
3609 length = 1;
3610 break;
3611 default:
3612 // Can't handle this type.
3613 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getUniform", "unhandled type");
3614 return nullptr;
3615 }
3616 }
3617 switch (baseType) {
3618 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT: {
3619 GCGLfloat value[16] = {0};
3620#if !USE(ANGLE)
3621 if (m_isRobustnessEXTSupported)
3622 m_context->getExtensions().getnUniformfvEXT(program.object(), location, 16 * sizeof(GCGLfloat), value);
3623 else
3624#endif
3625 m_context->getUniformfv(program.object(), location, makeGCGLSpan(value, length));
3626 if (length == 1)
3627 return value[0];
3628 return Float32Array::tryCreate(value, length);
3629 }
3630 case GraphicsContextGL::INT: {
3631 GCGLint value[4] = {0};
3632#if !USE(ANGLE)
3633 if (m_isRobustnessEXTSupported)
3634 m_context->getExtensions().getnUniformivEXT(program.object(), location, 4 * sizeof(GCGLint), value);
3635 else
3636#endif
3637 m_context->getUniformiv(program.object(), location, makeGCGLSpan(value, length));
3638 if (length == 1)
3639 return value[0];
3640 return Int32Array::tryCreate(value, length);
3641 }
3642 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT: {
3643 GCGLuint value[4] = {0};
3644 m_context->getUniformuiv(program.object(), location, makeGCGLSpan(value, length));
3645 if (length == 1)
3646 return value[0];
3647 return Uint32Array::tryCreate(value, length);
3648 }
3649 case GraphicsContextGL::BOOL: {
3650 GCGLint value[4] = {0};
3651#if !USE(ANGLE)
3652 if (m_isRobustnessEXTSupported)
3653 m_context->getExtensions().getnUniformivEXT(program.object(), location, 4 * sizeof(GCGLint), value);
3654 else
3655#endif
3656 m_context->getUniformiv(program.object(), location, makeGCGLSpan(value, length));
3657 if (length > 1) {
3658 Vector<bool> vector(length);
3659 for (unsigned j = 0; j < length; j++)
3660 vector[j] = value[j];
3661 return vector;
3662 }
3663 return static_cast<bool>(value[0]);
3664 }
3665 default:
3666 notImplemented();
3667 }
3668
3669 // If we get here, something went wrong in our unfortunately complex logic above
3670 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getUniform", "unknown error");
3671 return nullptr;
3672}
3673
3674RefPtr<WebGLUniformLocation> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getUniformLocation(WebGLProgram& program, const String& name)
3675{
3676 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("getUniformLocation", &program))
3677 return nullptr;
3678 if (!validateLocationLength("getUniformLocation", name))
3679 return nullptr;
3680 if (!validateString("getUniformLocation", name))
3681 return nullptr;
3682 if (isPrefixReserved(name))
3683 return nullptr;
3684 if (!program.getLinkStatus()) {
3685 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "getUniformLocation", "program not linked");
3686 return nullptr;
3687 }
3688 GCGLint uniformLocation = m_context->getUniformLocation(program.object(), name);
3689 if (uniformLocation == -1)
3690 return nullptr;
3691
3692 GCGLint activeUniforms = 0;
3693#if USE(ANGLE)
3694 activeUniforms = m_context->getProgrami(program.object(), GraphicsContextGL::ACTIVE_UNIFORMS);
3695#else
3696 static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->getNonBuiltInActiveSymbolCount(program.object(), GraphicsContextGL::ACTIVE_UNIFORMS, &activeUniforms);
3697#endif
3698 for (GCGLint i = 0; i < activeUniforms; i++) {
3699 GraphicsContextGL::ActiveInfo info;
3700 if (!m_context->getActiveUniform(program.object(), i, info))
3701 return nullptr;
3702 // Strip "[0]" from the name if it's an array.
3703 if (info.name.endsWith("[0]"))
3704 info.name = info.name.left(info.name.length() - 3);
3705 // If it's an array, we need to iterate through each element, appending "[index]" to the name.
3706 for (GCGLint index = 0; index < info.size; ++index) {
3707 auto uniformName = makeString(info.name, '[', index, ']');
3708
3709 if (name == uniformName || name == info.name)
3710 return WebGLUniformLocation::create(&program, uniformLocation, info.type);
3711 }
3712 }
3713 return nullptr;
3714}
3715
3716WebGLAny WebGLRenderingContextBase::getVertexAttrib(GCGLuint index, GCGLenum pname)
3717{
3718 if (isContextLostOrPending())
3719 return nullptr;
3720
3721 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
3722 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "getVertexAttrib", "index out of range");
3723 return nullptr;
3724 }
3725
3726 const WebGLVertexArrayObjectBase::VertexAttribState& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(index);
3727
3728 if ((isWebGL2() || m_angleInstancedArrays) && pname == GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR_ANGLE)
3729 return state.divisor;
3730
3731 if (isWebGL2() && pname == GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_INTEGER)
3732 return state.isInteger;
3733
3734 switch (pname) {
3735 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
3736#if !USE(ANGLE)
3737 if ((!isGLES2Compliant() && !index && m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(0).bufferBinding == m_vertexAttrib0Buffer)
3738 || !state.bufferBinding
3739 || !state.bufferBinding->object())
3740 return nullptr;
3741#endif
3742 return state.bufferBinding;
3743 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_ENABLED:
3744 return state.enabled;
3745 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_NORMALIZED:
3746 return state.normalized;
3747 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_SIZE:
3748 return state.size;
3749 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_STRIDE:
3750 return state.originalStride;
3751 case GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_TYPE:
3752 return state.type;
3753 case GraphicsContextGL::CURRENT_VERTEX_ATTRIB: {
3754 switch (m_vertexAttribValue[index].type) {
3755 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
3756 return Float32Array::tryCreate(m_vertexAttribValue[index].fValue, 4);
3757 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
3758 return Int32Array::tryCreate(m_vertexAttribValue[index].iValue, 4);
3759 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
3760 return Uint32Array::tryCreate(m_vertexAttribValue[index].uiValue, 4);
3761 default:
3762 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3763 break;
3764 }
3765 return nullptr;
3766 }
3767 default:
3768 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "getVertexAttrib", "invalid parameter name");
3769 return nullptr;
3770 }
3771}
3772
3773long long WebGLRenderingContextBase::getVertexAttribOffset(GCGLuint index, GCGLenum pname)
3774{
3775 if (isContextLostOrPending())
3776 return 0;
3777 return m_context->getVertexAttribOffset(index, pname);
3778}
3779
3780bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::extensionIsEnabled(const String& name)
3781{
3782#define CHECK_EXTENSION(variable, nameLiteral) \
3783 if (equalIgnoringASCIICase(name, nameLiteral)) \
3784 return variable != nullptr;
3785
3786 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extFragDepth, "EXT_frag_depth");
3787 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extBlendMinMax, "EXT_blend_minmax");
3788 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extsRGB, "EXT_sRGB");
3789 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extTextureCompressionRGTC, "EXT_texture_compression_rgtc");
3790 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extTextureFilterAnisotropic, "EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic");
3791 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extTextureFilterAnisotropic, "WEBKIT_EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic");
3792 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extShaderTextureLOD, "EXT_shader_texture_lod");
3793 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_khrParallelShaderCompile, "KHR_parallel_shader_compile");
3794 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureFloat, "OES_texture_float");
3795 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureFloatLinear, "OES_texture_float_linear");
3796 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureHalfFloat, "OES_texture_half_float");
3797 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureHalfFloatLinear, "OES_texture_half_float_linear");
3798 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesStandardDerivatives, "OES_standard_derivatives");
3799 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesVertexArrayObject, "OES_vertex_array_object");
3800 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesElementIndexUint, "OES_element_index_uint");
3801 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_oesFBORenderMipmap, "OES_fbo_render_mipmap");
3802 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglLoseContext, "WEBGL_lose_context");
3803 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglDebugRendererInfo, "WEBGL_debug_renderer_info");
3804 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglDebugShaders, "WEBGL_debug_shaders");
3805 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureASTC, "WEBGL_compressed_texture_astc");
3806 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureATC, "WEBKIT_WEBGL_compressed_texture_atc");
3807 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureETC, "WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc");
3808 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureETC1, "WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc1");
3809 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTexturePVRTC, "WEBKIT_WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc");
3810 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureS3TC, "WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc");
3811 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureS3TCsRGB, "WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc_srgb");
3812 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglDepthTexture, "WEBGL_depth_texture");
3813 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglDrawBuffers, "WEBGL_draw_buffers");
3814 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_angleInstancedArrays, "ANGLE_instanced_arrays");
3815 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extColorBufferHalfFloat, "EXT_color_buffer_half_float");
3816 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extFloatBlend, "EXT_float_blend");
3817 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglColorBufferFloat, "WEBGL_color_buffer_float");
3818 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_extColorBufferFloat, "EXT_color_buffer_float");
3819 CHECK_EXTENSION(m_webglMultiDraw, "WEBGL_multi_draw");
3820 return false;
3821}
3822
3823void WebGLRenderingContextBase::enablePreserveDrawingBuffer()
3824{
3825 ASSERT(!m_attributes.preserveDrawingBuffer);
3826 m_attributes.preserveDrawingBuffer = true;
3827 // Must send this notification down to the GraphicsContextGL as well.
3828 m_context->enablePreserveDrawingBuffer();
3829}
3830
3831void WebGLRenderingContextBase::hint(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum mode)
3832{
3833 if (isContextLostOrPending())
3834 return;
3835 bool isValid = false;
3836 switch (target) {
3837 case GraphicsContextGL::GENERATE_MIPMAP_HINT:
3838 isValid = true;
3839 break;
3840 case ExtensionsGL::FRAGMENT_SHADER_DERIVATIVE_HINT_OES: // OES_standard_derivatives, or core in WebGL 2.0
3841 if (m_oesStandardDerivatives || isWebGL2())
3842 isValid = true;
3843 break;
3844 }
3845 if (!isValid) {
3846 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "hint", "invalid target");
3847 return;
3848 }
3849 m_context->hint(target, mode);
3850}
3851
3852GCGLboolean WebGLRenderingContextBase::isBuffer(WebGLBuffer* buffer)
3853{
3854 if (!buffer || isContextLostOrPending() || !buffer->validate(contextGroup(), *this))
3855 return 0;
3856
3857 if (!buffer->hasEverBeenBound())
3858 return 0;
3859 if (buffer->isDeleted())
3860 return 0;
3861
3862 return m_context->isBuffer(buffer->object());
3863}
3864
3865bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::isContextLost() const
3866{
3867 return m_contextLost;
3868}
3869
3870bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::isContextLostOrPending()
3871{
3872 if (m_isPendingPolicyResolution && !m_hasRequestedPolicyResolution) {
3873 LOG(WebGL, "Context is being used. Attempt to resolve the policy.");
3874 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
3875 if (canvas) {
3876 Document& document = canvas->document().topDocument();
3877 Page* page = document.page();
3878 if (page && !document.url().isLocalFile())
3879 page->mainFrame().loader().client().resolveWebGLPolicyForURL(document.url());
3880 // FIXME: We don't currently do anything with the result from resolution. A more
3881 // complete implementation might try to construct a real context, etc and proceed
3882 // with normal operation.
3883 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=129122
3884 }
3885 m_hasRequestedPolicyResolution = true;
3886 }
3887
3888 return m_contextLost || m_isPendingPolicyResolution;
3889}
3890
3891GCGLboolean WebGLRenderingContextBase::isEnabled(GCGLenum cap)
3892{
3893 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateCapability("isEnabled", cap))
3894 return 0;
3895 if (cap == GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_TEST)
3896 return m_stencilEnabled;
3897 return m_context->isEnabled(cap);
3898}

3913GCGLboolean WebGLRenderingContextBase::isProgram(WebGLProgram* program)

3916 return 0;

3919 // while attached to the current context state, glIsProgram is supposed to
3920 // still return true. For this reason, isDeleted is not checked here.
3921
3922 return m_context->isProgram(program->object());
3923}

3969
3970void WebGLRenderingContextBase::linkProgram(WebGLProgram& program)
3971{
3972 if (!linkProgramWithoutInvalidatingAttribLocations(&program))
3973 return;
3974
3975 program.increaseLinkCount();
3976}
3977
3978bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::linkProgramWithoutInvalidatingAttribLocations(WebGLProgram* program)
3979{
3980 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("linkProgram", program))
3981 return false;
3982
3983 RefPtr<WebGLShader> vertexShader = program->getAttachedShader(GraphicsContextGL::VERTEX_SHADER);
3984 RefPtr<WebGLShader> fragmentShader = program->getAttachedShader(GraphicsContextGL::FRAGMENT_SHADER);
3985 if (!vertexShader || !vertexShader->isValid() || !fragmentShader || !fragmentShader->isValid()) {
3986 program->setLinkStatus(false);
3987 return false;
3988 }
3989
3990#if !USE(ANGLE)
3991 if (!static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->precisionsMatch(objectOrZero(vertexShader.get()), objectOrZero(fragmentShader.get()))
3992 || !static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->checkVaryingsPacking(objectOrZero(vertexShader.get()), objectOrZero(fragmentShader.get()))) {
3993 program->setLinkStatus(false);
3994 return false;
3995 }
3996#endif
3997
3998 m_context->linkProgram(objectOrZero(program));
3999 return true;
4000}
4001
4002#if ENABLE(WEBXR)
4003// https://immersive-web.github.io/webxr/#dom-webglrenderingcontextbase-makexrcompatible
4004void WebGLRenderingContextBase::makeXRCompatible(MakeXRCompatiblePromise&& promise)
4005{
4006 // Returning an exception in these two checks is not part of the spec.
4007 auto canvas = htmlCanvas();
4008 if (!canvas) {
4009 m_isXRCompatible = false;
4010 promise.reject(Exception { InvalidStateError });
4011 return;
4012 }
4013
4014 auto* window = canvas->document().domWindow();
4015 if (!window) {
4016 m_isXRCompatible = false;
4017 promise.reject(Exception { InvalidStateError });
4018 return;
4019 }
4020
4021 // 1. Let promise be a new Promise.
4022 // 2. Let context be the target WebGLRenderingContextBase object.
4023 // 3. Ensure an immersive XR device is selected.
4024 auto& xrSystem = NavigatorWebXR::xr(window->navigator());
4025 xrSystem.ensureImmersiveXRDeviceIsSelected([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), promise = WTFMove(promise), protectedXrSystem = makeRef(xrSystem)]() mutable {
4026 auto rejectPromiseWithInvalidStateError = makeScopeExit([&]() {
4027 m_isXRCompatible = false;
4028 promise.reject(Exception { InvalidStateError });
4029 });
4030
4031 // 4. Set contexts XR compatible boolean as follows:
4032 // If contexts WebGL context lost flag is set
4033 // Set contexts XR compatible boolean to false and reject promise with an InvalidStateError.
4034 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4035 return;
4036
4037 // If the immersive XR device is null
4038 // Set contexts XR compatible boolean to false and reject promise with an InvalidStateError.
4039 if (!protectedXrSystem->hasActiveImmersiveXRDevice())
4040 return;
4041
4042 // If contexts XR compatible boolean is true. Resolve promise.
4043 // If context was created on a compatible graphics adapter for the immersive XR device
4044 // Set contexts XR compatible boolean to true and resolve promise.
4045 // Otherwise: Queue a task on the WebGL task source to perform the following steps:
4046 // FIXME: add a way to verify that we're using a compatible graphics adapter.
4047 m_isXRCompatible = true;
4048 promise.resolve();
4049 rejectPromiseWithInvalidStateError.release();
4050 });
4051}
4052#endif
4053
4054void WebGLRenderingContextBase::pixelStorei(GCGLenum pname, GCGLint param)
4055{
4056 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4057 return;
4058 switch (pname) {
4059 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_FLIP_Y_WEBGL:
4060 m_unpackFlipY = param;
4061 break;
4062 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_PREMULTIPLY_ALPHA_WEBGL:
4063 m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha = param;
4064 break;
4065 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_COLORSPACE_CONVERSION_WEBGL:
4066 if (param == GraphicsContextGL::BROWSER_DEFAULT_WEBGL || param == GraphicsContextGL::NONE)
4067 m_unpackColorspaceConversion = static_cast<GCGLenum>(param);
4068 else {
4069 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "pixelStorei", "invalid parameter for UNPACK_COLORSPACE_CONVERSION_WEBGL");
4070 return;
4071 }
4072 break;
4073 case GraphicsContextGL::PACK_ALIGNMENT:
4074 case GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ALIGNMENT:
4075 if (param == 1 || param == 2 || param == 4 || param == 8) {
4076 if (pname == GraphicsContextGL::PACK_ALIGNMENT)
4077 m_packAlignment = param;
4078 else // GraphicsContextGL::UNPACK_ALIGNMENT:
4079 m_unpackAlignment = param;
4080 m_context->pixelStorei(pname, param);
4081 } else {
4082 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "pixelStorei", "invalid parameter for alignment");
4083 return;
4084 }
4085 break;
4086 default:
4087 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "pixelStorei", "invalid parameter name");
4088 return;
4089 }
4090}
4091
4092void WebGLRenderingContextBase::polygonOffset(GCGLfloat factor, GCGLfloat units)
4093{
4094 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4095 return;
4096 m_context->polygonOffset(factor, units);
4097}

4106 UnsignedInteger
4107};

4156 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB32I:

4169 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB32UI:
4170 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8UI:
4171 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA16UI:

4180{

4182 case GraphicsContextGL::RED:
4183 case GraphicsContextGL::RED_INTEGER:
4184 return 1;
4185 case GraphicsContextGL::RG:
4186 case GraphicsContextGL::RG_INTEGER:
4187 return 2;
4188 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB:
4189 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB_INTEGER:
4190 return 3;
4191 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA:
4192 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA_INTEGER:
4193 return 4;
4194 default:
4195 return 0;
4196 }
4197}

4210 case GraphicsContextGL::R16UI:

4226 case GraphicsContextGL::RG16I:

4228 case GraphicsContextGL::RG32I:

4272
4273void WebGLRenderingContextBase::readPixels(GCGLint x, GCGLint y, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, ArrayBufferView& pixels)
4274{
4275 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4276 return;
4277 // Due to WebGL's same-origin restrictions, it is not possible to
4278 // taint the origin using the WebGL API.
4279 ASSERT(canvasBase().originClean());
4280
4281#if USE(ANGLE)
4282 // ANGLE will validate the readback from the framebuffer according
4283 // to WebGL's restrictions. At this level, just validate the type
4284 // of the readback against the typed array's type.
4285 if (!validateArrayBufferType("readPixels", type, std::optional<JSC::TypedArrayType>(pixels.getType())))
4286 return;
4287#else
4288 GCGLenum internalFormat = 0;
4289 if (m_framebufferBinding) {
4290 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
4291 if (!m_framebufferBinding->onAccess(graphicsContextGL(), &reason)) {
4292 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, "readPixels", reason);
4293 return;
4294 }
4295 // FIXME: readBuffer() should affect this
4296 internalFormat = getReadFramebufferBinding()->getColorBufferFormat();
4297 } else {
4298 if (m_attributes.alpha)
4299 internalFormat = GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8;
4300 else
4301 internalFormat = GraphicsContextGL::RGB8;
4302 }
4303
4304 if (!internalFormat) {
4305 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "readPixels", "Missing attachment");
4306 return;
4307 }
4308
4309 if (isWebGL1()) {
4310 switch (format) {
4311 case GraphicsContextGL::ALPHA:
4312 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB:
4313 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA:
4314 break;
4315 default:
4316 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "invalid format");
4317 return;
4318 }
4319 switch (type) {
4320 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
4321 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5:
4322 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4:
4323 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1:
4324 break;
4325 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
4326 if (!m_oesTextureFloat && !m_oesTextureHalfFloat) {
4327 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "invalid type");
4328 return;
4329 }
4330 break;
4331 default:
4332 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "invalid type");
4333 return;
4334 }
4335 if (format != GraphicsContextGL::RGBA || (type != GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE && type != GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT)) {
4336 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "readPixels", "format not RGBA or type not UNSIGNED_BYTE|FLOAT");
4337 return;
4338 }
4339 }
4340
4341 InternalFormatTheme internalFormatTheme = WebCore::internalFormatTheme(internalFormat);
4342 int internalFormatComponentCount = numberOfComponentsForInternalFormat(internalFormat);
4343 if (internalFormatTheme == InternalFormatTheme::None || !internalFormatComponentCount) {
4344 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "Incorrect internal format");
4345 return;
4346 }
4347
4348#define CHECK_COMPONENT_COUNT \
4349 if (numberOfComponentsForFormat(format) < internalFormatComponentCount) { \
4350 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "Not enough components in format"); \
4351 return; \
4352 }
4353
4354#define INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(typeMacro, pixelTypeMacro) \
4355 if (type != GraphicsContextGL::typeMacro || pixels.getType() != JSC::pixelTypeMacro) { \
4356 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "type does not match internal format"); \
4357 return; \
4358 } \
4359 if (format != GraphicsContextGL::RED && format != GraphicsContextGL::RG && format != GraphicsContextGL::RGB && format != GraphicsContextGL::RGBA) { \
4360 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "Unknown format"); \
4361 return; \
4362 } \
4363 CHECK_COMPONENT_COUNT
4364
4365#define INTERNAL_FORMAT_INTEGER_CHECK(typeMacro, pixelTypeMacro) \
4366 if (type != GraphicsContextGL::typeMacro || pixels.getType() != JSC::pixelTypeMacro) { \
4367 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "type does not match internal format"); \
4368 return; \
4369 } \
4370 if (format != GraphicsContextGL::RED_INTEGER && format != GraphicsContextGL::RG_INTEGER && format != GraphicsContextGL::RGB_INTEGER && format != GraphicsContextGL::RGBA_INTEGER) { \
4371 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "Unknown format"); \
4372 return; \
4373 } \
4374 CHECK_COMPONENT_COUNT
4375
4376#define CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(internalFormatMacro, formatMacro, type0Macro, pixelType0Macro, type1Macro, pixelType1Macro) case GraphicsContextGL::internalFormatMacro: \
4377 if (!(type == GraphicsContextGL::type0Macro && pixels.getType() == JSC::pixelType0Macro) \
4378 && !(type == GraphicsContextGL::type1Macro && pixels.getType() == JSC::pixelType1Macro)) { \
4379 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "type does not match internal format"); \
4380 return; \
4381 } \
4382 if (format != GraphicsContextGL::formatMacro) { \
4383 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "readPixels", "Invalid format"); \
4384 return; \
4385 } \
4386 break;
4387
4388 switch (internalFormatTheme) {
4389 case InternalFormatTheme::NormalizedFixedPoint:
4390 if (type == GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT) {
4391 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(FLOAT, TypeFloat32);
4392 } else {
4393 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(UNSIGNED_BYTE, TypeUint8);
4394 }
4395 break;
4396 case InternalFormatTheme::SignedNormalizedFixedPoint:
4397 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(BYTE, TypeInt8);
4398 break;
4399 case InternalFormatTheme::FloatingPoint:
4400 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(FLOAT, TypeFloat32);
4401 break;
4402 case InternalFormatTheme::SignedInteger:
4403 INTERNAL_FORMAT_INTEGER_CHECK(INT, TypeInt32);
4404 break;
4405 case InternalFormatTheme::UnsignedInteger:
4406 INTERNAL_FORMAT_INTEGER_CHECK(UNSIGNED_INT, TypeUint32);
4407 break;
4408 case InternalFormatTheme::Packed:
4409 switch (internalFormat) {
4410 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(RGB565 , RGB , UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5 , TypeUint16, UNSIGNED_BYTE , TypeUint8 );
4411 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(RGB5_A1 , RGBA , UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1 , TypeUint16, UNSIGNED_BYTE , TypeUint8 );
4412 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(RGBA4 , RGBA , UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4 , TypeUint16, UNSIGNED_BYTE , TypeUint8 );
4413 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(RGB9_E5 , RGB , UNSIGNED_INT_5_9_9_9_REV , TypeUint32, UNSIGNED_INT_5_9_9_9_REV , TypeUint32 );
4414 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(RGB10_A2 , RGBA , UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV , TypeUint32, UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV, TypeUint32 );
4415 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(R11F_G11F_B10F, RGB , UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV, TypeUint32, FLOAT , TypeFloat32);
4416 CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK(RGB10_A2UI , RGBA_INTEGER, UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV , TypeUint32, UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV, TypeUint32 );
4417 }
4418 break;
4419 case InternalFormatTheme::None:
4420 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4421 }
4422#undef CHECK_COMPONENT_COUNT
4423#undef INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK
4424#undef INTERNAL_FORMAT_INTEGER_CHECK
4425#undef CASE_PACKED_INTERNAL_FORMAT_CHECK
4426
4427 // Calculate array size, taking into consideration of PACK_ALIGNMENT.
4428 unsigned totalBytesRequired = 0;
4429 unsigned padding = 0;
4430 if (!m_isRobustnessEXTSupported) {
4431 GCGLenum error = m_context->computeImageSizeInBytes(format, type, width, height, 1, getPackPixelStoreParams(), &totalBytesRequired, &padding, nullptr);
4432 if (error != GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR) {
4433 synthesizeGLError(error, "readPixels", "invalid dimensions");
4434 return;
4435 }
4436 if (pixels.byteLength() < totalBytesRequired) {
4437 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "readPixels", "ArrayBufferView not large enough for dimensions");
4438 return;
4439 }
4440 }
4441#endif // USE(ANGLE)
4442
4443 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
4444 void* data = pixels.baseAddress();
4445
4446#if USE(ANGLE)
4447 m_context->readnPixels(x, y, width, height, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(data, pixels.byteLength()));
4448#else
4449 if (m_isRobustnessEXTSupported)
4450 m_context->getExtensions().readnPixelsEXT(x, y, width, height, format, type, pixels.byteLength(), data);
4451 else
4452 m_context->readnPixels(x, y, width, height, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(data, pixels.byteLength()));
4453#endif
4454}
4455
4456void WebGLRenderingContextBase::renderbufferStorage(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height)
4457{
4458 const char* functionName = "renderbufferStorage";
4459 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4460 return;
4461 if (target != GraphicsContextGL::RENDERBUFFER) {
4462 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
4463 return;
4464 }
4465 if (!m_renderbufferBinding || !m_renderbufferBinding->object()) {
4466 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no bound renderbuffer");
4467 return;
4468 }
4469 if (!validateSize(functionName, width, height))
4470 return;
4471 renderbufferStorageImpl(target, 0, internalformat, width, height, functionName);
4472 applyStencilTest();
4473}
4474
4475void WebGLRenderingContextBase::renderbufferStorageImpl(GCGLenum target, GCGLsizei samples, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, const char* functionName)
4476{
4477#if ASSERT_ENABLED
4478 // |samples| > 0 is only valid in WebGL2's renderbufferStorageMultisample().
4479 ASSERT(!samples);
4480#else
4481 UNUSED_PARAM(samples);
4482#endif
4483 // Make sure this is overridden in WebGL 2.
4484 ASSERT(!isWebGL2());
4485 switch (internalformat) {
4486 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT16:
4487 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA4:
4488 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB5_A1:
4489 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB565:
4490 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_INDEX8:
4491 case ExtensionsGL::SRGB8_ALPHA8_EXT:
4492 if (internalformat == ExtensionsGL::SRGB8_ALPHA8_EXT && !m_extsRGB) {
4493 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid internalformat");
4494 return;
4495 }
4496 m_context->renderbufferStorage(target, internalformat, width, height);
4497 m_renderbufferBinding->setInternalFormat(internalformat);
4498 m_renderbufferBinding->setIsValid(true);
4499 m_renderbufferBinding->setSize(width, height);
4500 break;
4501 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL:
4502 if (isDepthStencilSupported())
4503 m_context->renderbufferStorage(target, ExtensionsGL::DEPTH24_STENCIL8, width, height);
4504 m_renderbufferBinding->setSize(width, height);
4505 m_renderbufferBinding->setIsValid(isDepthStencilSupported());
4506 m_renderbufferBinding->setInternalFormat(internalformat);
4507 break;
4508 default:
4509 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid internalformat");
4510 return;
4511 }
4512}
4513
4514void WebGLRenderingContextBase::sampleCoverage(GCGLfloat value, GCGLboolean invert)
4515{
4516 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4517 return;
4518 m_context->sampleCoverage(value, invert);
4519}

4530void WebGLRenderingContextBase::shaderSource(WebGLShader& shader, const String& string)
4531{

4533 return;

4536#else

4538 if (!validateString("shaderSource", stringWithoutComments))
4539 return;
4540 m_context->shaderSource(shader.object(), stringWithoutComments);
4541#endif
4542 shader.setSource(string);
4543}

4545void WebGLRenderingContextBase::stencilFunc(GCGLenum func, GCGLint ref, GCGLuint mask)
4546{
4547 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4548 return;
4549 if (!validateStencilFunc("stencilFunc", func))
4550 return;
4551 m_stencilFuncRef = ref;
4552 m_stencilFuncRefBack = ref;
4553 m_stencilFuncMask = mask;
4554 m_stencilFuncMaskBack = mask;
4555 m_context->stencilFunc(func, ref, mask);
4556}
4557
4558void WebGLRenderingContextBase::stencilFuncSeparate(GCGLenum face, GCGLenum func, GCGLint ref, GCGLuint mask)
4559{
4560 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4561 return;
4562 if (!validateStencilFunc("stencilFuncSeparate", func))
4563 return;
4564 switch (face) {
4565 case GraphicsContextGL::FRONT_AND_BACK:
4566 m_stencilFuncRef = ref;
4567 m_stencilFuncRefBack = ref;
4568 m_stencilFuncMask = mask;
4569 m_stencilFuncMaskBack = mask;
4570 break;
4571 case GraphicsContextGL::FRONT:
4572 m_stencilFuncRef = ref;
4573 m_stencilFuncMask = mask;
4574 break;
4575 case GraphicsContextGL::BACK:
4576 m_stencilFuncRefBack = ref;
4577 m_stencilFuncMaskBack = mask;
4578 break;
4579 default:
4580 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "stencilFuncSeparate", "invalid face");
4581 return;
4582 }
4583 m_context->stencilFuncSeparate(face, func, ref, mask);
4584}
4585

4587{
4588 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4589 return;
4590 m_stencilMask = mask;
4591 m_stencilMaskBack = mask;
4592 m_context->stencilMask(mask);
4593}
4594
4595void WebGLRenderingContextBase::stencilMaskSeparate(GCGLenum face, GCGLuint mask)
4596{
4597 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4598 return;

4600 case GraphicsContextGL::FRONT_AND_BACK:
4601 m_stencilMask = mask;
4602 m_stencilMaskBack = mask;
4603 break;
4604 case GraphicsContextGL::FRONT:
4605 m_stencilMask = mask;
4606 break;
4607 case GraphicsContextGL::BACK:
4608 m_stencilMaskBack = mask;
4609 break;
4610 default:
4611 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "stencilMaskSeparate", "invalid face");
4612 return;
4613 }
4614 m_context->stencilMaskSeparate(face, mask);
4615}
