4631#if !USE(ANGLE)
4632static bool isRGBFormat(GCGLenum internalFormat)
4633{
4634 return internalFormat == GraphicsContextGL::RGB
4635 || internalFormat == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA
4636 || internalFormat == GraphicsContextGL::RGB8
4637 || internalFormat == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA8;
4638}
4639#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
4640
4641IntRect WebGLRenderingContextBase::sentinelEmptyRect()
4642{
4643 // Return a rectangle with -1 width and height so we can recognize
4644 // it later and recalculate it based on the Image whose data we'll
4645 // upload. It's important that there be no possible differences in
4646 // the logic which computes the image's size.
4647 return IntRect(0, 0, -1, -1);
4648}
4649
4650IntRect WebGLRenderingContextBase::safeGetImageSize(Image* image)
4651{
4652 if (!image)
4653 return IntRect();
4654
4655 return getTextureSourceSize(image);
4656}
4657
4658IntRect WebGLRenderingContextBase::getImageDataSize(ImageData* pixels)
4659{
4660 ASSERT(pixels);
4661 return getTextureSourceSize(pixels);
4662}
4663
4664IntRect WebGLRenderingContextBase::getTexImageSourceSize(TexImageSource& source)
4665{
4666 auto visitor = WTF::makeVisitor([&](const RefPtr<ImageBitmap>& bitmap) -> ExceptionOr<IntRect> {
4667 return getTextureSourceSize(bitmap.get());
4668 }, [&](const RefPtr<ImageData>& pixels) -> ExceptionOr<IntRect> {
4669 return getTextureSourceSize(pixels.get());
4670 }, [&](const RefPtr<HTMLImageElement>& image) -> ExceptionOr<IntRect> {
4671 return getTextureSourceSize(image.get());
4672 }, [&](const RefPtr<HTMLCanvasElement>& canvas) -> ExceptionOr<IntRect> {
4673 return getTextureSourceSize(canvas.get());
4674#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
4675 }, [&](const RefPtr<HTMLVideoElement>& video) -> ExceptionOr<IntRect> {
4676 return IntRect(0, 0, video->videoWidth(), video->videoHeight());
4677#endif // ENABLE(VIDEO)
4678 }
4679 );
4680
4681 ExceptionOr<IntRect> result = WTF::visit(visitor, source);
4682 if (result.hasException())
4683 return sentinelEmptyRect();
4684 return result.returnValue();
4685}
4686
4687ExceptionOr<void> WebGLRenderingContextBase::texImageSourceHelper(TexImageFunctionID functionID, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint internalformat, GCGLint border, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLint zoffset, const IntRect& inputSourceImageRect, GCGLsizei depth, GCGLint unpackImageHeight, TexImageSource&& source)
4688{
4689 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4690 return { };
4691
4692 const char* functionName = getTexImageFunctionName(functionID);
4693 TexImageFunctionType functionType;
4694 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D || functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage3D)
4695 functionType = TexImageFunctionType::TexImage;
4696 else
4697 functionType = TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage;
4698
4699#if !USE(ANGLE)
4700 if (functionType == TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage) {
4701 auto texture = validateTexImageBinding(functionName, functionID, target);
4702 if (texture)
4703 internalformat = texture->getInternalFormat(target, level);
4704 }
4705#endif
4706
4707 auto visitor = WTF::makeVisitor([&](const RefPtr<ImageBitmap>& bitmap) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
4708 auto validationResult = validateImageBitmap(functionName, bitmap.get());
4709 if (validationResult.hasException())
4710 return validationResult.releaseException();
4711 auto texture = validateTexImageBinding(functionName, functionID, target);
4712 if (!texture)
4713 return { };
4714 IntRect sourceImageRect = inputSourceImageRect;
4715 if (sourceImageRect == sentinelEmptyRect()) {
4716 // Simply measure the input for WebGL 1.0, which doesn't support sub-rectangle selection.
4717 sourceImageRect = getTextureSourceSize(bitmap.get());
4718 }
4719 bool selectingSubRectangle = false;
4720 if (!validateTexImageSubRectangle(functionName, functionID, bitmap.get(), sourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight, &selectingSubRectangle))
4721 return { };
4722 int width = sourceImageRect.width();
4723 int height = sourceImageRect.height();
4724 if (!validateTexFunc(functionName, functionType, SourceImageBitmap, target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
4725 return { };
4726
4727 ImageBuffer* buffer = bitmap->buffer();
4728 if (!buffer)
4729 return { };
4730
4731#if !USE(ANGLE)
4732 // FIXME: Enable this path with ANGLE. Only used with Cairo, not on macOS or iOS.
4733 // If possible, copy from the bitmap directly to the texture
4734 // via the GPU, without a read-back to system memory.
4735 //
4736 // FIXME: restriction of (RGB || RGBA)/UNSIGNED_BYTE should be lifted when
4737 // ImageBuffer::copyToPlatformTexture implementations are fully functional.
4738 if (texture
4739 && (format == GraphicsContextGL::RGB || format == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA)
4740 && type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE) {
4741 auto textureInternalFormat = texture->getInternalFormat(target, level);
4742 if (isRGBFormat(textureInternalFormat) || !texture->isValid(target, level)) {
4743 // The premultiplyAlpha and flipY pixel unpack parameters are ignored for ImageBitmaps.
4744 if (buffer->copyToPlatformTexture(*m_context.get(), target, texture->object(), internalformat, bitmap->premultiplyAlpha(), false)) {
4745 texture->setLevelInfo(target, level, internalformat, width, height, type);
4746 return { };
4747 }
4748 }
4749 }
4750#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
4751
4752 // Fallback pure SW path.
4753 RefPtr<Image> image = buffer->copyImage(DontCopyBackingStore);
4754 // The premultiplyAlpha and flipY pixel unpack parameters are ignored for ImageBitmaps.
4755 if (image)
4756 texImageImpl(functionID, target, level, internalformat, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, format, type, image.get(), GraphicsContextGL::DOMSource::Image, false, bitmap->premultiplyAlpha(), bitmap->forciblyPremultiplyAlpha(), sourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight);
4757 return { };
4758 }, [&](const RefPtr<ImageData>& pixels) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
4759 if (pixels->data().isDetached()) {
4760 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "The source data has been detached.");
4761 return { };
4762 }
4763
4764 if (!validateTexImageBinding(functionName, functionID, target))
4765 return { };
4766 if (!validateTexFunc(functionName, functionType, SourceImageData, target, level, internalformat, pixels->width(), pixels->height(), depth, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
4767 return { };
4768 IntRect sourceImageRect = inputSourceImageRect;
4769 if (sourceImageRect == sentinelEmptyRect()) {
4770 // Simply measure the input for WebGL 1.0, which doesn't support sub-rectangle selection.
4771 sourceImageRect = getTextureSourceSize(pixels.get());
4772 }
4773 bool selectingSubRectangle = false;
4774 if (!validateTexImageSubRectangle(functionName, functionID, pixels.get(), sourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight, &selectingSubRectangle))
4775 return { };
4776 // Adjust the source image rectangle if doing a y-flip.
4777 IntRect adjustedSourceImageRect = sourceImageRect;
4778 if (m_unpackFlipY)
4779 adjustedSourceImageRect.setY(pixels->height() - adjustedSourceImageRect.maxY());
4780
4781 Vector<uint8_t> data;
4782 bool needConversion = true;
4783 GCGLsizei byteLength = 0;
4784 // The data from ImageData is always of format RGBA8.
4785 // No conversion is needed if destination format is RGBA and type is USIGNED_BYTE and no Flip or Premultiply operation is required.
4786 if (!m_unpackFlipY && !m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha && format == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA && type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE && !selectingSubRectangle && depth == 1) {
4787 needConversion = false;
4788 byteLength = pixels->data().byteLength();
4789 } else {
4790 if (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV) {
4791 // The UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV type pack/unpack isn't implemented.
4792 type = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
4793 }
4794 if (!m_context->extractPixelBuffer(pixels->pixelBuffer(), GraphicsContextGL::DataFormat::RGBA8, adjustedSourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight, format, type, m_unpackFlipY, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, data)) {
4795 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "texImage2D", "bad image data");
4796 return { };
4797 }
4798 byteLength = data.size();
4799 }
4800 ScopedUnpackParametersResetRestore temporaryResetUnpack(this);
4801 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D) {
4802 texImage2DBase(target, level, internalformat,
4803 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(), 0,
4804 format, type, byteLength, needConversion ? data.data() : pixels->data().data());
4805 } else if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D) {
4806 texSubImage2DBase(target, level, xoffset, yoffset,
4807 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(),
4808 format, format, type, byteLength, needConversion ? data.data() : pixels->data().data());
4809 } else {
4810#if USE(ANGLE)
4811 // 3D functions.
4812 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage3D) {
4813 m_context->texImage3D(target, level, internalformat,
4814 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(), depth, 0,
4815 format, type, makeGCGLSpan(needConversion ? data.data() : pixels->data().data(), byteLength));
4816 } else {
4817 ASSERT(functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage3D);
4818 m_context->texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset,
4819 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(), depth,
4820 format, type, makeGCGLSpan(needConversion ? data.data() : pixels->data().data(), byteLength));
4821 }
4822#else
4823 // WebGL 2.0 is only supported with the ANGLE backend.
4824 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
4825#endif
4826 }
4827
4828 return { };
4829 }, [&](const RefPtr<HTMLImageElement>& image) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
4830 auto validationResult = validateHTMLImageElement(functionName, image.get());
4831 if (validationResult.hasException())
4832 return validationResult.releaseException();
4833 if (!validationResult.returnValue())
4834 return { };
4835
4836 RefPtr<Image> imageForRender = image->cachedImage()->imageForRenderer(image->renderer());
4837 if (!imageForRender)
4838 return { };
4839
4840 if (imageForRender->isSVGImage() || imageForRender->orientation() != ImageOrientation::None || imageForRender->hasDensityCorrectedSize())
4841 imageForRender = drawImageIntoBuffer(*imageForRender, image->width(), image->height(), 1, functionName);
4842
4843 if (!imageForRender || !validateTexFunc(functionName, functionType, SourceHTMLImageElement, target, level, internalformat, imageForRender->width(), imageForRender->height(), depth, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
4844 return { };
4845
4846 // Pass along inputSourceImageRect unchanged. HTMLImageElements are unique in that their
4847 // size may differ from that of the Image obtained from them (because of devicePixelRatio),
4848 // so for WebGL 1.0 uploads, defer measuring their rectangle as long as possible.
4849 texImageImpl(functionID, target, level, internalformat, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, format, type, imageForRender.get(), GraphicsContextGL::DOMSource::Image, m_unpackFlipY, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, false, inputSourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight);
4850 return { };
4851 }, [&](const RefPtr<HTMLCanvasElement>& canvas) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
4852 auto validationResult = validateHTMLCanvasElement(functionName, canvas.get());
4853 if (validationResult.hasException())
4854 return validationResult.releaseException();
4855 if (!validationResult.returnValue())
4856 return { };
4857 auto texture = validateTexImageBinding(functionName, functionID, target);
4858 if (!texture)
4859 return { };
4860 IntRect sourceImageRect = inputSourceImageRect;
4861 if (sourceImageRect == sentinelEmptyRect()) {
4862 // Simply measure the input for WebGL 1.0, which doesn't support sub-rectangle selection.
4863 sourceImageRect = getTextureSourceSize(canvas.get());
4864 }
4865 if (!validateTexFunc(functionName, functionType, SourceHTMLCanvasElement, target, level, internalformat, sourceImageRect.width(), sourceImageRect.height(), depth, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
4866 return { };
4867
4868#if !USE(ANGLE)
4869 // FIXME: Enable this path with ANGLE. Only used with Cairo, not on macOS or iOS.
4870
4871 // If possible, copy from the canvas element directly to the texture
4872 // via the GPU, without a read-back to system memory.
4873 //
4874 // FIXME: restriction of (RGB || RGBA)/UNSIGNED_BYTE should be lifted when
4875 // ImageBuffer::copyToPlatformTexture implementations are fully functional.
4876 if (texture
4877 && (format == GraphicsContextGL::RGB || format == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA)
4878 && type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE) {
4879 auto textureInternalFormat = texture->getInternalFormat(target, level);
4880 if (isRGBFormat(textureInternalFormat) || !texture->isValid(target, level)) {
4881 ImageBuffer* buffer = canvas->buffer();
4882 if (buffer && buffer->copyToPlatformTexture(*m_context.get(), target, texture->object(), internalformat, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, m_unpackFlipY)) {
4883 texture->setLevelInfo(target, level, internalformat, sourceImageRect.width(), sourceImageRect.height(), type);
4884 return { };
4885 }
4886 }
4887 }
4888#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
4889 RefPtr<ImageData> imageData = canvas->getImageData();
4890 if (imageData)
4891 texImageSourceHelper(functionID, target, level, internalformat, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, sourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight, TexImageSource(imageData.get()));
4892 else
4893 texImageImpl(functionID, target, level, internalformat, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, format, type, canvas->copiedImage(), GraphicsContextGL::DOMSource::Canvas, m_unpackFlipY, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, false, sourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight);
4894 return { };
4895 }
4896#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
4897 , [&](const RefPtr<HTMLVideoElement>& video) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
4898 auto validationResult = validateHTMLVideoElement("texImage2D", video.get());
4899 if (validationResult.hasException())
4900 return validationResult.releaseException();
4901 if (!validationResult.returnValue())
4902 return { };
4903 auto texture = validateTexImageBinding(functionName, functionID, target);
4904 if (!texture)
4905 return { };
4906 if (!validateTexFunc(functionName, functionType, SourceHTMLVideoElement, target, level, internalformat, video->videoWidth(), video->videoHeight(), depth, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
4907 return { };
4908 if (!inputSourceImageRect.isValid()) {
4909 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "source sub-rectangle specified via pixel unpack parameters is invalid");
4910 return { };
4911 }
4912 // Pass along inputSourceImageRect unchanged, including empty rectangles. Measure video
4913 // elements' size for WebGL 1.0 as late as possible.
4914 bool sourceImageRectIsDefault = inputSourceImageRect == sentinelEmptyRect() || inputSourceImageRect == IntRect(0, 0, video->videoWidth(), video->videoHeight());
4915
4916 // Go through the fast path doing a GPU-GPU textures copy without a readback to system memory if possible.
4917 // Otherwise, it will fall back to the normal SW path.
4918 // FIXME: The current restrictions require that format shoud be RGB or RGBA,
4919 // type should be UNSIGNED_BYTE and level should be 0. It may be lifted in the future.
4920 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D && sourceImageRectIsDefault && texture
4921 && (format == GraphicsContextGL::RGB || format == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA)
4922 && type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE
4923 && !level) {
4924 if (video->player() && m_context->copyTextureFromMedia(*video->player(), texture->object(), target, level, internalformat, format, type, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, m_unpackFlipY)) {
4925#if !USE(ANGLE)
4926 texture->setLevelInfo(target, level, internalformat, video->videoWidth(), video->videoHeight(), type);
4927#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
4928 return { };
4929 }
4930 }
4931
4932 // Fallback pure SW path.
4933 RefPtr<Image> image = videoFrameToImage(video.get(), DontCopyBackingStore);
4934 if (!image)
4935 return { };
4936 texImageImpl(functionID, target, level, internalformat, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, format, type, image.get(), GraphicsContextGL::DOMSource::Video, m_unpackFlipY, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, false, inputSourceImageRect, depth, unpackImageHeight);
4937 return { };
4938 }
4939#endif // ENABLE(VIDEO)
4940 );
4941
4942 return WTF::visit(visitor, source);
4943}
4944
4945void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texImageArrayBufferViewHelper(TexImageFunctionID functionID, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint internalformat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLsizei depth, GCGLint border, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLint zoffset, RefPtr<ArrayBufferView>&& pixels, NullDisposition nullDisposition, GCGLuint srcOffset)
4946{
4947 if (isContextLostOrPending())
4948 return;
4949 const char* functionName = getTexImageFunctionName(functionID);
4950 auto texture = validateTexImageBinding(functionName, functionID, target);
4951 if (!texture)
4952 return;
4953 TexImageFunctionType functionType;
4954 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D || functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage3D)
4955 functionType = TexImageFunctionType::TexImage;
4956 else
4957 functionType = TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage;
4958#if !USE(ANGLE)
4959 if (functionType == TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage)
4960 internalformat = texture->getInternalFormat(target, level);
4961#endif
4962
4963 if (!validateTexFunc(functionName, functionType, SourceArrayBufferView, target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
4964 return;
4965 TexImageDimension sourceType;
4966 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D || functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D)
4967 sourceType = TexImageDimension::Tex2D;
4968 else
4969 sourceType = TexImageDimension::Tex3D;
4970 if (!validateTexFuncData(functionName, sourceType, width, height, depth, format, type, pixels.get(), nullDisposition, srcOffset))
4971 return;
4972 auto data = static_cast<uint8_t*>(pixels ? pixels->baseAddress() : nullptr);
4973 if (srcOffset) {
4974 ASSERT(pixels);
4975 // No need to check overflow because validateTexFuncData() already did.
4976 data += srcOffset * JSC::elementSize(pixels->getType());
4977 }
4978 GCGLsizei byteLength = pixels ? pixels->byteLength() : 0;
4979 Vector<uint8_t> tempData;
4980 bool changeUnpackParams = false;
4981 if (data && width && height
4982 && (m_unpackFlipY || m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha)) {
4983 ASSERT(sourceType == TexImageDimension::Tex2D);
4984 // Only enter here if width or height is non-zero. Otherwise, call to the
4985 // underlying driver to generate appropriate GL errors if needed.
4986 PixelStoreParams unpackParams = getUnpackPixelStoreParams(TexImageDimension::Tex2D);
4987 GCGLint dataStoreWidth = unpackParams.rowLength ? unpackParams.rowLength : width;
4988 if (unpackParams.skipPixels + width > dataStoreWidth) {
4989 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "Invalid unpack params combination.");
4990 return;
4991 }
4992 if (!m_context->extractTextureData(width, height, format, type, unpackParams, m_unpackFlipY, m_unpackPremultiplyAlpha, data, tempData))
4993 return;
4994 data = tempData.data();
4995 byteLength = tempData.size();
4996 changeUnpackParams = true;
4997 }
4998#if USE(ANGLE)
4999 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage3D) {
5000 m_context->texImage3D(target, level, internalformat, width, height, depth, border, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(data, byteLength));
5001 return;
5002 }
5003 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage3D) {
5004 m_context->texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, width, height, depth, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(data, byteLength));
5005 return;
5006 }
5007#endif // USE(ANGLE)
5008 ScopedUnpackParametersResetRestore temporaryResetUnpack(this, changeUnpackParams);
5009 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D)
5010 texImage2DBase(target, level, internalformat, width, height, border, format, type, byteLength, data);
5011 else {
5012 ASSERT(functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D);
5013 texSubImage2DBase(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, format, type, byteLength, data);
5014 }
5015}
5016
5017void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texImageImpl(TexImageFunctionID functionID, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLint zoffset, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, Image* image, GraphicsContextGL::DOMSource domSource, bool flipY, bool premultiplyAlpha, bool ignoreNativeImageAlphaPremultiplication, const IntRect& sourceImageRect, GCGLsizei depth, GCGLint unpackImageHeight)
5018{
5019 const char* functionName = getTexImageFunctionName(functionID);
5020 // All calling functions check isContextLostOrPending, so a duplicate check is not
5021 // needed here.
5022 if (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV) {
5023 // The UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV type pack/unpack isn't implemented.
5024 type = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
5025 }
5026 Vector<uint8_t> data;
5027
5028 IntRect subRect = sourceImageRect;
5029 if (subRect.isValid() && subRect == sentinelEmptyRect()) {
5030 // Recalculate based on the size of the Image.
5031 subRect = safeGetImageSize(image);
5032 }
5033
5034 bool selectingSubRectangle = false;
5035 if (!validateTexImageSubRectangle(functionName, functionID, image, subRect, depth, unpackImageHeight, &selectingSubRectangle))
5036 return;
5037
5038 // Adjust the source image rectangle if doing a y-flip.
5039 IntRect adjustedSourceImageRect = subRect;
5040 if (m_unpackFlipY)
5041 adjustedSourceImageRect.setY(image->height() - adjustedSourceImageRect.maxY());
5042
5043 GraphicsContextGLImageExtractor imageExtractor(image, domSource, premultiplyAlpha, m_unpackColorspaceConversion == GraphicsContextGL::NONE, ignoreNativeImageAlphaPremultiplication);
5044 if (!imageExtractor.extractSucceeded()) {
5045 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "bad image data");
5046 return;
5047 }
5048
5049 GraphicsContextGL::DataFormat sourceDataFormat = imageExtractor.imageSourceFormat();
5050 GraphicsContextGL::AlphaOp alphaOp = imageExtractor.imageAlphaOp();
5051 const void* imagePixelData = imageExtractor.imagePixelData();
5052
5053 bool needConversion = true;
5054 GCGLsizei byteLength = 0;
5055 if (type == GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE && sourceDataFormat == GraphicsContextGL::DataFormat::RGBA8 && format == GraphicsContextGL::RGBA && alphaOp == GraphicsContextGL::AlphaOp::DoNothing && !flipY && !selectingSubRectangle && depth == 1) {
5056 needConversion = false;
5057 byteLength = imageExtractor.imageWidth() * imageExtractor.imageHeight() * 4;
5058 } else {
5059 if (!m_context->packImageData(image, imagePixelData, format, type, flipY, alphaOp, sourceDataFormat, imageExtractor.imageWidth(), imageExtractor.imageHeight(), adjustedSourceImageRect, depth, imageExtractor.imageSourceUnpackAlignment(), unpackImageHeight, data)) {
5060 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "packImage error");
5061 return;
5062 }
5063 byteLength = data.size();
5064 }
5065
5066 ScopedUnpackParametersResetRestore temporaryResetUnpack(this, true);
5067 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D) {
5068 texImage2DBase(target, level, internalformat,
5069 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(), 0,
5070 format, type, byteLength, needConversion ? data.data() : imagePixelData);
5071 } else if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D) {
5072 texSubImage2DBase(target, level, xoffset, yoffset,
5073 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(),
5074 format, format, type, byteLength, needConversion ? data.data() : imagePixelData);
5075 } else {
5076#if USE(ANGLE)
5077 // 3D functions.
5078 if (functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexImage3D) {
5079 m_context->texImage3D(target, level, internalformat,
5080 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(), depth, 0,
5081 format, type, makeGCGLSpan(needConversion ? data.data() : imagePixelData, byteLength));
5082 } else {
5083 ASSERT(functionID == TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage3D);
5084 m_context->texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset,
5085 adjustedSourceImageRect.width(), adjustedSourceImageRect.height(), depth,
5086 format, type, makeGCGLSpan(needConversion ? data.data() : imagePixelData, byteLength));
5087 }
5088#else
5089 UNUSED_PARAM(zoffset);
5090 // WebGL 2.0 is only supported with the ANGLE backend.
5091 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5092#endif
5093 }
5094}
5095
5096void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texImage2DBase(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalFormat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLint border, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLsizei byteLength, const void* pixels)
5097{
5098#if USE(ANGLE)
5099 m_context->texImage2D(target, level, internalFormat, width, height, border, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(pixels, byteLength));
5100#else
5101 UNUSED_PARAM(byteLength);
5102 // FIXME: For now we ignore any errors returned.
5103 auto tex = validateTexture2DBinding("texImage2D", target);
5104 ASSERT(validateTexFuncParameters("texImage2D", TexImageFunctionType::TexImage, SourceArrayBufferView, target, level, internalFormat, width, height, 1, border, format, type));
5105 ASSERT(tex);
5106 ASSERT(validateNPOTTextureLevel(width, height, level, "texImage2D"));
5107 if (!pixels) {
5108 if (!static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->texImage2DResourceSafe(target, level, internalFormat, width, height, border, format, type, m_unpackAlignment))
5109 return;
5110 } else {
5111 ASSERT(validateSettableTexInternalFormat("texImage2D", internalFormat));
5112 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
5113 m_context->texImage2D(target, level, internalFormat, width, height, border, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(pixels, byteLength));
5114 if (m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList()) {
5115 // The texImage2D function failed. Tell the WebGLTexture it doesn't have the data for this level.
5116 tex->markInvalid(target, level);
5117 return;
5118 }
5119 }
5120 tex->setLevelInfo(target, level, internalFormat, width, height, type);
5121#endif // USE(ANGLE)
5122}
5123
5124void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texSubImage2DBase(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum internalFormat, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLsizei byteLength, const void* pixels)
5125{
5126 ASSERT(!isContextLost());
5127#if USE(ANGLE)
5128 UNUSED_PARAM(internalFormat);
5129 m_context->texSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(pixels, byteLength));
5130#else
5131 UNUSED_PARAM(byteLength);
5132 ASSERT(validateTexFuncParameters("texSubImage2D", TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage, SourceArrayBufferView, target, level, internalFormat, width, height, 1, 0, format, type));
5133 ASSERT(validateSize("texSubImage2D", xoffset, yoffset));
5134 ASSERT(validateSettableTexInternalFormat("texSubImage2D", internalFormat));
5135 auto tex = validateTexture2DBinding("texSubImage2D", target);
5136 if (!tex) {
5137 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5138 return;
5139 }
5140 ASSERT((xoffset + width) >= 0);
5141 ASSERT((yoffset + height) >= 0);
5142 ASSERT(tex->getWidth(target, level) >= (xoffset + width));
5143 ASSERT(tex->getHeight(target, level) >= (yoffset + height));
5144 if (!isWebGL2())
5145 ASSERT_UNUSED(internalFormat, tex->getInternalFormat(target, level) == internalFormat);
5146 m_context->texSubImage2D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, width, height, format, type, makeGCGLSpan(pixels, byteLength));
5147#endif
5148}
5149
5150const char* WebGLRenderingContextBase::getTexImageFunctionName(TexImageFunctionID funcName)
5151{
5152 switch (funcName) {
5153 case TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D:
5154 return "texImage2D";
5155 case TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D:
5156 return "texSubImage2D";
5157 case TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage3D:
5158 return "texSubImage3D";
5159 case TexImageFunctionID::TexImage3D:
5160 return "texImage3D";
5161 }
5162 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
5163 return nullptr;
5164}
5165
5166bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexFunc(const char* functionName, TexImageFunctionType functionType, TexFuncValidationSourceType sourceType, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalFormat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLsizei depth, GCGLint border, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLint zoffset)
5167{
5168 if (!validateTexFuncLevel(functionName, target, level))
5169 return false;
5170
5171 if (!validateTexFuncParameters(functionName, functionType, sourceType, target, level, internalFormat, width, height, depth, border, format, type))
5172 return false;
5173
5174#if USE(ANGLE)
5175 if (functionType == TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage) {
5176 // Format suffices to validate this.
5177 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat(functionName, format))
5178 return false;
5179 if (!validateSize(functionName, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset))
5180 return false;
5181 } else {
5182 // For SourceArrayBufferView, function validateTexFuncData()
5183 // will handle whether to validate the SettableTexFormat by
5184 // checking if the ArrayBufferView is null or not.
5185 if (sourceType != SourceArrayBufferView) {
5186 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat(functionName, format))
5187 return false;
5188 }
5189 }
5190#else
5191 UNUSED_PARAM(zoffset);
5192 auto texture = validateTexture2DBinding(functionName, target);
5193 if (!texture)
5194 return false;
5195
5196 if (functionType != TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage) {
5197 if (functionType == TexImageFunctionType::TexImage && texture->immutable()) {
5198 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "texStorage() called on this texture previously");
5199 return false;
5200 }
5201 if (!validateNPOTTextureLevel(width, height, level, functionName))
5202 return false;
5203
5204 // For SourceArrayBufferView, function validateTexFuncData() would handle whether to validate the SettableTexFormat
5205 // by checking if the ArrayBufferView is null or not.
5206 if (sourceType != SourceArrayBufferView) {
5207 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat(functionName, internalFormat))
5208 return false;
5209 }
5210 } else {
5211 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat(functionName, internalFormat))
5212 return false;
5213 if (!validateSize(functionName, xoffset, yoffset))
5214 return false;
5215
5216 // Before checking if it is in the range, check if overflow happens first.
5217 if (xoffset + width < 0 || yoffset + height < 0) {
5218 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "bad dimensions");
5219 return false;
5220 }
5221 if (xoffset + width > texture->getWidth(target, level) || yoffset + height > texture->getHeight(target, level)) {
5222 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "dimensions out of range");
5223 return false;
5224 }
5225 if (texture->getInternalFormat(target, level) != internalFormat || (isWebGL1() && texture->getType(target, level) != type)) {
5226 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "type and format do not match texture");
5227 return false;
5228 }
5229 }
5230#endif // USE(ANGLE)
5231
5232 return true;
5233}
5234
5235void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLint border, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, RefPtr<ArrayBufferView>&& pixels)
5236{
5237 texImageArrayBufferViewHelper(TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D, target, level, internalformat, width, height, 1, border, format, type, 0, 0, 0, WTFMove(pixels), NullAllowed, 0);
5238}
5239
5240void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texSubImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, RefPtr<ArrayBufferView>&& pixels)
5241{
5242 texImageArrayBufferViewHelper(TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D, target, level, 0, width, height, 1, 0, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, 0, WTFMove(pixels), NullNotAllowed, 0);
5243}
5244
5245ExceptionOr<void> WebGLRenderingContextBase::texSubImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, std::optional<TexImageSource>&& source)
5246{
5247 if (isContextLostOrPending())
5248 return { };
5249
5250 if (!source) {
5251 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "texSubImage2D", "source is null");
5252 return { };
5253 }
5254
5255 return texImageSourceHelper(TexImageFunctionID::TexSubImage2D, target, level, 0, 0, format, type, xoffset, yoffset, 0, sentinelEmptyRect(), 1, 0, WTFMove(*source));
5256}
5257
5258bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateArrayBufferType(const char* functionName, GCGLenum type, std::optional<JSC::TypedArrayType> arrayType)
5259{
5260#define TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(arrayTypeMacro) if (arrayType && arrayType.value() != JSC::arrayTypeMacro) { \
5261 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "ArrayBufferView not " #arrayTypeMacro); \
5262 return false; \
5263 } \
5264 break;
5265
5266#define TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE_2(arrayTypeMacro, arrayTypeMacro2) if (arrayType && arrayType.value() != JSC::arrayTypeMacro && arrayType.value() != JSC::arrayTypeMacro2) { \
5267 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "ArrayBufferView not " #arrayTypeMacro " or " #arrayTypeMacro2); \
5268 return false; \
5269 } \
5270 break;
5271
5272 switch (type) {
5273 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
5274 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE_2(TypeUint8, TypeUint8Clamped);
5275 case GraphicsContextGL::BYTE:
5276 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeInt8);
5277 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
5278 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5:
5279 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4:
5280 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1:
5281 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeUint16);
5282 case GraphicsContextGL::SHORT:
5283 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeInt16);
5284 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
5285 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV:
5286 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_5_9_9_9_REV:
5287 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_24_8:
5288 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
5289 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeUint32);
5290 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
5291 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeInt32);
5292 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT: // OES_texture_float
5293 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeFloat32);
5294 case GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT_OES: // OES_texture_half_float
5295 case GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT:
5296 TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE(TypeUint16);
5297 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_32_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_REV:
5298 if (arrayType)
5299 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "type FLOAT_32_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_REV but ArrayBufferView is not null");
5300 break;
5301 default:
5302 // This can now be reached in readPixels' ANGLE code path.
5303 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid type");
5304 return false;
5305 }
5306#undef TYPE_VALIDATION_CASE
5307 return true;
5308}
5309
5310bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexFuncData(const char* functionName, TexImageDimension texDimension, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLsizei depth, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, ArrayBufferView* pixels, NullDisposition disposition, GCGLuint srcOffset)
5311{
5312 // All calling functions check isContextLostOrPending, so a duplicate check is not
5313 // needed here.
5314 if (!pixels) {
5315 ASSERT(disposition != NullNotReachable);
5316 if (disposition == NullAllowed)
5317 return true;
5318 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "no pixels");
5319 return false;
5320 }
5321
5322 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat(functionName, format))
5323 return false;
5324 if (!validateArrayBufferType(functionName, type, pixels ? std::optional<JSC::TypedArrayType>(pixels->getType()) : std::nullopt))
5325 return false;
5326
5327 unsigned totalBytesRequired, skipBytes;
5328 GCGLenum error = m_context->computeImageSizeInBytes(format, type, width, height, depth, getUnpackPixelStoreParams(texDimension), &totalBytesRequired, nullptr, &skipBytes);
5329 if (error != GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR) {
5330 synthesizeGLError(error, functionName, "invalid texture dimensions");
5331 return false;
5332 }
5333 CheckedUint32 total = srcOffset;
5334 total *= JSC::elementSize(pixels->getType());
5335 total += totalBytesRequired;
5336 total += skipBytes;
5337 if (total.hasOverflowed() || pixels->byteLength() < total) {
5338 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "ArrayBufferView not big enough for request");
5339 return false;
5340 }
5341 return true;
5342}
5343
5344bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexFuncParameters(const char* functionName,
5345 TexImageFunctionType functionType,
5346 TexFuncValidationSourceType sourceType,
5347 GCGLenum target, GCGLint level,
5348 GCGLenum internalformat,
5349 GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLsizei depth, GCGLint border,
5350 GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type)
5351{
5352 // We absolutely have to validate the format and type combination.
5353 // The texImage2D entry points taking HTMLImage, etc. will produce
5354 // temporary data based on this combination, so it must be legal.
5355 if (sourceType == SourceHTMLImageElement
5356 || sourceType == SourceHTMLCanvasElement
5357#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
5358 || sourceType == SourceHTMLVideoElement
5359#endif
5360 || sourceType == SourceImageData
5361 || sourceType == SourceImageBitmap) {
5362 if (!validateTexImageSourceFormatAndType(functionName, functionType, internalformat, format, type))
5363 return false;
5364 } else {
5365 if (!validateTexFuncFormatAndType(functionName, internalformat, format, type, level))
5366 return false;
5367 }
5368
5369 if (width < 0 || height < 0 || depth < 0) {
5370 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "width or height < 0");
5371 return false;
5372 }
5373
5374 // ANGLE subsumes the validation of the texture level and the texture dimensions for the target.
5375#if USE(ANGLE)
5376 UNUSED_PARAM(target);
5377 UNUSED_PARAM(level);
5378#else
5379 GCGLint maxTextureSizeForLevel = pow(2.0, m_maxTextureLevel - 1 - level);
5380 switch (target) {
5381 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D:
5382 if (width > maxTextureSizeForLevel || height > maxTextureSizeForLevel) {
5383 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "width or height out of range");
5384 return false;
5385 }
5386 break;
5387 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X:
5388 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X:
5389 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y:
5390 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y:
5391 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z:
5392 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z:
5393 if (functionType != TexImageFunctionType::TexSubImage && width != height) {
5394 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "width != height for cube map");
5395 return false;
5396 }
5397 // No need to check height here. For texImage width == height.
5398 // For texSubImage that will be checked when checking yoffset + height is in range.
5399 if (width > maxTextureSizeForLevel) {
5400 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "width or height out of range for cube map");
5401 return false;
5402 }
5403 break;
5404 default:
5405 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
5406 return false;
5407 }
5408#endif // USE(ANGLE)
5409
5410 if (border) {
5411 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "border != 0");
5412 return false;
5413 }
5414
5415 return true;
5416}
5417
5418void WebGLRenderingContextBase::addExtensionSupportedFormatsAndTypes()
5419{
5420 if (!m_areOESTextureFloatFormatsAndTypesAdded && extensionIsEnabled("OES_texture_float")) {
5421 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceTypes, SupportedTypesOESTextureFloat);
5422 m_areOESTextureFloatFormatsAndTypesAdded = true;
5423 }
5424
5425 if (!m_areOESTextureHalfFloatFormatsAndTypesAdded && extensionIsEnabled("OES_texture_half_float")) {
5426 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceTypes, SupportedTypesOESTextureHalfFloat);
5427 m_areOESTextureHalfFloatFormatsAndTypesAdded = true;
5428 }
5429
5430 if (!m_areEXTsRGBFormatsAndTypesAdded && extensionIsEnabled("EXT_sRGB")) {
5431 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceInternalFormats, SupportedInternalFormatsEXTsRGB);
5432 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceFormats, SupportedFormatsEXTsRGB);
5433 m_areEXTsRGBFormatsAndTypesAdded = true;
5434 }
5435}
5436
5437void WebGLRenderingContextBase::addExtensionSupportedFormatsAndTypesWebGL2()
5438{
5439 // FIXME: add EXT_texture_norm16 support.
5440}
5441
5442bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexImageSourceFormatAndType(const char* functionName, TexImageFunctionType functionType, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type)
5443{
5444 if (!m_areWebGL2TexImageSourceFormatsAndTypesAdded && isWebGL2()) {
5445 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceInternalFormats, SupportedInternalFormatsTexImageSourceES3);
5446 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceFormats, SupportedFormatsTexImageSourceES3);
5447 ADD_VALUES_TO_SET(m_supportedTexImageSourceTypes, SupportedTypesTexImageSourceES3);
5448 m_areWebGL2TexImageSourceFormatsAndTypesAdded = true;
5449 }
5450
5451 if (!isWebGL2())
5452 addExtensionSupportedFormatsAndTypes();
5453 else
5454 addExtensionSupportedFormatsAndTypesWebGL2();
5455
5456 if (internalformat && !m_supportedTexImageSourceInternalFormats.contains(internalformat)) {
5457 if (functionType == TexImageFunctionType::TexImage)
5458 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid internalformat");
5459 else
5460 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid internalformat");
5461 return false;
5462 }
5463 if (!m_supportedTexImageSourceFormats.contains(format)) {
5464 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid format");
5465 return false;
5466 }
5467 if (!m_supportedTexImageSourceTypes.contains(type)) {
5468 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid type");
5469 return false;
5470 }
5471
5472 return true;
5473}
5474
5475bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexFuncFormatAndType(const char* functionName, GCGLenum internalFormat, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, GCGLint level)
5476{
5477 switch (format) {
5478 case GraphicsContextGL::ALPHA:
5479 case GraphicsContextGL::LUMINANCE:
5480 case GraphicsContextGL::LUMINANCE_ALPHA:
5481 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB:
5482 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA:
5483 break;
5484 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL:
5485 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_COMPONENT:
5486 if (!m_webglDepthTexture && isWebGL1()) {
5487 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "depth texture formats not enabled");
5488 return false;
5489 }
5490 if (level > 0 && isWebGL1()) {
5491 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "level must be 0 for depth formats");
5492 return false;
5493 }
5494 break;
5495 case ExtensionsGL::SRGB_EXT:
5496 case ExtensionsGL::SRGB_ALPHA_EXT:
5497 if (!m_extsRGB) {
5498 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "sRGB texture formats not enabled");
5499 return false;
5500 }
5501 break;
5502 default:
5503#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
5504 if (!isWebGL1()) {
5505 switch (format) {
5506 case GraphicsContextGL::RED:
5507 case GraphicsContextGL::RED_INTEGER:
5508 case GraphicsContextGL::RG:
5509 case GraphicsContextGL::RG_INTEGER:
5510 case GraphicsContextGL::RGB_INTEGER:
5511 case GraphicsContextGL::RGBA_INTEGER:
5512 break;
5513 default:
5514 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture format");
5515 return false;
5516 }
5517 } else
5518#endif
5519 {
5520 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture format");
5521 return false;
5522 }
5523 }
5524
5525 switch (type) {
5526 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
5527 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5:
5528 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4:
5529 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1:
5530 break;
5531 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
5532 if (!m_oesTextureFloat && isWebGL1()) {
5533 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture type");
5534 return false;
5535 }
5536 break;
5537 case GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT:
5538 case GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT_OES:
5539 if (!m_oesTextureHalfFloat && isWebGL1()) {
5540 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture type");
5541 return false;
5542 }
5543 break;
5544 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
5545 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_24_8:
5546 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
5547 if (!m_webglDepthTexture && isWebGL1()) {
5548 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture type");
5549 return false;
5550 }
5551 break;
5552 default:
5553#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
5554 if (!isWebGL1()) {
5555 switch (type) {
5556 case GraphicsContextGL::BYTE:
5557 case GraphicsContextGL::SHORT:
5558 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
5559 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
5560 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV:
5561 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_5_9_9_9_REV:
5562 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_32_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_REV:
5563 break;
5564 default:
5565 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture type");
5566 return false;
5567 }
5568 } else
5569#endif
5570 {
5571 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture type");
5572 return false;
5573 }
5574 }
5575
5576#if USE(ANGLE)
5577 UNUSED_PARAM(internalFormat);
5578#else
5579 // Verify that the combination of internalformat, format, and type is supported.
5580#define INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(internalFormatMacro, formatMacro, type0, type1, type2, type3, type4) case GraphicsContextGL::internalFormatMacro: \
5581 if (format != GraphicsContextGL::formatMacro) { \
5582 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "invalid format for internalformat"); \
5583 return false; \
5584 } \
5585 if (type != type0 && type != type1 && type != type2 && type != type3 && type != type4) { \
5586 if (type != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT_OES || (type0 != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT && type1 != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT && type2 != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT && type3 != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT)) { \
5587 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "invalid type for internalformat"); \
5588 return false; \
5589 } \
5590 } \
5591 break;
5592 switch (internalFormat) {
5593 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5 , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 );
5594 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1 , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT, GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT);
5595 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(LUMINANCE_ALPHA , LUMINANCE_ALPHA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 );
5596 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(LUMINANCE , LUMINANCE , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 );
5597 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(ALPHA , ALPHA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 );
5598 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R8 , RED , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5599 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R8_SNORM , RED , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5600 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R16F , RED , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5601 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R32F , RED , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5602 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R8UI , RED_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5603 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R8I , RED_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5604 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R16UI , RED_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5605 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R16I , RED_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5606 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R32UI , RED_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5607 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R32I , RED_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5608 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG8 , RG , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5609 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG8_SNORM , RG , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5610 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG16F , RG , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5611 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG32F , RG , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5612 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG8UI , RG_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5613 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG8I , RG_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5614 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG16UI , RG_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5615 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG16I , RG_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5616 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG32UI , RG_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5617 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RG32I , RG_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5618 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB8 , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5619 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(SRGB8 , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5620 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB565 , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5621 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB8_SNORM , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5622 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(R11F_G11F_B10F , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_10F_11F_11F_REV , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 );
5623 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB9_E5 , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_5_9_9_9_REV , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 );
5624 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB16F , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5625 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB32F , RGB , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5626 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB8UI , RGB_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5627 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB8I , RGB_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5628 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB16UI , RGB_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5629 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB16I , RGB_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5630 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB32UI , RGB_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5631 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB32I , RGB_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5632 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA8 , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5633 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(SRGB8_ALPHA8 , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5634 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA8_SNORM , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5635 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB5_A1 , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV , 0 , 0 );
5636 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA4 , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4, 0 , 0 , 0 );
5637 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB10_A2 , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5638 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA16F , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5639 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA32F , RGBA , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5640 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA8UI , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5641 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA8I , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::BYTE , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5642 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGB10_A2UI , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5643 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA16UI , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5644 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA16I , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::SHORT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5645 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA32I , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5646 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(RGBA32UI , RGBA_INTEGER , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5647 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH_COMPONENT , DEPTH_COMPONENT, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5648 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH_COMPONENT16 , DEPTH_COMPONENT, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5649 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH_COMPONENT24 , DEPTH_COMPONENT, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5650 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH_COMPONENT32F, DEPTH_COMPONENT, GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5651 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH_STENCIL , DEPTH_STENCIL , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_24_8 , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5652 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH24_STENCIL8 , DEPTH_STENCIL , GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_24_8 , 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5653 INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE(DEPTH32F_STENCIL8 , DEPTH_STENCIL , GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT_32_UNSIGNED_INT_24_8_REV, 0 , 0 , 0 , 0 );
5654 case ExtensionsGL::SRGB_EXT:
5655 if (format != internalFormat) {
5656 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "format and internalformat must match");
5657 return false;
5658 }
5659 if (type != GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE && type != GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_6_5 && type != GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT && type != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT_OES && type != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT) {
5660 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "invalid type for internal format");
5661 return false;
5662 }
5663 break;
5664 case ExtensionsGL::SRGB_ALPHA_EXT:
5665 if (format != internalFormat) {
5666 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "format and internalformat must match");
5667 return false;
5668 }
5669 if (type != GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE && type != GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_4_4_4_4 && type != GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT_5_5_5_1 && type != GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT && type != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT_OES && type != GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT) {
5670 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "invalid type for internal format");
5671 return false;
5672 }
5673 break;
5674 default:
5675 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "Unknown internal format");
5676 return false;
5677 }
5678#undef INTERNAL_FORMAT_CASE
5679
5680#endif // USE(ANGLE)
5681 return true;
5682}
5683
5684void WebGLRenderingContextBase::copyTexImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalFormat, GCGLint x, GCGLint y, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLint border)
5685{
5686 if (isContextLostOrPending())
5687 return;
5688#if !USE(ANGLE)
5689 // Fake the source so that simple validation of the format/type is done. This is subsumed by ANGLE.
5690 if (!validateTexFuncParameters("copyTexImage2D", TexImageFunctionType::CopyTexImage, TexFuncValidationSourceType::SourceArrayBufferView, target, level, internalFormat, width, height, 1, border, internalFormat, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE))
5691 return;
5692#endif
5693 if (!validateSettableTexInternalFormat("copyTexImage2D", internalFormat))
5694 return;
5695 auto tex = validateTexture2DBinding("copyTexImage2D", target);
5696 if (!tex)
5697 return;
5698#if USE(ANGLE)
5699 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
5700 m_context->copyTexImage2D(target, level, internalFormat, x, y, width, height, border);
5701#else
5702 if (!isTexInternalFormatColorBufferCombinationValid(internalFormat, getBoundReadFramebufferColorFormat())) {
5703 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "copyTexImage2D", "framebuffer is incompatible format");
5704 return;
5705 }
5706 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict() && level && WebGLTexture::isNPOT(width, height)) {
5707 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "copyTexImage2D", "level > 0 not power of 2");
5708 return;
5709 }
5710 const char* reason = "framebuffer incomplete";
5711 if (getReadFramebufferBinding() && !getReadFramebufferBinding()->onAccess(graphicsContextGL(), &reason)) {
5712 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION, "copyTexImage2D", reason);
5713 return;
5714 }
5715 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerOther);
5716
5717 GCGLint clippedX, clippedY;
5718 GCGLsizei clippedWidth, clippedHeight;
5719 if (clip2D(x, y, width, height, getBoundReadFramebufferWidth(), getBoundReadFramebufferHeight(), &clippedX, &clippedY, &clippedWidth, &clippedHeight)) {
5720 static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->texImage2DResourceSafe(target, level, internalFormat, width, height, border,
5721 internalFormat, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, m_unpackAlignment);
5722 if (clippedWidth > 0 && clippedHeight > 0) {
5723 m_context->copyTexSubImage2D(target, level, clippedX - x, clippedY - y,
5724 clippedX, clippedY, clippedWidth, clippedHeight);
5725 }
5726 } else
5727 m_context->copyTexImage2D(target, level, internalFormat, x, y, width, height, border);
5728
5729 // FIXME: if the framebuffer is not complete, none of the below should be executed.
5730 tex->setLevelInfo(target, level, internalFormat, width, height, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE);
5731#endif
5732}
5733
5734ExceptionOr<void> WebGLRenderingContextBase::texImage2D(GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLenum internalformat, GCGLenum format, GCGLenum type, std::optional<TexImageSource> source)
5735{
5736 if (isContextLostOrPending())
5737 return { };
5738
5739 if (!source) {
5740 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "texImage2D", "source is null");
5741 return { };
5742 }
5743
5744 return texImageSourceHelper(TexImageFunctionID::TexImage2D, target, level, internalformat, 0, format, type, 0, 0, 0, sentinelEmptyRect(), 1, 0, WTFMove(*source));
5745}
5746
5747RefPtr<Image> WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawImageIntoBuffer(Image& image, int width, int height, int deviceScaleFactor, const char* functionName)
5748{
5749 IntSize size(width, height);
5750 size.scale(deviceScaleFactor);
5751 ImageBuffer* buf = m_generatedImageCache.imageBuffer(size);
5752 if (!buf) {
5753 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::OUT_OF_MEMORY, functionName, "out of memory");
5754 return nullptr;
5755 }
5756
5757 FloatRect srcRect(FloatPoint(), image.size());
5758 FloatRect destRect(FloatPoint(), size);
5759 buf->context().drawImage(image, destRect, srcRect);
5760 return buf->copyImage(DontCopyBackingStore);
5761}
5762
5763#if ENABLE(VIDEO)
5764
5765RefPtr<Image> WebGLRenderingContextBase::videoFrameToImage(HTMLVideoElement* video, BackingStoreCopy backingStoreCopy)
5766{
5767 IntSize size(video->videoWidth(), video->videoHeight());
5768 ImageBuffer* buf = m_generatedImageCache.imageBuffer(size);
5769 if (!buf) {
5770 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::OUT_OF_MEMORY, "texImage2D", "out of memory");
5771 return nullptr;
5772 }
5773 FloatRect destRect(0, 0, size.width(), size.height());
5774 // FIXME: Turn this into a GPU-GPU texture copy instead of CPU readback.
5775 video->paintCurrentFrameInContext(buf->context(), destRect);
5776 return buf->copyImage(backingStoreCopy);
5777}

5779#endif
5780
5781void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texParameter(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname, GCGLfloat paramf, GCGLint parami, bool isFloat)
5782{
5783 if (isContextLostOrPending())
5784 return;
5785 auto tex = validateTextureBinding("texParameter", target);
5786 if (!tex)
5787 return;
5788 switch (pname) {
5789 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
5790 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
5791 break;
5792 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
5793 if (!isWebGL2()) {
5794 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "texParameter", "invalid parameter name");
5795 return;
5796 }
5797 FALLTHROUGH;
5798 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
5799 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
5800 if ((isFloat && paramf != GraphicsContextGL::CLAMP_TO_EDGE && paramf != GraphicsContextGL::MIRRORED_REPEAT && paramf != GraphicsContextGL::REPEAT)
5801 || (!isFloat && parami != GraphicsContextGL::CLAMP_TO_EDGE && parami != GraphicsContextGL::MIRRORED_REPEAT && parami != GraphicsContextGL::REPEAT)) {
5802 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "texParameter", "invalid parameter");
5803 return;
5804 }
5805 break;
5806 case ExtensionsGL::TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT: // EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic
5807 if (!m_extTextureFilterAnisotropic) {
5808 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "texParameter", "invalid parameter, EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic not enabled");
5809 return;
5810 }
5811 break;
5812 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
5813 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
5814 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_BASE_LEVEL:
5815 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MAX_LEVEL:
5816 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
5817 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
5818 if (!isWebGL2()) {
5819 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "texParameter", "invalid parameter name");
5820 return;
5821 }
5822 break;
5823 default:
5824 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "texParameter", "invalid parameter name");
5825 return;
5826 }
5827 if (isFloat) {
5828#if !USE(ANGLE)
5829 tex->setParameterf(pname, paramf);
5830#endif
5831 m_context->texParameterf(target, pname, paramf);
5832 } else {
5833#if !USE(ANGLE)
5834 tex->setParameteri(pname, parami);
5835#endif
5836 m_context->texParameteri(target, pname, parami);
5837 }
5838}
5839
5840void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texParameterf(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname, GCGLfloat param)
5841{
5842 texParameter(target, pname, param, 0, true);
5843}
5844
5845void WebGLRenderingContextBase::texParameteri(GCGLenum target, GCGLenum pname, GCGLint param)
5846{
5847 texParameter(target, pname, 0, param, false);
5848}
5849
5850bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateUniformLocation(const char* functionName, const WebGLUniformLocation* location)
5851{
5852 if (!location)
5853 return false;
5854 if (location->program() != m_currentProgram) {
5855 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "location not for current program");
5856 return false;
5857 }
5858 return true;
5859}

5864 return;
5865
5866 m_context->uniform1f(location->location(), x);
5867}

5884
5885void WebGLRenderingContextBase::uniform4f(const WebGLUniformLocation* location, GCGLfloat x, GCGLfloat y, GCGLfloat z, GCGLfloat w)
5886{
5887 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateUniformLocation("uniform4f", location))
5888 return;
5889
5890 m_context->uniform4f(location->location(), x, y, z, w);
5891}
5892
5893void WebGLRenderingContextBase::uniform1i(const WebGLUniformLocation* location, GCGLint x)
5894{
5895 if (isContextLostOrPending() || !validateUniformLocation("uniform1i", location))
5896 return;
5897
5898 if ((location->type() == GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_2D || location->type() == GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_CUBE) && x >= (int)m_textureUnits.size()) {
5899 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "uniform1i", "invalid texture unit");
5900 return;
5901 }
5902
5903 m_context->uniform1i(location->location(), x);
5904}

5970void WebGLRenderingContextBase::uniform1iv(const WebGLUniformLocation* location, Int32List&& v)
5971{
5972 if (isContextLostOrPending())
5973 return;
5974 auto result = validateUniformParameters("uniform1iv", location, v, 1);
5975 if (!result)
5976 return;
5977
5978 auto data = result.value();
5979
5980 if (location->type() == GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_2D || location->type() == GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLER_CUBE) {
5981 for (size_t i = 0; i < data.bufSize; ++i) {
5982 if (data[i] >= static_cast<int>(m_textureUnits.size())) {
5983 LOG(WebGL, "Texture unit size=%zu, v[%zu]=%d. Location type = %04X.", m_textureUnits.size(), i, data[i], location->type());
5984 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "uniform1iv", "invalid texture unit");
5985 return;
5986 }
5987 }
5988 }
5989
5990 m_context->uniform1iv(location->location(), data);
5991}

6053void WebGLRenderingContextBase::useProgram(WebGLProgram* program)
6054{
6055 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
6056
6057 if (!validateNullableWebGLObject("useProgram", program))
6058 return;
6059 if (program && !program->getLinkStatus()) {
6060 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "useProgram", "program not valid");
6061 return;
6062 }
6063 if (m_currentProgram != program) {
6064 if (m_currentProgram)
6065 m_currentProgram->onDetached(locker, graphicsContextGL());
6066 m_currentProgram = program;
6067 m_context->useProgram(objectOrZero(program));
6068 if (program)
6069 program->onAttached();
6070 }
6071}
6072

6074{
6075 if (!validateWebGLProgramOrShader("validateProgram", &program))
6076 return;
6077 m_context->validateProgram(program.object());
6078}

6119
6120void WebGLRenderingContextBase::vertexAttribPointer(GCGLuint index, GCGLint size, GCGLenum type, GCGLboolean normalized, GCGLsizei stride, long long offset)
6121{
6122 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
6123
6124 if (isContextLostOrPending())
6125 return;
6126 switch (type) {
6127 case GraphicsContextGL::BYTE:
6128 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE:
6129 case GraphicsContextGL::SHORT:
6130 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_SHORT:
6131 case GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT:
6132 break;
6133 default:
6134 if (!isWebGL2()) {
6135 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "vertexAttribPointer", "invalid type");
6136 return;
6137 }
6138 switch (type) {
6139 case GraphicsContextGL::INT:
6140 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT:
6141 case GraphicsContextGL::HALF_FLOAT:
6142 break;
6143 case GraphicsContextGL::INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
6144 case GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_INT_2_10_10_10_REV:
6145 if (size != 4) {
6146 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "vertexAttribPointer", "[UNSIGNED_]INT_2_10_10_10_REV requires size 4");
6147 return;
6148 }
6149 break;
6150 default:
6151 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "vertexAttribPointer", "invalid type");
6152 return;
6153 }
6154 }
6155 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
6156 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribPointer", "index out of range");
6157 return;
6158 }
6159 if (size < 1 || size > 4) {
6160 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribPointer", "bad size");
6161 return;
6162 }
6163 if (stride < 0 || stride > 255) {
6164 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribPointer", "bad stride");
6165 return;
6166 }
6167 if (offset < 0 || offset > std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::max()) {
6168 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribPointer", "bad offset");
6169 return;
6170 }
6171 if (!m_boundArrayBuffer && offset) {
6172 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "vertexAttribPointer", "no bound ARRAY_BUFFER");
6173 return;
6174 }
6175 // Determine the number of elements the bound buffer can hold, given the offset, size, type and stride
6176 auto typeSize = sizeInBytes(type);
6177 if (!typeSize) {
6178 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, "vertexAttribPointer", "invalid type");
6179 return;
6180 }
6181 if ((stride % typeSize) || (static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset) % typeSize)) {
6182 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "vertexAttribPointer", "stride or offset not valid for type");
6183 return;
6184 }
6185 GCGLsizei bytesPerElement = size * typeSize;
6186
6187 m_boundVertexArrayObject->setVertexAttribState(locker, index, bytesPerElement, size, type, normalized, stride, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), false, m_boundArrayBuffer.get());
6188 m_context->vertexAttribPointer(index, size, type, normalized, stride, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset));
6189}

6192{
6193 if (isContextLostOrPending())

6196 return;
6197 m_context->viewport(x, y, width, height);
6198}
6199
6200void WebGLRenderingContextBase::forceLostContext(WebGLRenderingContextBase::LostContextMode mode)
6201{
6202 if (isContextLostOrPending()) {
6203 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "loseContext", "context already lost");
6204 return;
6205 }
6206
6207 m_contextGroup->loseContextGroup(mode);
6208}
6209
6210void WebGLRenderingContextBase::loseContextImpl(WebGLRenderingContextBase::LostContextMode mode)
6211{
6212 if (isContextLost())
6213 return;
6214
6215 m_contextLost = true;
6216 m_contextLostMode = mode;
6217
6218 if (mode == RealLostContext) {
6219 // Inform the embedder that a lost context was received. In response, the embedder might
6220 // decide to take action such as asking the user for permission to use WebGL again.
6221 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
6222 if (canvas) {
6223 if (RefPtr<Frame> frame = canvas->document().frame())
6224 frame->loader().client().didLoseWebGLContext(m_context->getExtensions().getGraphicsResetStatusARB());
6225 }
6226 }
6227
6228 detachAndRemoveAllObjects();
6229 loseExtensions(mode);
6230
6231 // There is no direct way to clear errors from a GL implementation and
6232 // looping until getError() becomes NO_ERROR might cause an infinite loop if
6233 // the driver or context implementation had a bug. So, loop a reasonably
6234 // large number of times to clear any existing errors.
6235 for (int i = 0; i < 100; ++i) {
6236 if (m_context->getError() == GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR)
6237 break;
6238 }
6239 ConsoleDisplayPreference display = (mode == RealLostContext) ? DisplayInConsole: DontDisplayInConsole;
6240 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::CONTEXT_LOST_WEBGL, "loseContext", "context lost", display);
6241
6242 // Don't allow restoration unless the context lost event has both been
6243 // dispatched and its default behavior prevented.
6244 m_restoreAllowed = false;
6245
6246 // Always defer the dispatch of the context lost event, to implement
6247 // the spec behavior of queueing a task.
6248 scheduleTaskToDispatchContextLostEvent();
6249}
6250
6251void WebGLRenderingContextBase::forceRestoreContext()
6252{
6253 if (!isContextLostOrPending()) {
6254 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "restoreContext", "context not lost");
6255 return;
6256 }
6257
6258 if (!m_restoreAllowed) {
6259 if (m_contextLostMode == SyntheticLostContext)
6260 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "restoreContext", "context restoration not allowed");
6261 return;
6262 }
6263
6264 if (!m_restoreTimer.isActive())
6265 m_restoreTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
6266}
6267
6268bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::isContextUnrecoverablyLost() const
6269{
6270 return m_contextLost && !m_restoreAllowed;
6271}
6272
6273PlatformLayer* WebGLRenderingContextBase::platformLayer() const
6274{
6275 return (!isContextLost() && !m_isPendingPolicyResolution) ? m_context->platformLayer() : 0;
6276}

6312void WebGLRenderingContextBase::detachAndRemoveAllObjects()
6313{
6314 if (m_isPendingPolicyResolution)
6315 return;
6316
6317 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
6318
6319 while (m_contextObjects.size() > 0) {
6320 HashSet<WebGLContextObject*>::iterator it = m_contextObjects.begin();
6321 (*it)->detachContext(locker);
6322 }
6323}

6326{

6328 forceLostContext(SyntheticLostContext);
6329 destroyGraphicsContextGL();
6330 }
6331}

6382RefPtr<Float32Array> WebGLRenderingContextBase::getWebGLFloatArrayParameter(GCGLenum pname)

6389 case GraphicsContextGL::ALIASED_LINE_WIDTH_RANGE:
