6436
6437#if !USE(ANGLE)
6438bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::checkTextureCompleteness(const char* functionName, bool prepareToDraw)
6439{
6440 bool resetActiveUnit = false;
6441 bool usesAtLeastOneBlackTexture = false;
6442 WebGLTexture::TextureExtensionFlag extensions = textureExtensionFlags();
6443
6444 Vector<unsigned> noLongerUnrenderable;
6445 for (unsigned badTexture : m_unrenderableTextureUnits) {
6446 ASSERT(badTexture < m_textureUnits.size());
6447 auto& textureUnit = m_textureUnits[badTexture];
6448 bool needsToUseBlack2DTexture = textureUnit.texture2DBinding && textureUnit.texture2DBinding->needToUseBlackTexture(extensions);
6449 bool needsToUseBlack3DTexture = textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding && textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding->needToUseBlackTexture(extensions);
6450
6451 if (!needsToUseBlack2DTexture && !needsToUseBlack3DTexture) {
6452 noLongerUnrenderable.append(badTexture);
6453 continue;
6454 }
6455
6456 usesAtLeastOneBlackTexture = true;
6457
6458 if (badTexture != m_activeTextureUnit) {
6459 m_context->activeTexture(badTexture + GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE0);
6460 resetActiveUnit = true;
6461 } else if (resetActiveUnit) {
6462 m_context->activeTexture(badTexture + GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE0);
6463 resetActiveUnit = false;
6464 }
6465 RefPtr<WebGLTexture> tex2D;
6466 RefPtr<WebGLTexture> texCubeMap;
6467 if (prepareToDraw) {
6468 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Error, makeString("WebGL: ", functionName, ": texture bound to texture unit ", badTexture,
6469 " is not renderable. It maybe non-power-of-2 and have incompatible texture filtering or is not 'texture complete',"
6470 " or it is a float/half-float type with linear filtering and without the relevant float/half-float linear extension enabled."));
6471 tex2D = m_blackTexture2D.get();
6472 texCubeMap = m_blackTextureCubeMap.get();
6473 } else {
6474 tex2D = textureUnit.texture2DBinding.get();
6475 texCubeMap = textureUnit.textureCubeMapBinding.get();
6476 }
6477 if (needsToUseBlack2DTexture)
6478 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D, objectOrZero(tex2D.get()));
6479 if (needsToUseBlack3DTexture)
6480 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP, objectOrZero(texCubeMap.get()));
6481 }
6482 if (resetActiveUnit)
6483 m_context->activeTexture(m_activeTextureUnit + GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE0);
6484
6485 for (unsigned renderable : noLongerUnrenderable)
6486 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.remove(renderable);
6487
6488 return usesAtLeastOneBlackTexture;
6489}
6490
6491void WebGLRenderingContextBase::createFallbackBlackTextures1x1()
6492{
6493 unsigned char black[] = {0, 0, 0, 255};
6494 m_blackTexture2D = createTexture();
6495 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D, m_blackTexture2D->object());
6496 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6497 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6498 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D, 0);
6499 m_blackTextureCubeMap = createTexture();
6500 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP, m_blackTextureCubeMap->object());
6501 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6502 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6503 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6504 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6505 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6506 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6507 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6508 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6509 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6510 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6511 m_context->texImage2D(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z, 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, 1, 1,
6512 0, GraphicsContextGL::RGBA, GraphicsContextGL::UNSIGNED_BYTE, black);
6513 m_context->bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP, 0);
6514}
6515
6516bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::isTexInternalFormatColorBufferCombinationValid(GCGLenum texInternalFormat, GCGLenum colorBufferFormat)
6517{
6518 auto need = GraphicsContextGL::getChannelBitsByFormat(texInternalFormat);
6519 auto have = GraphicsContextGL::getChannelBitsByFormat(colorBufferFormat);
6520 return (need & have) == need;
6521}
6522
6523GCGLenum WebGLRenderingContextBase::getBoundReadFramebufferColorFormat()
6524{
6525 WebGLFramebuffer* framebuffer = getReadFramebufferBinding();
6526 if (framebuffer && framebuffer->object())
6527 return framebuffer->getColorBufferFormat();
6528 if (m_attributes.alpha)
6529 return GraphicsContextGL::RGBA;
6530 return GraphicsContextGL::RGB;
6531}
6532
6533int WebGLRenderingContextBase::getBoundReadFramebufferWidth()
6534{
6535 WebGLFramebuffer* framebuffer = getReadFramebufferBinding();
6536 if (framebuffer && framebuffer->object())
6537 return framebuffer->getColorBufferWidth();
6538 return m_context->getInternalFramebufferSize().width();
6539}
6540
6541int WebGLRenderingContextBase::getBoundReadFramebufferHeight()
6542{
6543 WebGLFramebuffer* framebuffer = getReadFramebufferBinding();
6544 if (framebuffer && framebuffer->object())
6545 return framebuffer->getColorBufferHeight();
6546 return m_context->getInternalFramebufferSize().height();
6547}
6548#endif // USE(ANGLE)
6549
6550RefPtr<WebGLTexture> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTextureBinding(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
6551{
6552 RefPtr<WebGLTexture> texture;
6553 switch (target) {
6554 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D:
6555 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture2DBinding;
6556 break;
6557 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP:
6558 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].textureCubeMapBinding;
6559 break;
6560 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_3D:
6561 if (!isWebGL2()) {
6562 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture target");
6563 return nullptr;
6564 }
6565 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture3DBinding;
6566 break;
6567 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY:
6568 if (!isWebGL2()) {
6569 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture target");
6570 return nullptr;
6571 }
6572 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture2DArrayBinding;
6573 break;
6574 default:
6575 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture target");
6576 return nullptr;
6577 }
6578
6579#if !USE(ANGLE)
6580 if (texture && texture->needToUseBlackTexture(textureExtensionFlags()))
6581 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(m_activeTextureUnit);
6582#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
6583
6584 if (!texture)
6585 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no texture");
6586 return texture;
6587}
6588
6589RefPtr<WebGLTexture> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexImageBinding(const char* functionName, TexImageFunctionID functionID, GCGLenum target)
6590{
6591 UNUSED_PARAM(functionID);
6592 return validateTexture2DBinding(functionName, target);
6593}
6594
6595RefPtr<WebGLTexture> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexture2DBinding(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target)
6596{
6597 RefPtr<WebGLTexture> texture;
6598 switch (target) {
6599 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D:
6600 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture2DBinding;
6601 break;
6602 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X:
6603 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X:
6604 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y:
6605 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y:
6606 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z:
6607 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z:
6608 texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].textureCubeMapBinding;
6609 break;
6610 default:
6611 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid texture target");
6612 return nullptr;
6613 }
6614
6615#if !USE(ANGLE)
6616 if (texture && texture->needToUseBlackTexture(textureExtensionFlags()))
6617 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(m_activeTextureUnit);
6618#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
6619
6620 if (!texture)
6621 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "no texture");
6622 return texture;
6623}
6624
6625bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateLocationLength(const char* functionName, const String& string)
6626{
6627 unsigned maxWebGLLocationLength = isWebGL2() ? 1024 : 256;
6628 if (string.length() > maxWebGLLocationLength) {
6629 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "location length is too large");
6630 return false;
6631 }
6632 return true;
6633}
6634
6635bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateSize(const char* functionName, GCGLint x, GCGLint y, GCGLint z)
6636{
6637 if (x < 0 || y < 0 || z < 0) {
6638 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "size < 0");
6639 return false;
6640 }
6641 return true;
6642}
6643
6644bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateString(const char* functionName, const String& string)
6645{
6646 for (size_t i = 0; i < string.length(); ++i) {
6647 if (!validateCharacter(string[i])) {
6648 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "string not ASCII");
6649 return false;
6650 }
6651 }
6652 return true;
6653}
6654
6655bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateTexFuncLevel(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level)
6656{
6657 if (level < 0) {
6658 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "level < 0");
6659 return false;
6660 }
6661 GCGLint maxLevel = maxTextureLevelForTarget(target);
6662 if (maxLevel && level >= maxLevel) {
6663 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "level out of range");
6664 return false;
6665 }
6666 // This function only checks if level is legal, so we return true and don't
6667 // generate INVALID_ENUM if target is illegal.
6668 return true;
6669}
6670
6671GCGLint WebGLRenderingContextBase::maxTextureLevelForTarget(GCGLenum target)
6672{
6673 switch (target) {
6674 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D:
6675 return m_maxTextureLevel;
6676 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_X:
6677 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_X:
6678 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Y:
6679 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Y:
6680 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_POSITIVE_Z:
6681 case GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_NEGATIVE_Z:
6682 return m_maxCubeMapTextureLevel;
6683 }
6684 return 0;
6685}
6686
6687#if !USE(ANGLE)
6688bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateCompressedTexFormat(GCGLenum format)
6689{
6690 return m_compressedTextureFormats.contains(format);
6691}
6692
6693struct BlockParameters {
6694 const int width;
6695 const int height;
6696 const int size;
6697};
6698
6699static inline unsigned calculateBytesForASTC(GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, const BlockParameters& parameters)
6700{
6701 return ((width + parameters.width - 1) / parameters.width) * ((height + parameters.height - 1) / parameters.height) * parameters.size;
6702}
6703
6704bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateCompressedTexFuncData(const char* functionName, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format, ArrayBufferView& pixels)
6705{
6706 if (width < 0 || height < 0) {
6707 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "width or height < 0");
6708 return false;
6709 }
6710
6711 unsigned bytesRequired = 0;
6712
6713 // Block parameters for ASTC formats
6714 const int kASTCBlockSize = 16;
6715 static const BlockParameters ASTCParameters[] {
6716 BlockParameters { 4, 4, kASTCBlockSize },
6717 BlockParameters { 5, 4, kASTCBlockSize },
6718 BlockParameters { 5, 5, kASTCBlockSize },
6719 BlockParameters { 6, 5, kASTCBlockSize },
6720 BlockParameters { 6, 6, kASTCBlockSize },
6721 BlockParameters { 8, 5, kASTCBlockSize },
6722 BlockParameters { 8, 6, kASTCBlockSize },
6723 BlockParameters { 8, 8, kASTCBlockSize },
6724 BlockParameters { 10, 5, kASTCBlockSize },
6725 BlockParameters { 10, 6, kASTCBlockSize },
6726 BlockParameters { 10, 8, kASTCBlockSize },
6727 BlockParameters { 10, 10, kASTCBlockSize },
6728 BlockParameters { 12, 10, kASTCBlockSize },
6729 BlockParameters { 12, 12, kASTCBlockSize }
6730 };
6731 const GCGLenum ASTCEnumStartRGBA = ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_4x4_KHR;
6732 const GCGLenum ASTCEnumStartSRGB8 = ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_4x4_KHR;
6733
6734 const int kEACAndETC2BlockSize = 4;
6735
6736 switch (format) {
6737 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6738 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6739 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6740 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6741 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_ATC_RGB_AMD:
6742 case ExtensionsGL::ETC1_RGB8_OES: {
6743 const int kBlockSize = 8;
6744 const int kBlockWidth = 4;
6745 const int kBlockHeight = 4;
6746 int numBlocksAcross = (width + kBlockWidth - 1) / kBlockWidth;
6747 int numBlocksDown = (height + kBlockHeight - 1) / kBlockHeight;
6748 bytesRequired = numBlocksAcross * numBlocksDown * kBlockSize;
6749 break;
6750 }
6751 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
6752 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT:
6753 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
6754 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT:
6755 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_ATC_RGBA_EXPLICIT_ALPHA_AMD:
6756 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_ATC_RGBA_INTERPOLATED_ALPHA_AMD:
6757 {
6758 const int kBlockSize = 16;
6759 const int kBlockWidth = 4;
6760 const int kBlockHeight = 4;
6761 int numBlocksAcross = (width + kBlockWidth - 1) / kBlockWidth;
6762 int numBlocksDown = (height + kBlockHeight - 1) / kBlockHeight;
6763 bytesRequired = numBlocksAcross * numBlocksDown * kBlockSize;
6764 }
6765 break;
6766 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
6767 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
6768 {
6769 const int kBlockSize = 8;
6770 const int kBlockWidth = 8;
6771 const int kBlockHeight = 8;
6772 bytesRequired = (std::max(width, kBlockWidth) * std::max(height, kBlockHeight) * 4 + 7) / kBlockSize;
6773 }
6774 break;
6775 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
6776 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
6777 {
6778 const int kBlockSize = 8;
6779 const int kBlockWidth = 16;
6780 const int kBlockHeight = 8;
6781 bytesRequired = (std::max(width, kBlockWidth) * std::max(height, kBlockHeight) * 2 + 7) / kBlockSize;
6782 }
6783 break;
6784 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_4x4_KHR:
6785 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_5x4_KHR:
6786 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_5x5_KHR:
6787 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_6x5_KHR:
6788 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_6x6_KHR:
6789 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_8x5_KHR:
6790 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_8x6_KHR:
6791 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_8x8_KHR:
6792 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x5_KHR:
6793 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x6_KHR:
6794 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x8_KHR:
6795 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x10_KHR:
6796 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_12x10_KHR:
6797 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_12x12_KHR:
6798 bytesRequired = calculateBytesForASTC(width, height, ASTCParameters[format - ASTCEnumStartRGBA]);
6799 break;
6800 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_4x4_KHR:
6801 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_5x4_KHR:
6802 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_5x5_KHR:
6803 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_6x5_KHR:
6804 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_6x6_KHR:
6805 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_8x5_KHR:
6806 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_8x6_KHR:
6807 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_8x8_KHR:
6808 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x5_KHR:
6809 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x6_KHR:
6810 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x8_KHR:
6811 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x10_KHR:
6812 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_12x10_KHR:
6813 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_12x12_KHR:
6814 bytesRequired = calculateBytesForASTC(width, height, ASTCParameters[format - ASTCEnumStartSRGB8]);
6815 break;
6816 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_R11_EAC:
6817 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC:
6818 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2:
6819 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ETC2:
6820 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2:
6821 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2: {
6822 CheckedUint32 checkedBytesRequired = (width + kEACAndETC2BlockSize - 1) / kEACAndETC2BlockSize;
6823 checkedBytesRequired *= (height + kEACAndETC2BlockSize - 1) / kEACAndETC2BlockSize;
6824 checkedBytesRequired *= 8;
6825 if (checkedBytesRequired.hasOverflowed()) {
6826 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "too large dimensions");
6827 return false;
6828 }
6829 bytesRequired = checkedBytesRequired;
6830 break;
6831 }
6832 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC:
6833 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC:
6834 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC:
6835 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ETC2_EAC: {
6836 CheckedUint32 checkedBytesRequired = (width + kEACAndETC2BlockSize - 1) / kEACAndETC2BlockSize;
6837 checkedBytesRequired *= (height + kEACAndETC2BlockSize - 1) / kEACAndETC2BlockSize;
6838 checkedBytesRequired *= 16;
6839 if (checkedBytesRequired.hasOverflowed()) {
6840 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "too large dimensions");
6841 return false;
6842 }
6843 bytesRequired = checkedBytesRequired;
6844 break;
6845 }
6846 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RED_RGTC1_EXT:
6847 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_RGTC1_EXT: {
6848 const int kBlockSize = 8;
6849 const int kBlockWidth = 4;
6850 const int kBlockHeight = 4;
6851 int numBlocksAcross = (width + kBlockWidth - 1) / kBlockWidth;
6852 int numBlocksDown = (height + kBlockHeight - 1) / kBlockHeight;
6853 bytesRequired = numBlocksAcross * numBlocksDown * kBlockSize;
6854 break;
6855 }
6856 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT:
6857 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RED_GREEN_RGTC2_EXT: {
6858 const int kBlockSize = 16;
6859 const int kBlockWidth = 4;
6860 const int kBlockHeight = 4;
6861 int numBlocksAcross = (width + kBlockWidth - 1) / kBlockWidth;
6862 int numBlocksDown = (height + kBlockHeight - 1) / kBlockHeight;
6863 bytesRequired = numBlocksAcross * numBlocksDown * kBlockSize;
6864 break;
6865 }
6866 default:
6867 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid format");
6868 return false;
6869 }
6870
6871 if (pixels.byteLength() != bytesRequired) {
6872 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "length of ArrayBufferView is not correct for dimensions");
6873 return false;
6874 }
6875
6876 return true;
6877}
6878
6879bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateCompressedTexDimensions(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format)
6880{
6881 switch (format) {
6882 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6883 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6884 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
6885 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT:
6886 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6887 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6888 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
6889 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT: {
6890 const GCGLsizei kBlockWidth = 4;
6891 const GCGLsizei kBlockHeight = 4;
6892 const GCGLint maxTextureSize = target ? m_maxTextureSize : m_maxCubeMapTextureSize;
6893 const GCGLsizei maxCompressedDimension = maxTextureSize >> level;
6894 bool widthValid = (level && width == 1) || (level && width == 2) || (!(width % kBlockWidth) && width <= maxCompressedDimension);
6895 bool heightValid = (level && height == 1) || (level && height == 2) || (!(height % kBlockHeight) && height <= maxCompressedDimension);
6896 if (!widthValid || !heightValid) {
6897 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "width or height invalid for level");
6898 return false;
6899 }
6900 return true;
6901 }
6902 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
6903 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
6904 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
6905 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
6906 // Height and width must be powers of 2.
6907 if ((width & (width - 1)) || (height & (height - 1))) {
6908 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "width or height invalid for level");
6909 return false;
6910 }
6911 return true;
6912 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_4x4_KHR:
6913 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_5x4_KHR:
6914 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_5x5_KHR:
6915 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_6x5_KHR:
6916 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_6x6_KHR:
6917 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_8x5_KHR:
6918 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_8x6_KHR:
6919 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_8x8_KHR:
6920 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x5_KHR:
6921 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x6_KHR:
6922 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x8_KHR:
6923 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_10x10_KHR:
6924 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_12x10_KHR:
6925 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_ASTC_12x12_KHR:
6926 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_4x4_KHR:
6927 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_5x4_KHR:
6928 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_5x5_KHR:
6929 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_6x5_KHR:
6930 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_6x6_KHR:
6931 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_8x5_KHR:
6932 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_8x6_KHR:
6933 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_8x8_KHR:
6934 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x5_KHR:
6935 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x6_KHR:
6936 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x8_KHR:
6937 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_10x10_KHR:
6938 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_12x10_KHR:
6939 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ASTC_12x12_KHR:
6940 case ExtensionsGL::ETC1_RGB8_OES:
6941 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_R11_EAC:
6942 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC:
6943 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC:
6944 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC:
6945 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2:
6946 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ETC2:
6947 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2:
6948 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2:
6949 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC:
6950 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ETC2_EAC:
6951 // No height and width restrictions on ASTC, ETC1 or ETC2.
6952 return true;
6953 default:
6954 return false;
6955 }
6956}
6957
6958bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateCompressedTexSubDimensions(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLint level, GCGLint xoffset, GCGLint yoffset, GCGLsizei width, GCGLsizei height, GCGLenum format, WebGLTexture* tex)
6959{
6960 if (xoffset < 0 || yoffset < 0) {
6961 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "xoffset or yoffset < 0");
6962 return false;
6963 }
6964
6965 switch (format) {
6966 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6967 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6968 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
6969 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT:
6970 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6971 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT1_EXT:
6972 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT3_EXT:
6973 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB_ALPHA_S3TC_DXT5_EXT: {
6974 const int kBlockWidth = 4;
6975 const int kBlockHeight = 4;
6976 if ((xoffset % kBlockWidth) || (yoffset % kBlockHeight)) {
6977 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "xoffset or yoffset not multiple of 4");
6978 return false;
6979 }
6980 if (width - xoffset > tex->getWidth(target, level)
6981 || height - yoffset > tex->getHeight(target, level)) {
6982 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "dimensions out of range");
6983 return false;
6984 }
6985 return validateCompressedTexDimensions(functionName, target, level, width, height, format);
6986 }
6987 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
6988 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG:
6989 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG:
6990 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG: {
6991 if (xoffset || yoffset) {
6992 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "xoffset and yoffset must be zero");
6993 return false;
6994 }
6995 if (width != tex->getWidth(target, level)
6996 || height != tex->getHeight(target, level)) {
6997 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "dimensions must match existing level");
6998 return false;
6999 }
7000 return validateCompressedTexDimensions(functionName, target, level, width, height, format);
7001 }
7002 case ExtensionsGL::ETC1_RGB8_OES:
7003 // Not supported for ETC1_RGB8_OES textures.
7004 return false;
7005 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_R11_EAC:
7006 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_R11_EAC:
7007 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RG11_EAC:
7008 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SIGNED_RG11_EAC:
7009 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB8_ETC2:
7010 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ETC2:
7011 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2:
7012 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_PUNCHTHROUGH_ALPHA1_ETC2:
7013 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_RGBA8_ETC2_EAC:
7014 case ExtensionsGL::COMPRESSED_SRGB8_ALPHA8_ETC2_EAC: {
7015 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_3D) {
7016 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "not supported on TEXTURE_3D textures");
7017 return false;
7018 }
7019 const int kBlockSize = 4;
7020 int texWidth = tex->getWidth(target, level);
7021 int texHeight = tex->getHeight(target, level);
7022 if ((xoffset % kBlockSize) || (yoffset % kBlockSize)
7023 || ((width % kBlockSize) && xoffset + width != texWidth)
7024 || ((height % kBlockSize) && yoffset + height != texHeight)) {
7025 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "dimensions must match existing texture level dimensions");
7026 return false;
7027 }
7028 return true;
7029 }
7030 default:
7031 return false;
7032 }
7033}
7034#endif // !USE(ANGLE)

7040 case GraphicsContextGL::LINE_STRIP:
7041 case GraphicsContextGL::LINE_LOOP:
7042 case GraphicsContextGL::LINES:
7043 case GraphicsContextGL::TRIANGLE_STRIP:
7044 case GraphicsContextGL::TRIANGLE_FAN:
7045 case GraphicsContextGL::TRIANGLES:
7046 return true;
7047 default:
7048 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid draw mode");
7049 return false;
7050 }
7051}

7053bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateStencilSettings(const char* functionName)
7054{
7055 if (m_stencilMask != m_stencilMaskBack || m_stencilFuncRef != m_stencilFuncRefBack || m_stencilFuncMask != m_stencilFuncMaskBack) {
7056 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "front and back stencils settings do not match");
7057 return false;
7058 }
7059 return true;

7069 case GraphicsContextGL::GEQUAL:
7070 case GraphicsContextGL::EQUAL:
7071 case GraphicsContextGL::NOTEQUAL:
7072 case GraphicsContextGL::ALWAYS:

7076 return false;

7079
7080void WebGLRenderingContextBase::printToConsole(MessageLevel level, const String& message)
7081{
7082 if (!m_synthesizedErrorsToConsole || !m_numGLErrorsToConsoleAllowed)
7083 return;
7084
7085 std::unique_ptr<Inspector::ConsoleMessage> consoleMessage;
7086
7087 // Error messages can occur during function calls, so show stack traces for them.
7088 if (level == MessageLevel::Error) {
7089 Ref<Inspector::ScriptCallStack> stackTrace = Inspector::createScriptCallStack(JSExecState::currentState());
7090 consoleMessage = makeUnique<Inspector::ConsoleMessage>(MessageSource::Rendering, MessageType::Log, level, message, WTFMove(stackTrace));
7091 } else
7092 consoleMessage = makeUnique<Inspector::ConsoleMessage>(MessageSource::Rendering, MessageType::Log, level, message);
7093
7094 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
7095 if (canvas)
7096 canvas->document().addConsoleMessage(WTFMove(consoleMessage));
7097
7098 --m_numGLErrorsToConsoleAllowed;
7099 if (!m_numGLErrorsToConsoleAllowed)
7100 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Warning, "WebGL: too many errors, no more errors will be reported to the console for this context.");
7101}

7121
7122bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateFramebufferFuncParameters(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLenum attachment)
7123{
7124 if (!validateFramebufferTarget(target)) {
7125 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid target");
7126 return false;
7127 }
7128 // This rejects attempts to set COLOR_ATTACHMENT > 0 if the functionality for multiple color
7129 // attachments is not enabled, either through the WEBGL_draw_buffers extension or availability
7130 // of WebGL 2.0.
7131 switch (attachment) {
7132 case GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0:
7133 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_ATTACHMENT:
7134 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
7135 case GraphicsContextGL::DEPTH_STENCIL_ATTACHMENT:
7136 return true;
7137 default:
7138 if ((m_webglDrawBuffers || isWebGL2())
7139 && attachment > GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0
7140 && attachment < static_cast<GCGLenum>(GraphicsContextGL::COLOR_ATTACHMENT0 + getMaxColorAttachments()))
7141 return true;
7142 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid attachment");
7143 return false;
7144 }
7145}
7146
7147bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateBlendFuncFactors(const char* functionName, GCGLenum src, GCGLenum dst)
7148{
7149 if (((src == GraphicsContextGL::CONSTANT_COLOR || src == GraphicsContextGL::ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_COLOR)
7150 && (dst == GraphicsContextGL::CONSTANT_ALPHA || dst == GraphicsContextGL::ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA))
7151 || ((dst == GraphicsContextGL::CONSTANT_COLOR || dst == GraphicsContextGL::ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_COLOR)
7152 && (src == GraphicsContextGL::CONSTANT_ALPHA || src == GraphicsContextGL::ONE_MINUS_CONSTANT_ALPHA))) {
7153 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, functionName, "incompatible src and dst");
7154 return false;
7155 }
7156 return true;
7157}

7168 case GraphicsContextGL::SAMPLE_COVERAGE:
7169 case GraphicsContextGL::SCISSOR_TEST:
7170 case GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_TEST:
7171 return true;
7172 default:
7173 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid capability");
7174 return false;
7175 }

7178
7179template<typename T, typename TypedListType>
7180std::optional<GCGLSpan<const T>> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateUniformMatrixParameters(const char* functionName, const WebGLUniformLocation* location, GCGLboolean transpose, const TypedList<TypedListType, T>& values, GCGLsizei requiredMinSize, GCGLuint srcOffset, GCGLuint srcLength)
7181{
7182 if (!validateUniformLocation(functionName, location))
7183 return { };
7184 if (!values.data()) {
7185 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "no array");
7186 return { };
7187 }
7188 if (transpose && !isWebGL2()) {
7189 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "transpose not FALSE");
7190 return { };
7191 }
7192 if (srcOffset >= static_cast<GCGLuint>(values.length())) {
7193 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid srcOffset");
7194 return { };
7195 }
7196 GCGLsizei actualSize = values.length() - srcOffset;
7197 if (srcLength > 0) {
7198 if (srcLength > static_cast<GCGLuint>(actualSize)) {
7199 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid srcOffset + srcLength");
7200 return { };
7201 }
7202 actualSize = srcLength;
7203 }
7204 if (actualSize < requiredMinSize || (actualSize % requiredMinSize)) {
7205 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid size");
7206 return { };
7207 }
7208 return makeGCGLSpan(values.data() + srcOffset, actualSize);
7209}

7212std::optional<GCGLSpan<const GCGLuint>> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateUniformMatrixParameters<GCGLuint, Uint32Array>(const char* functionName, const WebGLUniformLocation*, GCGLboolean transpose, const TypedList<Uint32Array, uint32_t>& values, GCGLsizei requiredMinSize, GCGLuint srcOffset, GCGLuint srcLength);

7214template
7215std::optional<GCGLSpan<const GCGLint>> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateUniformMatrixParameters<GCGLint, Int32Array>(const char* functionName, const WebGLUniformLocation*, GCGLboolean transpose, const TypedList<Int32Array, int32_t>& values, GCGLsizei requiredMinSize, GCGLuint srcOffset, GCGLuint srcLength);
7216
7217template
7218std::optional<GCGLSpan<const GCGLfloat>> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateUniformMatrixParameters<GCGLfloat, Float32Array>(const char* functionName, const WebGLUniformLocation*, GCGLboolean transpose, const TypedList<Float32Array, float>& values, GCGLsizei requiredMinSize, GCGLuint srcOffset, GCGLuint srcLength);

7220WebGLBuffer* WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateBufferDataParameters(const char* functionName, GCGLenum target, GCGLenum usage)
7221{
7222 WebGLBuffer* buffer = validateBufferDataTarget(functionName, target);
7223 if (!buffer)
7224 return nullptr;
7225 switch (usage) {
7226 case GraphicsContextGL::STREAM_DRAW:
7227 case GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_DRAW:
7228 case GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_DRAW:
7229 return buffer;
7230 case GraphicsContextGL::STREAM_COPY:
7231 case GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_COPY:
7232 case GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_COPY:
7233 case GraphicsContextGL::STREAM_READ:
7234 case GraphicsContextGL::STATIC_READ:
7235 case GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_READ:
7236 if (isWebGL2())
7237 return buffer;
7238 }
7239 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM, functionName, "invalid usage");
7240 return nullptr;
7241}

7243ExceptionOr<bool> WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateHTMLImageElement(const char* functionName, HTMLImageElement* image)
7244{
7245 if (!image || !image->cachedImage()) {
7246 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "no image");
7247 return false;
7248 }
7249 const URL& url = image->cachedImage()->response().url();
7250 if (url.isNull() || url.isEmpty() || !url.isValid()) {
7251 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid image");
7252 return false;
7253 }
7254 if (wouldTaintOrigin(image))
7255 return Exception { SecurityError };
7256 return true;
7257}

7260{

7263 return false;
7264 }
7265 if (wouldTaintOrigin(canvas))
7266 return Exception { SecurityError };
7267 return true;
7268}

7299
7300void WebGLRenderingContextBase::vertexAttribfImpl(const char* functionName, GCGLuint index, GCGLsizei expectedSize, GCGLfloat v0, GCGLfloat v1, GCGLfloat v2, GCGLfloat v3)
7301{
7302 if (isContextLostOrPending())
7303 return;
7304 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
7305 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "index out of range");
7306 return;
7307 }
7308#if !USE(ANGLE)
7309 // In GL, we skip setting vertexAttrib0 values.
7310 if (index || isGLES2Compliant())
7311#endif
7312 {
7313 switch (expectedSize) {
7314 case 1:
7315 m_context->vertexAttrib1f(index, v0);
7316 break;
7317 case 2:
7318 m_context->vertexAttrib2f(index, v0, v1);
7319 break;
7320 case 3:
7321 m_context->vertexAttrib3f(index, v0, v1, v2);
7322 break;
7323 case 4:
7324 m_context->vertexAttrib4f(index, v0, v1, v2, v3);
7325 break;
7326 }
7327 }
7328 VertexAttribValue& attribValue = m_vertexAttribValue[index];
7329 attribValue.type = GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT;
7330 attribValue.fValue[0] = v0;
7331 attribValue.fValue[1] = v1;
7332 attribValue.fValue[2] = v2;
7333 attribValue.fValue[3] = v3;
7334}
7335
7336void WebGLRenderingContextBase::vertexAttribfvImpl(const char* functionName, GCGLuint index, Float32List&& list, GCGLsizei expectedSize)
7337{
7338 if (isContextLostOrPending())
7339 return;
7340
7341 auto data = list.data();
7342 if (!data) {
7343 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "no array");
7344 return;
7345 }
7346
7347 int size = list.length();
7348 if (size < expectedSize) {
7349 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "invalid size");
7350 return;
7351 }
7352 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
7353 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, functionName, "index out of range");
7354 return;
7355 }
7356#if !USE(ANGLE)
7357 // In GL, we skip setting vertexAttrib0 values.
7358 if (index || isGLES2Compliant())
7359#endif
7360 {
7361 switch (expectedSize) {
7362 case 1:
7363 m_context->vertexAttrib1fv(index, makeGCGLSpan<1>(data));
7364 break;
7365 case 2:
7366 m_context->vertexAttrib2fv(index, makeGCGLSpan<2>(data));
7367 break;
7368 case 3:
7369 m_context->vertexAttrib3fv(index, makeGCGLSpan<3>(data));
7370 break;
7371 case 4:
7372 m_context->vertexAttrib4fv(index, makeGCGLSpan<4>(data));
7373 break;
7374 }
7375 }
7376 VertexAttribValue& attribValue = m_vertexAttribValue[index];
7377 attribValue.initValue();
7378 for (int ii = 0; ii < expectedSize; ++ii)
7379 attribValue.fValue[ii] = data[ii];
7380}
7381
7382#if !USE(ANGLE)
7383void WebGLRenderingContextBase::initVertexAttrib0()
7384{
7385 WebGLVertexArrayObjectBase::VertexAttribState& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(0);
7386
7387 m_vertexAttrib0Buffer = createBuffer();
7388 m_context->bindBuffer(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, m_vertexAttrib0Buffer->object());
7389 m_context->bufferData(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, 0, GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_DRAW);
7390 m_context->vertexAttribPointer(0, 4, GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT, false, 0, 0);
7391 state.bufferBinding = m_vertexAttrib0Buffer;
7392 m_context->bindBuffer(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, 0);
7393 m_context->enableVertexAttribArray(0);
7394 m_vertexAttrib0BufferSize = 0;
7395 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[0] = 0.0f;
7396 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[1] = 0.0f;
7397 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[2] = 0.0f;
7398 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[3] = 1.0f;
7399 m_forceAttrib0BufferRefill = false;
7400 m_vertexAttrib0UsedBefore = false;
7401}
7402
7403bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::validateSimulatedVertexAttrib0(GCGLuint numVertex)
7404{
7405 if (!m_currentProgram)
7406 return true;
7407
7408 bool usingVertexAttrib0 = m_currentProgram->isUsingVertexAttrib0();
7409 if (!usingVertexAttrib0)
7410 return true;
7411
7412 auto& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(0);
7413 if (state.enabled)
7414 return true;
7415
7416 auto bufferSize = checkedAddAndMultiply<GCGLuint>(numVertex, 1, 4);
7417 if (!bufferSize)
7418 return false;
7419
7420 Checked<GCGLsizeiptr, RecordOverflow> bufferDataSize(bufferSize.value());
7421 bufferDataSize *= Checked<GCGLsizeiptr>(sizeof(GCGLfloat));
7422 return !bufferDataSize.hasOverflowed() && bufferDataSize > 0;
7423}
7424
7425std::optional<bool> WebGLRenderingContextBase::simulateVertexAttrib0(GCGLuint numVertex)
7426{
7427 if (!m_currentProgram)
7428 return false;
7429 bool usingVertexAttrib0 = m_currentProgram->isUsingVertexAttrib0();
7430 if (usingVertexAttrib0)
7431 m_vertexAttrib0UsedBefore = true;
7432
7433 auto& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(0);
7434 if (state.enabled && usingVertexAttrib0)
7435 return false;
7436 if (!usingVertexAttrib0 && !m_vertexAttrib0UsedBefore)
7437 return false;
7438 m_vertexAttrib0UsedBefore = true;
7439 m_context->bindBuffer(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, m_vertexAttrib0Buffer->object());
7440
7441 // We know bufferSize and bufferDataSize won't overflow or go negative, thanks to validateSimulatedVertexAttrib0
7442 GCGLuint bufferSize = (numVertex + 1) * 4;
7443 GCGLsizeiptr bufferDataSize = bufferSize * sizeof(GCGLfloat);
7444
7445 if (bufferDataSize > m_vertexAttrib0BufferSize) {
7446 m_context->moveErrorsToSyntheticErrorList();
7447 m_context->bufferData(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, bufferDataSize, GraphicsContextGL::DYNAMIC_DRAW);
7448 if (m_context->getError() != GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR) {
7449 // We were unable to create a buffer.
7450 m_vertexAttrib0UsedBefore = false;
7451 m_vertexAttrib0BufferSize = 0;
7452 m_forceAttrib0BufferRefill = true;
7453 return std::nullopt;
7454 }
7455 m_vertexAttrib0BufferSize = bufferDataSize;
7456 m_forceAttrib0BufferRefill = true;
7457 }
7458
7459 auto& attribValue = m_vertexAttribValue[0];
7460 // This code shouldn't be called with WebGL2 where the type can be non-float.
7461 ASSERT(attribValue.type == GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT);
7462
7463 if (usingVertexAttrib0
7464 && (m_forceAttrib0BufferRefill
7465 || attribValue.fValue[0] != m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[0]
7466 || attribValue.fValue[1] != m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[1]
7467 || attribValue.fValue[2] != m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[2]
7468 || attribValue.fValue[3] != m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[3])) {
7469
7470 auto bufferData = makeUniqueArray<GCGLfloat>(bufferSize);
7471 for (GCGLuint ii = 0; ii < numVertex + 1; ++ii) {
7472 bufferData[ii * 4] = attribValue.fValue[0];
7473 bufferData[ii * 4 + 1] = attribValue.fValue[1];
7474 bufferData[ii * 4 + 2] = attribValue.fValue[2];
7475 bufferData[ii * 4 + 3] = attribValue.fValue[3];
7476 }
7477 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[0] = attribValue.fValue[0];
7478 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[1] = attribValue.fValue[1];
7479 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[2] = attribValue.fValue[2];
7480 m_vertexAttrib0BufferValue[3] = attribValue.fValue[3];
7481 m_forceAttrib0BufferRefill = false;
7482 m_context->bufferSubData(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, 0, makeGCGLSpan(bufferData.get(), bufferSize));
7483 }
7484 m_context->vertexAttribPointer(0, 4, GraphicsContextGL::FLOAT, 0, 0, 0);
7485 return true;
7486}
7487
7488void WebGLRenderingContextBase::restoreStatesAfterVertexAttrib0Simulation()
7489{
7490 const WebGLVertexArrayObjectBase::VertexAttribState& state = m_boundVertexArrayObject->getVertexAttribState(0);
7491 if (state.bufferBinding != m_vertexAttrib0Buffer) {
7492 m_context->bindBuffer(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, objectOrZero(state.bufferBinding.get()));
7493 m_context->vertexAttribPointer(0, state.size, state.type, state.normalized, state.originalStride, state.offset);
7494 }
7495 m_context->bindBuffer(GraphicsContextGL::ARRAY_BUFFER, objectOrZero(m_boundArrayBuffer.get()));
7496}
7497#endif
7498
7499void WebGLRenderingContextBase::scheduleTaskToDispatchContextLostEvent()
7500{
7501 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
7502 if (!canvas)
7503 return;
7504
7505 // It is safe to capture |this| because we keep the canvas element alive and it owns |this|.
7506 queueTaskKeepingObjectAlive(*canvas, TaskSource::WebGL, [this, canvas] {
7507 if (isContextStopped())
7508 return;
7509
7510 auto event = WebGLContextEvent::create(eventNames().webglcontextlostEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes, emptyString());
7511 canvas->dispatchEvent(event);
7512 m_restoreAllowed = event->defaultPrevented();
7513 if (m_contextLostMode == RealLostContext && m_restoreAllowed)
7514 m_restoreTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
7515 });
7516}
7517
7518void WebGLRenderingContextBase::maybeRestoreContext()
7519{
7520 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_isSuspended);
7521 ASSERT(m_contextLost);
7522 if (!m_contextLost)
7523 return;
7524
7525 // The rendering context is not restored unless the default behavior of the
7526 // webglcontextlost event was prevented earlier.
7527 //
7528 // Because of the way m_restoreTimer is set up for real vs. synthetic lost
7529 // context events, we don't have to worry about this test short-circuiting
7530 // the retry loop for real context lost events.
7531 if (!m_restoreAllowed)
7532 return;
7533
7534 int contextLostReason = m_context->getExtensions().getGraphicsResetStatusARB();
7535
7536 switch (contextLostReason) {
7537 case GraphicsContextGL::NO_ERROR:
7538 // The GraphicsContextGLOpenGL implementation might not fully
7539 // support GL_ARB_robustness semantics yet. Alternatively, the
7540 // WEBGL_lose_context extension might have been used to force
7541 // a lost context.
7542 break;
7543 case ExtensionsGL::GUILTY_CONTEXT_RESET_ARB:
7544 // The rendering context is not restored if this context was
7545 // guilty of causing the graphics reset.
7546 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Warning, "WARNING: WebGL content on the page caused the graphics card to reset; not restoring the context");
7547 return;
7548 case ExtensionsGL::INNOCENT_CONTEXT_RESET_ARB:
7549 // Always allow the context to be restored.
7550 break;
7551 case ExtensionsGL::UNKNOWN_CONTEXT_RESET_ARB:
7552 // Warn. Ideally, prompt the user telling them that WebGL
7553 // content on the page might have caused the graphics card to
7554 // reset and ask them whether they want to continue running
7555 // the content. Only if they say "yes" should we start
7556 // attempting to restore the context.
7557 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Warning, "WARNING: WebGL content on the page might have caused the graphics card to reset");
7558 break;
7559 }
7560
7561 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
7562 if (!canvas)
7563 return;
7564
7565 RefPtr<Frame> frame = canvas->document().frame();
7566 if (!frame)
7567 return;
7568
7569 if (!frame->loader().client().allowWebGL(frame->settings().webGLEnabled()))
7570 return;
7571
7572 RefPtr<FrameView> view = frame->view();
7573 if (!view)
7574 return;
7575 RefPtr<ScrollView> root = view->root();
7576 if (!root)
7577 return;
7578 HostWindow* hostWindow = root->hostWindow();
7579 if (!hostWindow)
7580 return;
7581
7582 RefPtr<GraphicsContextGL> context(GraphicsContextGLOpenGL::create(m_attributes, hostWindow));
7583 if (!context) {
7584 if (m_contextLostMode == RealLostContext)
7585 m_restoreTimer.startOneShot(secondsBetweenRestoreAttempts);
7586 else
7587 // This likely shouldn't happen but is the best way to report it to the WebGL app.
7588 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "", "error restoring context");
7589 return;
7590 }
7591
7592 m_context = context;
7593 addActivityStateChangeObserverIfNecessary();
7594 m_contextLost = false;
7595 setupFlags();
7596 initializeNewContext();
7597 canvas->dispatchEvent(WebGLContextEvent::create(eventNames().webglcontextrestoredEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes, emptyString()));
7598}
7599
7600void WebGLRenderingContextBase::simulateEventForTesting(SimulatedEventForTesting event)
7601{
7602 if (m_context)
7603 m_context->simulateEventForTesting(event);
7604}

7607{
7608 if (text.isNull())
7609 return WTF::emptyString();
7610 return text;
7611}

7613WebGLRenderingContextBase::LRUImageBufferCache::LRUImageBufferCache(int capacity)
7614 : m_buffers(capacity)
7615{
7616}
7617
7618ImageBuffer* WebGLRenderingContextBase::LRUImageBufferCache::imageBuffer(const IntSize& size)
7619{
7620 size_t i;
7621 for (i = 0; i < m_buffers.size(); ++i) {
7622 ImageBuffer* buf = m_buffers[i].get();
7623 if (!buf)
7624 break;
7625 if (buf->logicalSize() != size)
7626 continue;
7627 bubbleToFront(i);
7628 buf->context().clearRect(FloatRect({ }, FloatSize(size)));
7629 return buf;
7630 }
7631
7632 // FIXME (149423): Should this ImageBuffer be unconditionally unaccelerated?
7633 auto temp = ImageBuffer::create(size, RenderingMode::Unaccelerated, 1, DestinationColorSpace::SRGB(), PixelFormat::BGRA8);
7634 if (!temp)
7635 return nullptr;
7636 ASSERT(m_buffers.size() > 0);
7637 i = std::min(m_buffers.size() - 1, i);
7638 m_buffers[i] = WTFMove(temp);
7639
7640 ImageBuffer* buf = m_buffers[i].get();
7641 bubbleToFront(i);
7642 return buf;
7643}
7644
7645void WebGLRenderingContextBase::LRUImageBufferCache::bubbleToFront(size_t idx)
7646{
7647 for (size_t i = idx; i > 0; --i)
7648 m_buffers[i].swap(m_buffers[i-1]);
7649}

7653 String GetErrorString(GCGLenum error)
7654 {
7655 switch (error) {
7656 case GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_ENUM:
7657 return "INVALID_ENUM"_s;
7658 case GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE:
7659 return "INVALID_VALUE"_s;
7660 case GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION:
7661 return "INVALID_OPERATION"_s;
7662 case GraphicsContextGL::OUT_OF_MEMORY:
7663 return "OUT_OF_MEMORY"_s;
7664 case GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION:
7665 return "INVALID_FRAMEBUFFER_OPERATION"_s;
7666 case GraphicsContextGL::CONTEXT_LOST_WEBGL:
7667 return "CONTEXT_LOST_WEBGL"_s;
7668 default:
7669 return makeString("WebGL ERROR(", hex(error, 4, Lowercase), ')');
7670 }
7671 }
7672
7673} // namespace anonymous

7675void WebGLRenderingContextBase::synthesizeGLError(GCGLenum error, const char* functionName, const char* description, ConsoleDisplayPreference display)
7676{
7677 if (m_synthesizedErrorsToConsole && display == DisplayInConsole) {
7678 String str = "WebGL: " + GetErrorString(error) + ": " + String(functionName) + ": " + String(description);
7679 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Error, str);
7680 }
7681 m_context->synthesizeGLError(error);
7682}

7684void WebGLRenderingContextBase::applyStencilTest()
7685{
7686 bool haveStencilBuffer = false;
7687
7688 if (m_framebufferBinding)
7689 haveStencilBuffer = m_framebufferBinding->hasStencilBuffer();
7690 else {
7691 auto attributes = getContextAttributes();
7692 ASSERT(attributes);
7693 haveStencilBuffer = attributes->stencil;
7694 }
7695 enableOrDisable(GraphicsContextGL::STENCIL_TEST, m_stencilEnabled && haveStencilBuffer);
7696}

7698void WebGLRenderingContextBase::enableOrDisable(GCGLenum capability, bool enable)
7699{
7700 if (enable)
7701 m_context->enable(capability);
7702 else
7703 m_context->disable(capability);
7704}

7709 clamp(canvasBase().height(), 1, m_maxViewportDims[1]));

7712GCGLint WebGLRenderingContextBase::getMaxDrawBuffers()
7713{
7714 if (!supportsDrawBuffers())
7715 return 0;
7716 if (!m_maxDrawBuffers)
7717 m_maxDrawBuffers = m_context->getInteger(ExtensionsGL::MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS_EXT);
7718 if (!m_maxColorAttachments)
7719 m_maxColorAttachments = m_context->getInteger(ExtensionsGL::MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS_EXT);
7720 // WEBGL_draw_buffers requires MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS >= MAX_DRAW_BUFFERS.
7721 return std::min(m_maxDrawBuffers, m_maxColorAttachments);
7722}
7723
7724GCGLint WebGLRenderingContextBase::getMaxColorAttachments()
7725{
7726 if (!supportsDrawBuffers())
7727 return 0;
7728 if (!m_maxColorAttachments)
7729 m_maxColorAttachments = m_context->getInteger(ExtensionsGL::MAX_COLOR_ATTACHMENTS_EXT);
7730 return m_maxColorAttachments;
7731}

7738void WebGLRenderingContextBase::setFramebuffer(const AbstractLocker&, GCGLenum target, WebGLFramebuffer* buffer)
7739{
7740 if (buffer)
7741 buffer->setHasEverBeenBound();
7742
7743 if (target == GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER || target == GraphicsContextGL::DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER) {
7744 m_framebufferBinding = buffer;
7745 applyStencilTest();
7746 }
7747 m_context->bindFramebuffer(target, objectOrZero(buffer));
7748}

7750void WebGLRenderingContextBase::restoreCurrentFramebuffer()
7751{
7752 bindFramebuffer(GraphicsContextGL::FRAMEBUFFER, m_framebufferBinding.get());
7753}

7755void WebGLRenderingContextBase::restoreCurrentTexture2D()
7756{
7757 auto texture = m_textureUnits[m_activeTextureUnit].texture2DBinding.get();
7758 bindTexture(GraphicsContextGL::TEXTURE_2D, texture);
7759#if !USE(ANGLE)
7760 if (texture && texture->needToUseBlackTexture(textureExtensionFlags()))
7761 m_unrenderableTextureUnits.add(m_activeTextureUnit);
7762#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
7763}

7765bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::supportsDrawBuffers()
7766{
7767 if (!m_drawBuffersWebGLRequirementsChecked) {
7768 m_drawBuffersWebGLRequirementsChecked = true;
7769 m_drawBuffersSupported = WebGLDrawBuffers::supported(*this);
7770 }
7771 return m_drawBuffersSupported;
7772}
7773
7774void WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawArraysInstanced(GCGLenum mode, GCGLint first, GCGLsizei count, GCGLsizei primcount)
7775{
7776#if USE(ANGLE)
7777 if (isContextLostOrPending())
7778 return;
7779#else
7780 if (!validateDrawArrays("drawArraysInstanced", mode, first, count, primcount))
7781 return;
7782#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
7783
7784 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerDrawOrClear);
7785
7786#if !USE(ANGLE)
7787 bool vertexAttrib0Simulated = false;
7788 if (!isGLES2Compliant()) {
7789 auto simulateVertexAttrib0Status = simulateVertexAttrib0(first + count - 1);
7790 if (!simulateVertexAttrib0Status) {
7791 // We were unable to simulate the attribute buffer.
7792 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawArraysInstanced", "unable to simulate vertexAttrib0 array");
7793 return;
7794 }
7795 vertexAttrib0Simulated = simulateVertexAttrib0Status.value();
7796 }
7797 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
7798 checkTextureCompleteness("drawArraysInstanced", true);
7799#endif
7800
7801 m_context->drawArraysInstanced(mode, first, count, primcount);
7802
7803#if !USE(ANGLE)
7804 if (!isGLES2Compliant() && vertexAttrib0Simulated)
7805 restoreStatesAfterVertexAttrib0Simulation();
7806 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
7807 checkTextureCompleteness("drawArraysInstanced", false);
7808#endif
7809 markContextChangedAndNotifyCanvasObserver();
7810}
7811
7812void WebGLRenderingContextBase::drawElementsInstanced(GCGLenum mode, GCGLsizei count, GCGLenum type, long long offset, GCGLsizei primcount)
7813{
7814#if USE(ANGLE)
7815 if (isContextLostOrPending())
7816 return;
7817#else
7818 unsigned numElements = 0;
7819 if (!validateDrawElements("drawElementsInstanced", mode, count, type, offset, numElements, primcount))
7820 return;
7821#endif // !USE(ANGLE)
7822
7823 clearIfComposited(ClearCallerDrawOrClear);
7824
7825#if !USE(ANGLE)
7826 bool vertexAttrib0Simulated = false;
7827 if (!isGLES2Compliant()) {
7828 if (!numElements)
7829 validateIndexArrayPrecise(count, type, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), numElements);
7830 auto simulateVertexAttrib0Status = simulateVertexAttrib0(numElements);
7831 if (!simulateVertexAttrib0Status) {
7832 // We were unable to simulate the attribute buffer.
7833 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_OPERATION, "drawArraysInstanced", "unable to simulate vertexAttrib0 array");
7834 return;
7835 }
7836 vertexAttrib0Simulated = simulateVertexAttrib0Status.value();
7837 }
7838 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
7839 checkTextureCompleteness("drawElementsInstanced", true);
7840#endif
7841
7842#if USE(OPENGL) && ENABLE(WEBGL2)
7843 if (isWebGL2())
7844 static_cast<GraphicsContextGLOpenGL*>(m_context.get())->primitiveRestartIndex(getRestartIndex(type));
7845#endif
7846
7847 m_context->drawElementsInstanced(mode, count, type, static_cast<GCGLintptr>(offset), primcount);
7848
7849#if !USE(ANGLE)
7850 if (!isGLES2Compliant() && vertexAttrib0Simulated)
7851 restoreStatesAfterVertexAttrib0Simulation();
7852 if (!isGLES2NPOTStrict())
7853 checkTextureCompleteness("drawElementsInstanced", false);
7854#endif
7855 markContextChangedAndNotifyCanvasObserver();
7856}
7857
7858void WebGLRenderingContextBase::vertexAttribDivisor(GCGLuint index, GCGLuint divisor)
7859{
7860 if (isContextLostOrPending())
7861 return;
7862
7863 if (index >= m_maxVertexAttribs) {
7864 synthesizeGLError(GraphicsContextGL::INVALID_VALUE, "vertexAttribDivisor", "index out of range");
7865 return;
7866 }
7867
7868 m_boundVertexArrayObject->setVertexAttribDivisor(index, divisor);
7869 m_context->vertexAttribDivisor(index, divisor);
7870}

7872bool WebGLRenderingContextBase::enableSupportedExtension(ASCIILiteral extensionNameLiteral)
7873{
7874 ASSERT(m_context);
7875 auto& extensions = m_context->getExtensions();
7876 String extensionName { extensionNameLiteral };
7877 if (!extensions.supports(extensionName))
7878 return false;
7879 extensions.ensureEnabled(extensionName);
7880 return true;
7881}

7883void WebGLRenderingContextBase::loseExtensions(LostContextMode mode)
7884{
7885#define LOSE_EXTENSION(variable) \
7886 if (variable) { \
7887 variable->loseParentContext(mode); \
7888 if (variable->isLost()) \
7889 (void) variable.releaseNonNull(); \
7890 }
7891
7892 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extFragDepth);
7893 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extBlendMinMax);
7894 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extsRGB);
7895 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extTextureCompressionRGTC);
7896 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extTextureFilterAnisotropic);

7898 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_khrParallelShaderCompile);
7899 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureFloat);
7900 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureFloatLinear);
7901 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureHalfFloat);
7902 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesTextureHalfFloatLinear);
7903 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesStandardDerivatives);
7904 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesVertexArrayObject);
7905 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesElementIndexUint);
7906 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_oesFBORenderMipmap);
7907 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglLoseContext);
7908 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglDebugRendererInfo);
7909 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglDebugShaders);
7910 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureASTC);
7911 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureATC);
7912 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureETC);
7913 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureETC1);
7914 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTexturePVRTC);
7915 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglCompressedTextureS3TC);
7916 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglDepthTexture);
7917 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglDrawBuffers);
7918 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_angleInstancedArrays);
7919 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extColorBufferHalfFloat);
7920 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extFloatBlend);
7921 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_webglColorBufferFloat);
7922 LOSE_EXTENSION(m_extColorBufferFloat);
7923}

7925void WebGLRenderingContextBase::activityStateDidChange(OptionSet<ActivityState::Flag> oldActivityState, OptionSet<ActivityState::Flag> newActivityState)
7926{
7927 if (!m_context)
7928 return;
7929
7930 auto changed = oldActivityState ^ newActivityState;
7931 if (changed & ActivityState::IsVisible)
7932 m_context->setContextVisibility(newActivityState.contains(ActivityState::IsVisible));
7933}

7940 InspectorInstrumentation::didFinishRecordingCanvasFrame(*this);

7947
7948void WebGLRenderingContextBase::recycleContext()
7949{
7950 printToConsole(MessageLevel::Error, "There are too many active WebGL contexts on this page, the oldest context will be lost.");
7951 // Using SyntheticLostContext means the developer won't be able to force the restoration
7952 // of the context by calling preventDefault() in a "webglcontextlost" event handler.
7953 forceLostContext(SyntheticLostContext);
7954 destroyGraphicsContextGL();
7955}

7957void WebGLRenderingContextBase::dispatchContextChangedNotification()
7958{
7959 auto* canvas = htmlCanvas();
7960 if (!canvas)
7961 return;
7962
7963 queueTaskToDispatchEvent(*canvas, TaskSource::WebGL, WebGLContextEvent::create(eventNames().webglcontextchangedEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::Yes, emptyString()));
7964}
7965
7966void WebGLRenderingContextBase::addMembersToOpaqueRoots(JSC::AbstractSlotVisitor& visitor)
7967{
7968 Locker locker { objectGraphLock() };
7969
7970 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(m_boundArrayBuffer.get());
7971
7972 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(m_boundVertexArrayObject.get());
7973 if (m_boundVertexArrayObject)
7974 m_boundVertexArrayObject->addMembersToOpaqueRoots(locker, visitor);
7975
7976 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(m_currentProgram.get());
7977 if (m_currentProgram)
7978 m_currentProgram->addMembersToOpaqueRoots(locker, visitor);
7979
7980 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(m_framebufferBinding.get());
7981 if (m_framebufferBinding)
7982 m_framebufferBinding->addMembersToOpaqueRoots(locker, visitor);
7983
7984 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(m_renderbufferBinding.get());
7985
7986 for (auto& unit : m_textureUnits) {
7987 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(unit.texture2DBinding.get());
7988 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(unit.textureCubeMapBinding.get());
7989 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(unit.texture3DBinding.get());
7990 visitor.addOpaqueRoot(unit.texture2DArrayBinding.get());
7991 }
7992
7993 // Extensions' IDL files use GenerateIsReachable=ImplWebGLRenderingContext,
7994 // which checks to see whether the context is in the opaque root set (it is;
7995 // it's added in JSWebGLRenderingContext / JSWebGL2RenderingContext's custom
7996 // bindings code). For this reason it's unnecessary to explicitly add opaque
7997 // roots for extensions.
7998}
7999
8000Lock& WebGLRenderingContextBase::objectGraphLock()
8001{
8002 return m_objectGraphLock;
8003}

8011}
